mins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|discipline        = [[Archaeology]]\n|ethnicity         = Irish and Scottish decent<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|field             = [[archaeology]]\n|work_institutions = Royal Ontario Museum], Ontario, Canada\n|alma_mater        = University of Toronto, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>   & Columbia University, New York City, NY, US<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Ontario Museum of Archaeology, London, Ontario |publisher=Ontario Museum of Archaeology, London, Ontario |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|doctoral_advisor  = \n|doctoral_students = \n|known_for         = her role in excavations at Sainte-Marie among the Hurons, Ontario, in 1947. Helped establish Fanshawe Pioneer Village<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and the Museum of Ontario Archaeology<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>.\n|influences        = \n|influenced        = Wilfrid Jury<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n|prizes            = \n|religion          = \n}}\n\n==Early Life and Education:==\nElsie McLeod Murray Jury was born in Perth, Ontario,<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>   Canada in 1910<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She attended University of Toronto for a degree where she specialised in History and English<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and graduated in 1933.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She subsequently studied for a MA at Columbia University in History<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and wrote her thesis on her Scottish ancestors who had settled in Perth County, Ontario<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She was of Scottish and Irish descent and her parents had immigrated to Millbank, in Mornington Township, in Perth County, Ontario during the early 19th century.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. Elsie's father was was a doctor while her mother had raised their family<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>.\n\n==Sites Excavated:==\n* Ste. Marie, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n* Forget, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n* Penetanguishene, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Publications:==\nSole Author:\n* Jury, Elsie 1974 ''The Neutral Indians of Southwestern Ontario''. London: MIA, Bulletin 13 (Reprinted, 1977).\nJoint Author:\n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1952 The Burly Site. ''Ontario History'' 44:57-75. \n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1954 ''Sainte-Marie Among Hurons.'' Toronto: Oxford University Press. \n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1955 ''Saint Louis: Huron Village and Jesuit Mission Site.'' London: MIA, Bulletin 10.\n\n==References:==\n\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:1993 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Elsie Jury|timestamp=20200414130308|year=2020|month=April|day=14|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Elsie Jury|date=14 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{short description|Canadian archaeologist}}\n{{Infobox academic\n|name              = Elsie Jury\n|image             =\n|birth_date        = 1910<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n|birth_place       = Perth, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n|death_date        = {{death date and age|1993|3|31|1910|10|11}}\n|death_place       = Ontario, Ontario<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n|residence         = \n|citizenship       = \n|nationality       = Canadian\n|occupation        = Archaeologist, Historian, Author, and Archivist\n|spouse            = Wilfrid Jury<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|discipline        = [[Archaeology]]\n|ethnicity         = Irish and Scottish decent<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|field             = [[archaeology]]\n|work_institutions = Royal Ontario Museum], Ontario, Canada\n|alma_mater        = University of Toronto, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>   & Columbia University, New York City, NY, US<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Ontario Museum of Archaeology, London, Ontario |publisher=Ontario Museum of Archaeology, London, Ontario |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n|doctoral_advisor  = \n|doctoral_students = \n|known_for         = her role in excavations at Sainte-Marie among the Hurons, Ontario, in 1947. Helped establish Fanshawe Pioneer Village<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and the Museum of Ontario Archaeology<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>.\n|influences        = \n|influenced        = Wilfrid Jury<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n|prizes            = \n|religion          = \n}}\n\n==Early Life and Education:==\nShe was born in Perth, Ontario,<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>   Canada in 1910<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She attended University of Toronto for a degree where she specialised in History and English<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and graduated in 1933.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She subsequently studied for a MA at Columbia University in History<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> and wrote her thesis on her Scottish ancestors who had settled in Perth County, Ontario<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kanigan |first1=Joan |title=Elsie Jury Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=https://trowelblazers.com/elsie-jury/ |website=Trowelblazers |publisher=Trowelblazers |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. She was of Scottish and Irish descent and her parents had immigrated to Millbank, in Mornington Township, in Perth County, Ontario during the early 19th century.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>. Elsie's father was was a doctor while her mother had raised their family<ref>{{cite web |title=Elsie Jury: Pioneering Local Archaeology |url=http://archaeologymuseum.ca/elsie-jury/ |website=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |publisher=Museum of Ontario Archaeology |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>.\n\n==Sites Excavated:==\n* Ste. Marie, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n* Forget, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>  \n* Penetanguishene, Ontario, Canada<ref>{{cite web |title=Wilfrid Jury and the Museum of Indian Archaeology and Pioneer Life |url=https://tmhc.ca/digital-exhibits/lawson/lawson-site-jurys |website=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |publisher=Timmins Martelle Heritage Consultants Inc. |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Publications:==\nSole Author:\n* Jury, Elsie 1974 ''The Neutral Indians of Southwestern Ontario''. London: MIA, Bulletin 13 (Reprinted, 1977).\nJoint Author:\n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1952 The Burly Site. ''Ontario History'' 44:57-75. \n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1954 ''Sainte-Marie Among Hurons.'' Toronto: Oxford University Press. \n* Jury, Wilfrid and Elsie M. Jury 1955 ''Saint Louis: Huron Village and Jesuit Mission Site.'' London: MIA, Bulletin 10.\n\n==References:==\n\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:1993 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "35winds", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly Life and Education:", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elsie_Jury"}
{"title_page": "123Movies", "text_new": "{{short description|Online illlegal movie streaming site network}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = 123Movies / GoMovies\n| current_status   = Offline (clones and copy sites are still available)<ref name=\"mpaa2018\"/>\n| commercial       = Yes\n| owners           = \n| author           = \n| users            = 98 million {{small|at peak}}<ref name=\"refa\"/>\n| alexa            = \n| editors          = (Vietnamese-based)<ref name=\"mpaa2017\"/><ref name=\"mpaa2018\"/>\n| content_license  = Unlicensed<ref name=\"mpaa2016\"/>\n| registration     = Optional\n| launch_date      = est. 2015\u20132016{{efn|The MPAA only first makes comment on 123Movies in its 2016 report to the USTR; it does not appear in the MPAA 2015 report to the USTR on Notorious Markets.<ref name=\"mpaa2016\"/>  Similarly, the earliest article on TorrentFreak regarding 123Movies dates from late 2016.<ref name=\"torrent2016\">{{cite web | url=https://torrentfreak.com/uk-piracy-blocklist-expands-with-123movies-and-other-streaming-sites-161028/ | title=UK Piracy Blocklist Expands With 123movies and Other Streaming Sites|author=Ernsto|date=28 October 2016|accessdate=22 February 2019|quote=The 123movies.to website is by far the largest target on the list. The site is currently the most used pirate site in the UK, and attracts millions of daily visitors around the globe.  While the looming blockade will result in a temporary reduction in traffic, 123movies is already anticipating such measures. The streaming portal currently features a message alerting people that they have an alternative .ru domain available that may help to bypass blockades.}}</ref>}}\n| language         = English\n| logo             = Movies 123movies.png\n| logo_alt         = 123Movies, GoMovies, GoStream, 123movieshub\n| type             = Online file hosting index\n| revenue          = Advertising\n}}\n'''123Movies''', '''GoMovies''', '''GoStream''', '''MeMovies''' or '''123movieshub''' was a network of [[Streaming media|file streaming]] websites operating from Vietnam which allowed users to watch films for free. It was called the world's \"most popular illegal site\" by the [[Motion Picture Association of America]] (MPAA) in March 2018,<ref name=\"refa\"/><ref name=\"refb\"/><ref name=\":0\"/> before being shut down a few weeks later on foot of a criminal investigation by the Vietnamese authorities.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"refc\"/> {{As of|2019|12|df=}}, the network is still active via clone sites.\n\n123movies very nice\n\n==Shutdown==\n[[File:Streaming-site-123movies-to shutdown.png|thumb|The 123Movies shutdown notice.]]\nIn March 2017, ''[[TorrentFreak]]'' reported that the U.S. ambassador to Vietnam, [[Ted Osius]], had been in talks with the local Minister of Information and Communications, Truong Minh Tuan, about shutting down illegal video streaming sites operating from Vietnam, and listed 123movies as one specific site.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/us-ambassador-asks-vietnam-to-target-123movies-putlocker-and-kisscartoon-170323/|title=US Ambassador Asks Vietnam to Target 123movies, Putlocker and Kisscartoon|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://vnexpress.net/kinh-doanh/viet-my-hop-tac-chan-noi-dung-xau-tren-youtube-facebook-3559244.html|newspaper=[[VnExpress]]|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019|title=[TRANSLATED] Vietnam - US cooperates to block bad content on YouTube and Facebook}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite news|url=https://www.news.com.au/technology/online/piracy/the-worlds-largest-piracy-site-has-announced-its-closing-down-for-good-urges-people-to-buy-content/news-story/728380a53ddd4c7c576081b6a13f4d6d|title=123movies shuts down: Streaming giant warns users to stop piracy|work=[[news.com.au]]|author=Matthew Dunn|access-date=2019-01-19|quote=123movies has previously attracted the attention of the office of the US Trade Representative, having been listed in its latest Notorious Markets report which highlights markets engaging in and facilitating substantial copyright piracy and trademark counterfeiting.  Last year the US Ambassador to Vietnam also requested the local Government criminally prosecute 123movies and other piracy sites running from the country.}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, the MPAA listed 123Movies (and GoStream.is) in its ''Online Notorious Markets'' overview to the [[Office of the United States Trade Representative]], stating that while the site was technically hosted from [[Ukraine]] that: \"The site takes numerous steps to hide the identity of the\noperator, including using [[Cloudflare]], but there is strong reason to believe the operator is still in [[Vietnam]]; content is uploaded using [[cyberlockers]] from numerous email accounts originating from [[Can Tho University|Can Tho University of Medicine and Pharmacy]]\".<ref name=\"mpaa2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mpaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/notorious-markets-final.pdf|title=Letter to Christine Peterson, Director for Intellectual Property and Innovation|date=2 October 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=[[Charles Rivkin]] (CEO MPAA)|quote= 123movies, now redirects to Gostream.is, the latest iteration of which is a very popular streaming website that embeds popular movie and series content from third-party cyberlockers. The site has undergone changes in 2016-2017, rebranding as gomovies in March 2017, and then the domain name registered as gostream in July 2017; it is believed this is due in part to highprofile pressure. Gostream currently has a global Alexa rank of 477 and a local rank of 170 in the U.S. Gostream (and its associated domains) garnered 18.45 million unique visitors in July 2017 according to SimilarWeb data.}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/why-did-the-worlds-largest-streaming-site-suddenly-shut-down-180401/|title=Why Did The World's Largest Streaming Site Suddenly Shut Down?|date=1 April 2018|website=[[TorrentFreak]]| author=Ernesto|language=en|accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn March 2018, the MPAA said that the site was the \"most popular illegal site in the world\", stated it was operated from Vietnam and estimated that it received 98 million visitors per month.<ref name=\"refa\">{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/world-s-most-popular-pirated-movie-site-being-run-from-vietnam-us-trade-association-3722948.html|title=World's most popular pirated movie site being run from Vietnam: US trade association|date=15 March 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=An Nguyen|newspaper=[[VnExpress]]|quote=\"Right now, the most popular illegal site in the world, 123movies.to (at this point), is operated from Vietnam, and has 98 million visitors a month,\" said Jan van Voorn, executive vice president & chief of Global Content Protection at the MPAA.}}</ref><ref name=\"refb\">{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.com.au/worlds-most-popular-illegal-site-says-goodbye-encourages-paying-movies-shows-1566346|title=World's 'most popular illegal site' says goodbye, encourages paying for movies, shows|newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|author=Dan Perez|date=21 March 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|quote=Speaking to VN Express, van Voorn said that the website is being operated in  Vietnam and has 98 million visitors per month. The MPAA was in Vietnam for a global campaign dealing with illegal piracy sites.}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/mpaa-brands-123movies-as-the-worlds-most-popular-illegal-site-180316/|title=MPAA Brands 123Movies as the World's Most Popular Illegal Site|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19|date=16 March 2018|author=Ernesto|quote=\u201cRight now, the most popular illegal site in the world, 123movies.to (at this point), is operated from Vietnam, and has 98 million visitors a month,\u201d Van Voorn said, quoted by VNExpress.}}</ref>  On 19 March 2018, a note on the site's home page announced its shutdown, and urged users to \"respect filmmakers by paying for movies and TV-shows\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/pirate-streaming-giant-123movies-announces-shutdown-180319/|title=Pirate Streaming Giant 123Movies Announces Shutdown|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=Ernesto|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|quote=According to a message posted on the site, it will close its doors at the end of the week. At the same time, the operators are now urging their users to respect filmmakers by paying for movies and TV-shows.}}</ref><ref name=\"refc\">{{cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/science-technology/934391/123Movies-Not-Working-Shut-Down|title=World's 'most popular illegal site' 123Movies SHUTS DOWN, warns users to STOP streaming|author=Arron Brown|date=22 March 2018|accessdate=19 February 2019|newspaper=[[Daily Express]]}}</ref><ref name=\":6\"/>\n\n==Reappearance==\n\nIn October 2018, the MPAA's update on ''Online Notorious Markets'' to the United States Trade Representative, said that the closure of 123movies, 123movieshub, gostream, and gomovies, on foot of a criminal investigation in Vietnam in 2018, was \"an important development\" in combatting illegal film piracy services.  However, the MPAA report also noted that numerous copycat sites had emerged in at least eight other countries.<ref name=\"mpaa2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mpaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/notorious-markets-final.pdf|title=Letter to Sung Chang, Director for Intellectual Property and Innovation|date=1 October 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=[[Charles Rivkin]] (CEO MPAA)|quote= An important development in 2018 was the shuttering of a ring of piracy services that had operated under the names 123movies, 123movieshub, gostream, and gomovies following the launch of a criminal investigation in Vietnam and significant industry engagement. Since its closure, many copycat sites have emerged. This ring of piracy services had been blocked in at least eight countries prior to its shut down and efforts are underway to shut down the copycats as well:}}</ref><ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/123movies-was-shut-down-following-a-criminal-investigation-181005/|title=123movies Was Shut Down Following a Criminal Investigation|date=2018-10-05|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>  In November 2018 ''TorrentFreak'' reported sites connected or similar to 123Movies such as ''WatchAsap'' had also been shut down by the [[FBI]], but were re-directing to other file sharing sites.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/is-there-a-mysterious-criminal-case-against-watchasap-181118/|title=Is There a Mysterious Criminal Case Against WatchAsap?|date=2018-11-18|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of websites blocked in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Putlocker]], similar online movie streaming network\n*[[YIFY]] Torrents (or YTS Torrents), online movie file downloading network\n*[[Popcorn Time]], a [[freeware]] program allowing users to watch movies through torrenting on several platforms.\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.mpaa.org/policy-statement/mpaa-comments-to-ustr-on-notorious-markets/ MPAA Research on Notorious Markets]\n\n{{VOD services}}\n{{BitTorrent}}\n{{Intellectual property activism}}\n{{Tor hidden services}}\n{{Portal bar|Internet|Freedom of speech}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:123Movies}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:BitTorrent websites]]\n[[Category:Defunct video on demand services]]\n[[Category:Defunct websites]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of disestablishment missing]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of establishment missing]]\n[[Category:Streaming media systems]]\n[[Category:Internet services shut down by a legal challenge]]\n[[Category:Internet censorship]]\n[[Category:Notorious markets]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Online illlegal movie streaming site network}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = 123Movies / GoMovies\n| current_status   = Offline (clones and copy sites are still available)<ref name=\"mpaa2018\"/>\n| commercial       = Yes\n| owners           = \n| author           = \n| users            = 98 million {{small|at peak}}<ref name=\"refa\"/>\n| alexa            = \n| editors          = (Vietnamese-based)<ref name=\"mpaa2017\"/><ref name=\"mpaa2018\"/>\n| content_license  = Unlicensed<ref name=\"mpaa2016\"/>\n| registration     = Optional\n| launch_date      = est. 2015\u20132016{{efn|The MPAA only first makes comment on 123Movies in its 2016 report to the USTR; it does not appear in the MPAA 2015 report to the USTR on Notorious Markets.<ref name=\"mpaa2016\"/>  Similarly, the earliest article on TorrentFreak regarding 123Movies dates from late 2016.<ref name=\"torrent2016\">{{cite web | url=https://torrentfreak.com/uk-piracy-blocklist-expands-with-123movies-and-other-streaming-sites-161028/ | title=UK Piracy Blocklist Expands With 123movies and Other Streaming Sites|author=Ernsto|date=28 October 2016|accessdate=22 February 2019|quote=The 123movies.to website is by far the largest target on the list. The site is currently the most used pirate site in the UK, and attracts millions of daily visitors around the globe.  While the looming blockade will result in a temporary reduction in traffic, 123movies is already anticipating such measures. The streaming portal currently features a message alerting people that they have an alternative .ru domain available that may help to bypass blockades.}}</ref>}}\n| language         = English\n| logo             = Movies 123movies.png\n| logo_alt         = 123Movies, GoMovies, GoStream, 123movieshub\n| type             = Online file hosting index\n| revenue          = Advertising\n}}\n'''123Movies''', '''GoMovies''', '''GoStream''', '''MeMovies''' or '''123movieshub''' was a network of [[Streaming media|file streaming]] websites operating from Vietnam which allowed users to watch films for free. It was called the world's \"most popular illegal site\" by the [[Motion Picture Association of America]] (MPAA) in March 2018,<ref name=\"refa\"/><ref name=\"refb\"/><ref name=\":0\"/> before being shut down a few weeks later on foot of a criminal investigation by the Vietnamese authorities.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"refc\"/> {{As of|2019|12|df=}}, the network is still active via clone sites.\n\n==Development==\n[[File:GoMovies Logo.png|thumb|GoMovies logo]]\nThe site went through several name changes after being shut down from different domains; sometimes the name appeared as \"123Movies\", and other times as \"123movies\". The original name, and URL, was '''123movies.to''', which changed to other domains including 123movies.is before redirecting to gomovies.to and later gomovies.is.<ref name=\"mpaa2017\"/><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/pirate-streaming-site-123movies-rebrands-as-gomovies-170329/|title=Pirate Streaming Site 123Movies Rebrands as GoMovies (Updated)|date=2017-03-29|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/gomovies-moves-to-gostream-is-and-evades-google-ban-170714/|title=GoMovies Moves to GoStream.is and Evades Google 'Ban'|date=2017-07-14|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref> It was changed to gostream.is, and then to memovies.to, before changing to 123movieshub.to/is and remaining there until shutdown.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn October 2016, the MPAA listed 123Movies in its ''Online Notorious Markets'' overview to the [[Office of the United States Trade Representative]] (USTR), stating that: \"The site has a global Alexa rank of 559 and a local rank of 386 in the U.S. 123movies.to had 9.26 million worldwide unique visitors in August 2016 according to SimilarWeb data\".<ref name=\"mpaa2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mpaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/MPAA-Notorious-Markets-2016-Final.pdf|title=Letter to Christine Peterson, Director for Intellectual Property and Innovation|date=7 October 2016|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=Joanna McIntosh (Executive Vice President)|quote  =The site has a global Alexa rank of 559 and a local rank of 386 in the U.S. 123movies.to had 9.26 million worldwide unique visitors in August 2016 according to SimilarWeb data. The site is currently using a chain of reverse proxy services in the United States, Iran and Romania to curb rights holders\u2019 ability to identify its precise host.}}</ref> In October 2016, ''[[Business Insider]]'' reported that 123movies.to was the \"most-used pirate website\" in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/13-illegal-movie-tv-streaming-sites-blocked-in-uk-2016-10?r=US&IR=T|title=13 more illegal movie and TV streaming sites have been blocked in the UK|website=[[Business Insider]]|author=James Cook|date=28 October 2019|quote=TorrentFreak points out that 123movies.to, one of the newly blocked sites, is actually the most-used pirate website in the UK.|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"torrent2016\"/>\n\n123Movies included HD, HD-RIP, [[Blu-ray]] and [[Cam (bootleg)|camera]] qualities of films.  The video hosters and players it used included Openload, Streamango, and MyCloud.  During its existence and shutdown period, the site was covered by ''[[TorrentFreak]]'' regarding its features, uptime/downtime, shutdown, and reasons for shutdown.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/gomovies123movies-launches-anime-streaming-site-171204/|title=GoMovies/123Movies Launches Anime Streaming Site|date=2017-12-04|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":12\" /><ref name=\":11\" /><ref name=\":10\" />\n\nIn December 2017, the creators of 123movies launched another streaming site dedicated to [[anime]], named AnimeHub.to, which remained online for months after 123Movies's shutdown.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n==Shutdown==\n[[File:Streaming-site-123movies-to shutdown.png|thumb|The 123Movies shutdown notice.]]\nIn March 2017, ''[[TorrentFreak]]'' reported that the U.S. ambassador to Vietnam, [[Ted Osius]], had been in talks with the local Minister of Information and Communications, Truong Minh Tuan, about shutting down illegal video streaming sites operating from Vietnam, and listed 123movies as one specific site.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/us-ambassador-asks-vietnam-to-target-123movies-putlocker-and-kisscartoon-170323/|title=US Ambassador Asks Vietnam to Target 123movies, Putlocker and Kisscartoon|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://vnexpress.net/kinh-doanh/viet-my-hop-tac-chan-noi-dung-xau-tren-youtube-facebook-3559244.html|newspaper=[[VnExpress]]|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019|title=[TRANSLATED] Vietnam - US cooperates to block bad content on YouTube and Facebook}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite news|url=https://www.news.com.au/technology/online/piracy/the-worlds-largest-piracy-site-has-announced-its-closing-down-for-good-urges-people-to-buy-content/news-story/728380a53ddd4c7c576081b6a13f4d6d|title=123movies shuts down: Streaming giant warns users to stop piracy|work=[[news.com.au]]|author=Matthew Dunn|access-date=2019-01-19|quote=123movies has previously attracted the attention of the office of the US Trade Representative, having been listed in its latest Notorious Markets report which highlights markets engaging in and facilitating substantial copyright piracy and trademark counterfeiting.  Last year the US Ambassador to Vietnam also requested the local Government criminally prosecute 123movies and other piracy sites running from the country.}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, the MPAA listed 123Movies (and GoStream.is) in its ''Online Notorious Markets'' overview to the [[Office of the United States Trade Representative]], stating that while the site was technically hosted from [[Ukraine]] that: \"The site takes numerous steps to hide the identity of the\noperator, including using [[Cloudflare]], but there is strong reason to believe the operator is still in [[Vietnam]]; content is uploaded using [[cyberlockers]] from numerous email accounts originating from [[Can Tho University|Can Tho University of Medicine and Pharmacy]]\".<ref name=\"mpaa2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mpaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/notorious-markets-final.pdf|title=Letter to Christine Peterson, Director for Intellectual Property and Innovation|date=2 October 2017|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=[[Charles Rivkin]] (CEO MPAA)|quote= 123movies, now redirects to Gostream.is, the latest iteration of which is a very popular streaming website that embeds popular movie and series content from third-party cyberlockers. The site has undergone changes in 2016-2017, rebranding as gomovies in March 2017, and then the domain name registered as gostream in July 2017; it is believed this is due in part to highprofile pressure. Gostream currently has a global Alexa rank of 477 and a local rank of 170 in the U.S. Gostream (and its associated domains) garnered 18.45 million unique visitors in July 2017 according to SimilarWeb data.}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/why-did-the-worlds-largest-streaming-site-suddenly-shut-down-180401/|title=Why Did The World's Largest Streaming Site Suddenly Shut Down?|date=1 April 2018|website=[[TorrentFreak]]| author=Ernesto|language=en|accessdate=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn March 2018, the MPAA said that the site was the \"most popular illegal site in the world\", stated it was operated from Vietnam and estimated that it received 98 million visitors per month.<ref name=\"refa\">{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/world-s-most-popular-pirated-movie-site-being-run-from-vietnam-us-trade-association-3722948.html|title=World's most popular pirated movie site being run from Vietnam: US trade association|date=15 March 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=An Nguyen|newspaper=[[VnExpress]]|quote=\"Right now, the most popular illegal site in the world, 123movies.to (at this point), is operated from Vietnam, and has 98 million visitors a month,\" said Jan van Voorn, executive vice president & chief of Global Content Protection at the MPAA.}}</ref><ref name=\"refb\">{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.com.au/worlds-most-popular-illegal-site-says-goodbye-encourages-paying-movies-shows-1566346|title=World's 'most popular illegal site' says goodbye, encourages paying for movies, shows|newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|author=Dan Perez|date=21 March 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|quote=Speaking to VN Express, van Voorn said that the website is being operated in  Vietnam and has 98 million visitors per month. The MPAA was in Vietnam for a global campaign dealing with illegal piracy sites.}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/mpaa-brands-123movies-as-the-worlds-most-popular-illegal-site-180316/|title=MPAA Brands 123Movies as the World's Most Popular Illegal Site|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19|date=16 March 2018|author=Ernesto|quote=\u201cRight now, the most popular illegal site in the world, 123movies.to (at this point), is operated from Vietnam, and has 98 million visitors a month,\u201d Van Voorn said, quoted by VNExpress.}}</ref>  On 19 March 2018, a note on the site's home page announced its shutdown, and urged users to \"respect filmmakers by paying for movies and TV-shows\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/pirate-streaming-giant-123movies-announces-shutdown-180319/|title=Pirate Streaming Giant 123Movies Announces Shutdown|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=Ernesto|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|quote=According to a message posted on the site, it will close its doors at the end of the week. At the same time, the operators are now urging their users to respect filmmakers by paying for movies and TV-shows.}}</ref><ref name=\"refc\">{{cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/science-technology/934391/123Movies-Not-Working-Shut-Down|title=World's 'most popular illegal site' 123Movies SHUTS DOWN, warns users to STOP streaming|author=Arron Brown|date=22 March 2018|accessdate=19 February 2019|newspaper=[[Daily Express]]}}</ref><ref name=\":6\"/>\n\n==Reappearance==\n\nIn October 2018, the MPAA's update on ''Online Notorious Markets'' to the United States Trade Representative, said that the closure of 123movies, 123movieshub, gostream, and gomovies, on foot of a criminal investigation in Vietnam in 2018, was \"an important development\" in combatting illegal film piracy services.  However, the MPAA report also noted that numerous copycat sites had emerged in at least eight other countries.<ref name=\"mpaa2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mpaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/notorious-markets-final.pdf|title=Letter to Sung Chang, Director for Intellectual Property and Innovation|date=1 October 2018|accessdate=21 February 2019|author=[[Charles Rivkin]] (CEO MPAA)|quote= An important development in 2018 was the shuttering of a ring of piracy services that had operated under the names 123movies, 123movieshub, gostream, and gomovies following the launch of a criminal investigation in Vietnam and significant industry engagement. Since its closure, many copycat sites have emerged. This ring of piracy services had been blocked in at least eight countries prior to its shut down and efforts are underway to shut down the copycats as well:}}</ref><ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/123movies-was-shut-down-following-a-criminal-investigation-181005/|title=123movies Was Shut Down Following a Criminal Investigation|date=2018-10-05|website=[[TorrentFreak]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>  In November 2018 ''TorrentFreak'' reported sites connected or similar to 123Movies such as ''WatchAsap'' had also been shut down by the [[FBI]], but were re-directing to other file sharing sites.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/is-there-a-mysterious-criminal-case-against-watchasap-181118/|title=Is There a Mysterious Criminal Case Against WatchAsap?|date=2018-11-18|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of websites blocked in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Putlocker]], similar online movie streaming network\n*[[YIFY]] Torrents (or YTS Torrents), online movie file downloading network\n*[[Popcorn Time]], a [[freeware]] program allowing users to watch movies through torrenting on several platforms.\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.mpaa.org/policy-statement/mpaa-comments-to-ustr-on-notorious-markets/ MPAA Research on Notorious Markets]\n\n{{VOD services}}\n{{BitTorrent}}\n{{Intellectual property activism}}\n{{Tor hidden services}}\n{{Portal bar|Internet|Freedom of speech}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:123Movies}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:BitTorrent websites]]\n[[Category:Defunct video on demand services]]\n[[Category:Defunct websites]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of disestablishment missing]]\n[[Category:Companies with year of establishment missing]]\n[[Category:Streaming media systems]]\n[[Category:Internet services shut down by a legal challenge]]\n[[Category:Internet censorship]]\n[[Category:Notorious markets]]\n", "name_user": "185.236.134.88", "label": "vandal", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eDevelopment)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/123Movies"}
{"title_page": "Landelino Lavilla Alsina", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Spanish name|Lavilla|Alsina}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name =Landelino Lavilla Alsina\n| image   = Leopoldo Calvo-Sotelo conversa con el presidente del Congreso, Landelino Lavilla (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize =\n| caption = Landelino Lavilla in 1981.\n| office2 = [[Ministry of Justice (Spain)|Minister of Justice]]\n| primeminister =  [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez]] \n| predecessor2 = Antonio Garrigues y D\u00edaz-Ca\u00f1abate\n| successor2 = [[\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero|\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero Lataillade]] \n| term_start2 = 5 July 1976\n| term_end2 =  6 April 1979\n||office        = [[President of the Congress of Deputies]]\n|monarch        = [[Juan Carlos I]]\n|term_start     = 6 April 1979\n|term_end       = 18 November 1982\n|predecessor    = [[Fernando \u00c1lvarez de Miranda]]\n|successor      = [[Gregorio Peces-Barba]]\n| office3       = Member of the [[Congress of Deputies]]\n| constituency3 = [[Ja\u00e9n (Congress of Deputies constituency)|Ja\u00e9n]] \n| term_start3   = 6 April 1979\n| term_end3     =  18 November 1982\n| constituency4 = [[Madrid]] \n| term_start4   = 18 November 1982\n| term_end4     =  28 July 1983\n| office5       = Member of the [[Spanish Senate|Senate]]\n| constituency5 =Royal appointment\n| term_start5 = 15 June 1977\n| term_end5 =  6 April 1979\n| birth_date ={{birth date|1934|8|6|df=y}} \n| birth_place = [[Lerida]], Spain\n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2020|04|13|1934|8|6}}\n| death_place      = [[Madrid]], Spain\n| restingplace     = \n| party =[[Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain)|Union of the Democratic Centre]]\n| residence = \n| alma_mater =[[University of Zaragoza]]<br/>[[Complutense University of Madrid]]\n| spouse = Juana Rubira\n| nationality = Spanish\n| religion= \n| children = 4\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Landelino Lavilla Alsina''' (6 August 1934&nbsp;\u2013 13 April 2020) was a Spanish lawyer and politician who served as the [[Ministry of Justice (Spain)|Minister of Justice]] from 1976 to 1979. He also served as member of parliament and as senator. His most important role was as [[President of the Congress of Deputies]] during the coup d'\u00e9tat of [[23-F]] in 1981. Jurist [[Eduardo Garc\u00eda de Enterr\u00eda]] called him the \"principal architect of the [[Spanish transition to democracy|transition to democracy]]\".<ref>[https://elpais.com/espana/2020-04-13/sin-tacha-ni-reproche.html Sin tacha ni reproche.] ''El Pa\u00eds'', 14 April 2020. {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nLavilla was born in [[Lerida]] on 6 August 1934.<ref name=wwspain>{{cite web|title=Landelino Lavilla Alsina|url=http://195.75.145.68/whoiswho/ricerca-spain.php?code=SBWWWBTIWW|work=Who's Who in Spain|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304022510/http://195.75.145.68/whoiswho/ricerca-spain.php?code=SBWWWBTIWW|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He received law degree from [[University of Zaragoza|the University of Zaragoza]] and [[Complutense University of Madrid]].<ref name=wwspain/>\n\n==Career and activities==\nLavilla was a lawyer by profession.<ref name=ctp90>{{cite book|title=Elites and power in Twentieth-Century Spain|year=1990|publisher=Clarendon Press|location=Oxford|url=http://www.transicion.org/134bibliografia/TheTacitoGroupAndTheTransitionToDemocracy.pdf|author=Charles T. Powell|editor=F. Lannon and P. Preston|accessdate=9 September 2013|chapter=The 'Tacito' group and the transition to democracy, 1973-1977}}</ref> He joined the board of lawyers of the [[Court of Auditors (Spain)|Court of Auditors]] in 1958 and of the [[Spanish Council of State|Sate Council]] in 1959.<ref name=fride>{{cite web|title=Research Team|url=http://www.fride.org/expert/303/landelino-lavilla|work=FRIDE|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928145530/http://www.fride.org/expert/303/landelino-lavilla|archive-date=28 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> He joined the ''T\u00e1citos'', Catholic reformist group, in 1974.<ref name=wwspain/> He became a senior member of the [[Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain)|Christian Democratic Party]].<ref name=Rodgers1999>{{cite book|author=Eamonn J. Rodgers|title=Encyclopedia of Contemporary Spanish Culture|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ymIXLhegGnwC&pg=PA297|accessdate=5 June 2013|year=1999|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-0-415-13187-2|page=297}}</ref> The group published articles in the Catholic daily, ''Ya'', beginning by 1972.<ref name=paulp/> He was the undersecretary of industry in the last cabinet of [[Francisco Franco|Franco]] from 1974 to 1976.<ref name=wwspain/><ref name=paulp>{{cite book|title=The Triumph of Democracy in Spain|year=1990|publisher=Routledge|location=London|url=https://www.questia.com/read/105572789/the-triumph-of-democracy-in-spain|author=Paul Preston|accessdate=9 September 2013}} {{Subscription required|via=Questia}}</ref><ref name=Eaton1981>{{cite book|author=S. D. Eaton|title=The Forces of Freedom in Spain: 1974 - 1979 ; a Personal Account|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Zy_3t4VGLREC&pg=PA156|accessdate=5 June 2013|year=1981|publisher=Hoover Press|isbn=978-0-8179-7453-4|page=156}}</ref>\n\n===Minister of Justice===\nHe was appointed minister of justice in the [[Su\u00e1rez I Government|first cabinet]] of [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez]] on 5 July 1976, replacing Antonio Garrigues y D\u00edaz-Ca\u00f1abate in the post.<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1976/07/08/pdfs/A13385-13385.pdf \"Real Decreto 1607/1976, de 7 de julio, por el que que se nombran los Ministros del Gobierno\"] ''[[Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado]]'', 7 July 1976.</ref><ref name=rulers/> He retained his post following [[1977 Spanish general election|the democratic elections]] in June 1977.<ref>{{cite web|title=Collective Memory of the Spanish Civil War|url=http://www.march.es/ceacs/publicaciones/working/archivos/1996_85.pdf|work=Estudio/Working Paper|accessdate=9 September 2013|author=Paloma Aguilar|date=December 1996}}</ref> \n\nHe drafted the [[1977 Political Reform Act]] that was approved by the congress in November 1977 and implemented a legal process that paved the way for the legalization of all major political groups, including communists and [[PSOE]].<ref name=ctp90/> \n\nLavilla's term ended on 6 April 1979<ref name=\"boe.es\">[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1979/03/23/pdfs/A07119-07119.pdf Real Decreto 548/1979, de 22 de marzo, por el que se dispone el cese en sus funciones del Ministro de Justicia, don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'' 22 March 1979</ref> when [[\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero]] was appointed justice minister.<ref name=rulers>{{cite web|title=Spanish justice ministers|url=http://www.rulers.org/spangovt.html|work=Rulers|accessdate=9 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"boe.es\"/>\n\n===President of the Congress of Deputies and 23-F===\nHe was appointed senator in 1977 and was in office until 1978.<ref name=fride/> He was elected to the congress of deputies in 1979, representing [[Ja\u00e9n (Spanish Congress Electoral District)|Ja\u00e9n province]].\n\nHe served as speaker of the Congress from 1979 to 1982. On [[23-F|23 February 1981]], members of the [[Civil Guard (Spain)|Civil Guard]] led by [[Antonio Tejero]] burst into the chamber in a failed [[coup d'\u00e9tat]]. Lavilla faced Tejero saying that \"in this chamber, the orders are given by the presidency. This is over. Evict\". The colonel obeyed and the deputies were able to occupy their seats after getting down.<ref name=Rodgers1999/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/opinion/20181216/landelino-lavilla-pp-psoe-no-suarez-vox/360963905_0.html|title=Landelino Lavilla: \"De PP, PSOE o Cs, no lo s\u00e9... pero seguro que Su\u00e1rez nunca se habr\u00eda hecho de Vox\"|first=Ram\u00edrez|last=Daniel|date=16 December 2018|publisher=El Espa\u00f1ol}}</ref> During the night of 23\u201324, he offered Tejero the members of the parliament Board as hostages and asked that they free the [[Su\u00e1rez III Government|members of the government]] and the legislators, but he rejected it.<ref name=Rodgers1999/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://elpais.com/diario/1981/03/13/espana/353286004_850215.html|title=Landelino Lavilla ofreci\u00f3 como rehenes a los miembros de la Mesa del Congreso|first=Ediciones El|last=Pa\u00eds|newspaper=El Pa\u00eds|date=13 March 1981|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nBefore [[1982 Spanish general election|the 1982 general election]] he led the Christian Democrat party.<ref>{{cite news|title=Spanish socialist a darling of public, if not army|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1982/10/13/world/spanish-socialist-a-darling-of-public-if-not-army.html|accessdate=9 September 2013|newspaper=The New York Times|date=13 October 1982|author=R. W. Apple Jr.|location=Madrid}}</ref> He was re-elected in 1982, representing [[Madrid (Spanish Congress Electoral District)|Madrid province]], but resigned from office in 1983.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n===Member of the Council of State and later life===\nHe was named permanent member of the [[Spanish Council of State|Council of State]] by Royal Decree on 28 July 1983 at the proposal of Prime Minister,<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1983/08/09/pdfs/A22027-22027.pdf Real Decreto 2126/1983, de 28 de julio, por el que se nombra Consejero permanente de Estado a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 28 July 1983</ref> office he held until his death in 2020.<ref>[http://www.consejo-estado.es/directorio.htm Directorio] Council of State official page.</ref> On 28 December 1995 he was appointed chairman of the Council's first section.<ref>[https://www.boe.es/buscar/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1996-89 Real Decreto 2213/1995, de 28 de diciembre, por el que se nombra Presidente de la Secci\u00f3n Primera del Consejo de Estado a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina, Consejero permanente de Estado.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 28 December 1995</ref>\n\nOn 8 February 1999 he took office as permanent member of the [[Royal Academy of Jurisprudence and Legislation]]<ref>[http://www.rajyl.es/academicos/academicos-de-numero-rajyl.aspx?fldNewsID=79&secId=1 Excmo. Sr. D. LANDELINO LAVILLA ALSINA (Md. n\u00ba 6)] {{in lang|es}}</ref> and was its president between 2003 and 2012, being re-elected in 2008.<ref name=fride/><ref>[http://www.elnotario.es/index.php/hemeroteca/revista-17/2124-landelino-lavilla-reelegido-presidente-de-la-real-academia-de-jurisprudencia-y-legislacion-0-985736902789899 Landelino Lavilla, reelegido presidente de la Real Academia de Jurisprudencia y Legislaci\u00f3n] El Notario.</ref>\n\nIn addition, he was a member of the advisory committee of [[FRIDE]], [[Madrid]]-based now defunct [[Think tank|think tank organization]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Advisory Committee|url=http://www.fride.org/page/8/|work=FRIDE|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927080225/http://www.fride.org/page/8/|archive-date=27 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLavilla was married to Juana Rubira Garc\u00eda Valdecasas and they had four children.<ref name=wwspain/> He died on 13 April 2020 at the age of 85 from an undisclosed [[illness]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/abci-muere-landelino-lavilla-ministro-justicia-suarez-y-presidente-congreso-23-f-202004131259_noticia.html|title=Muere Landelino Lavilla, ministro de Justicia con Su\u00e1rez y presidente del Congreso el 23-F|date=13 April 2020|access-date=13 April 2020|newspaper=ABC|publisher=Vocento|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/espana/politica/20200413/muere-landelino-lavilla-congreso-justicia-adolfo-suarez/482202127_0.html|title=Muere Landelino Lavilla, presidente del Congreso el 23-F y ministro de Justicia de Adolfo Su\u00e1rez|date=13 April 2020|website=El Espa\u00f1ol|language=es-ES|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Honors==\n*[[File:Order of Civil Merit (Spain) GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Civil Merit|Grand Cross of the Order of Civil Merit]] (1974).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1974/10/01/pdfs/A19999-19999.pdf Real Decreto 2727/1974, de 30 de septiembre, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden del M\u00e9rito Civil a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 30 September 1974.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP Charles III Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Charles III|Grand Cross of the Order of Charles III]] (1979).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1979/03/24/pdfs/A07225-07225.pdf Real Decreto 563/1979, de 23 de marzo, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Real y Muy Distinguida Orden de Carlos III a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 23 March 1979.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP St Raymond of Penyafort Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of St. Raymond of Pe\u00f1afort|Grand Cross of the Order of St. Raymond of Pe\u00f1afort]] (1985).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1985/04/16/pdfs/A10113-10113.pdf Real Decreto 503/1985, de 10 de abril, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden de San Raimundo de Pe\u00f1afort a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 10 April 1985.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP Isabella Catholic Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Isabella the Catholic|Knight Grand Cross of the Order of Isabella the Catholic]] (2010).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2010/06/26/pdfs/BOE-A-2010-10195.pdf Real Decreto 834/2010, de 25 de junio, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden de Isabel la Cat\u00f3lica a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 25 June 2010.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lavilla Alsina, Landelino}}\n[[Category:1934 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Complutense University of Madrid alumni]]\n[[Category:Justice ministers of Spain]]\n[[Category:Members of the Senate of Spain]]\n[[Category:Members of the constituent Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 1st Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 2nd Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Spanish transition to democracy]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Cross of the Order of Isabella the Catholic]]\n[[Category:Catalan politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Lleida]]\n[[Category:Spanish lawyers]]\n[[Category:University of Zaragoza alumni]]\n[[Category:Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain) politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Spanish name|Lavilla|Alsina}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name =Landelino Lavilla Alsina\n| image   = Leopoldo Calvo-Sotelo conversa con el presidente del Congreso, Landelino Lavilla (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize =\n| caption = Landelino Lavilla in 1981.\n| office2 = [[Ministry of Justice (Spain)|Minister of Justice]]\n| primeminister =  [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez]] \n| predecessor2 = Antonio Garrigues y D\u00edaz-Ca\u00f1abate\n| successor2 = [[\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero|\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero Lataillade]] \n| term_start2 = 5 July 1976\n| term_end2 =  6 April 1979\n||office        = [[President of the Congress of Deputies]]\n|monarch        = [[Juan Carlos I]]\n|term_start     = 6 April 1979\n|term_end       = 18 November 1982\n|predecessor    = [[Fernando \u00c1lvarez de Miranda]]\n|successor      = [[Gregorio Peces-Barba]]\n| office3       = Member of the [[Congress of Deputies]]\n| constituency3 = [[Ja\u00e9n (Congress of Deputies constituency)|Ja\u00e9n]] \n| term_start3   = 6 April 1979\n| term_end3     =  18 November 1982\n| constituency4 = [[Madrid]] \n| term_start4   = 18 November 1982\n| term_end4     =  28 July 1983\n| office5       = Member of the [[Spanish Senate|Senate]]\n| constituency5 =Royal appointment\n| term_start5 = 15 June 1977\n| term_end5 =  6 April 1979\n| birth_date ={{birth date|1934|8|6|df=y}} \n| birth_place = [[Lerida]], Spain\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2020|04|13|1934|8|6}}\n| death_place      = [[Madrid]], Spain\n| restingplace     = \n| party =[[Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain)|Union of the Democratic Centre]]\n| residence = \n| alma_mater =[[University of Zaragoza]]<br/>[[Complutense University of Madrid]]\n| spouse = Juana Rubira\n| nationality = Spanish\n| religion= \n| children = 4\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Landelino Lavilla Alsina''' (6 August 1934&nbsp;\u2013 13 April 2020) was a Spanish lawyer and politician who served as the [[Ministry of Justice (Spain)|Minister of Justice]] from 1976 to 1979. He also served as member of parliament and as senator. His most important role was as [[President of the Congress of Deputies]] during the coup d'\u00e9tat of [[23-F]] in 1981. Jurist [[Eduardo Garc\u00eda de Enterr\u00eda]] called him the \"principal architect of the [[Spanish transition to democracy|transition to democracy]]\".<ref>[https://elpais.com/espana/2020-04-13/sin-tacha-ni-reproche.html Sin tacha ni reproche.] ''El Pa\u00eds'', 14 April 2020. {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nLavilla was born in [[Lerida]] on 6 August 1934.<ref name=wwspain>{{cite web|title=Landelino Lavilla Alsina|url=http://195.75.145.68/whoiswho/ricerca-spain.php?code=SBWWWBTIWW|work=Who's Who in Spain|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304022510/http://195.75.145.68/whoiswho/ricerca-spain.php?code=SBWWWBTIWW|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He received law degree from [[University of Zaragoza|the University of Zaragoza]] and [[Complutense University of Madrid]].<ref name=wwspain/>\n\n==Career and activities==\nLavilla was a lawyer by profession.<ref name=ctp90>{{cite book|title=Elites and power in Twentieth-Century Spain|year=1990|publisher=Clarendon Press|location=Oxford|url=http://www.transicion.org/134bibliografia/TheTacitoGroupAndTheTransitionToDemocracy.pdf|author=Charles T. Powell|editor=F. Lannon and P. Preston|accessdate=9 September 2013|chapter=The 'Tacito' group and the transition to democracy, 1973-1977}}</ref> He joined the board of lawyers of the [[Court of Auditors (Spain)|Court of Auditors]] in 1958 and of the [[Spanish Council of State|Sate Council]] in 1959.<ref name=fride>{{cite web|title=Research Team|url=http://www.fride.org/expert/303/landelino-lavilla|work=FRIDE|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928145530/http://www.fride.org/expert/303/landelino-lavilla|archive-date=28 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> He joined the ''T\u00e1citos'', Catholic reformist group, in 1974.<ref name=wwspain/> He became a senior member of the [[Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain)|Christian Democratic Party]].<ref name=Rodgers1999>{{cite book|author=Eamonn J. Rodgers|title=Encyclopedia of Contemporary Spanish Culture|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ymIXLhegGnwC&pg=PA297|accessdate=5 June 2013|year=1999|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-0-415-13187-2|page=297}}</ref> The group published articles in the Catholic daily, ''Ya'', beginning by 1972.<ref name=paulp/> He was the undersecretary of industry in the last cabinet of [[Francisco Franco|Franco]] from 1974 to 1976.<ref name=wwspain/><ref name=paulp>{{cite book|title=The Triumph of Democracy in Spain|year=1990|publisher=Routledge|location=London|url=https://www.questia.com/read/105572789/the-triumph-of-democracy-in-spain|author=Paul Preston|accessdate=9 September 2013}} {{Subscription required|via=Questia}}</ref><ref name=Eaton1981>{{cite book|author=S. D. Eaton|title=The Forces of Freedom in Spain: 1974 - 1979 ; a Personal Account|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Zy_3t4VGLREC&pg=PA156|accessdate=5 June 2013|year=1981|publisher=Hoover Press|isbn=978-0-8179-7453-4|page=156}}</ref>\n\n===Minister of Justice===\nHe was appointed minister of justice in the [[Su\u00e1rez I Government|first cabinet]] of [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez]] on 5 July 1976, replacing Antonio Garrigues y D\u00edaz-Ca\u00f1abate in the post.<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1976/07/08/pdfs/A13385-13385.pdf \"Real Decreto 1607/1976, de 7 de julio, por el que que se nombran los Ministros del Gobierno\"] ''[[Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado]]'', 7 July 1976.</ref><ref name=rulers/> He retained his post following [[1977 Spanish general election|the democratic elections]] in June 1977.<ref>{{cite web|title=Collective Memory of the Spanish Civil War|url=http://www.march.es/ceacs/publicaciones/working/archivos/1996_85.pdf|work=Estudio/Working Paper|accessdate=9 September 2013|author=Paloma Aguilar|date=December 1996}}</ref> \n\nHe drafted the [[1977 Political Reform Act]] that was approved by the congress in November 1977 and implemented a legal process that paved the way for the legalization of all major political groups, including communists and [[PSOE]].<ref name=ctp90/> \n\nLavilla's term ended on 6 April 1979<ref name=\"boe.es\">[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1979/03/23/pdfs/A07119-07119.pdf Real Decreto 548/1979, de 22 de marzo, por el que se dispone el cese en sus funciones del Ministro de Justicia, don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'' 22 March 1979</ref> when [[\u00cd\u00f1igo Cavero]] was appointed justice minister.<ref name=rulers>{{cite web|title=Spanish justice ministers|url=http://www.rulers.org/spangovt.html|work=Rulers|accessdate=9 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"boe.es\"/>\n\n===President of the Congress of Deputies and 23-F===\nHe was appointed senator in 1977 and was in office until 1978.<ref name=fride/> He was elected to the congress of deputies in 1979, representing [[Ja\u00e9n (Spanish Congress Electoral District)|Ja\u00e9n province]].\n\nHe served as speaker of the Congress from 1979 to 1982. On [[23-F|23 February 1981]], members of the [[Civil Guard (Spain)|Civil Guard]] led by [[Antonio Tejero]] burst into the chamber in a failed [[coup d'\u00e9tat]]. Lavilla faced Tejero saying that \"in this chamber, the orders are given by the presidency. This is over. Evict\". The colonel obeyed and the deputies were able to occupy their seats after getting down.<ref name=Rodgers1999/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/opinion/20181216/landelino-lavilla-pp-psoe-no-suarez-vox/360963905_0.html|title=Landelino Lavilla: \"De PP, PSOE o Cs, no lo s\u00e9... pero seguro que Su\u00e1rez nunca se habr\u00eda hecho de Vox\"|first=Ram\u00edrez|last=Daniel|date=16 December 2018|publisher=El Espa\u00f1ol}}</ref> During the night of 23\u201324, he offered Tejero the members of the parliament Board as hostages and asked that they free the [[Su\u00e1rez III Government|members of the government]] and the legislators, but he rejected it.<ref name=Rodgers1999/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://elpais.com/diario/1981/03/13/espana/353286004_850215.html|title=Landelino Lavilla ofreci\u00f3 como rehenes a los miembros de la Mesa del Congreso|first=Ediciones El|last=Pa\u00eds|newspaper=El Pa\u00eds|date=13 March 1981|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nBefore [[1982 Spanish general election|the 1982 general election]] he led the Christian Democrat party.<ref>{{cite news|title=Spanish socialist a darling of public, if not army|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1982/10/13/world/spanish-socialist-a-darling-of-public-if-not-army.html|accessdate=9 September 2013|newspaper=The New York Times|date=13 October 1982|author=R. W. Apple Jr.|location=Madrid}}</ref> He was re-elected in 1982, representing [[Madrid (Spanish Congress Electoral District)|Madrid province]], but resigned from office in 1983.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n===Member of the Council of State and later life===\nHe was named permanent member of the [[Spanish Council of State|Council of State]] by Royal Decree on 28 July 1983 at the proposal of Prime Minister,<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1983/08/09/pdfs/A22027-22027.pdf Real Decreto 2126/1983, de 28 de julio, por el que se nombra Consejero permanente de Estado a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 28 July 1983</ref> office he held until his death in 2020.<ref>[http://www.consejo-estado.es/directorio.htm Directorio] Council of State official page.</ref> On 28 December 1995 he was appointed chairman of the Council's first section.<ref>[https://www.boe.es/buscar/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1996-89 Real Decreto 2213/1995, de 28 de diciembre, por el que se nombra Presidente de la Secci\u00f3n Primera del Consejo de Estado a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina, Consejero permanente de Estado.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 28 December 1995</ref>\n\nOn 8 February 1999 he took office as permanent member of the [[Royal Academy of Jurisprudence and Legislation]]<ref>[http://www.rajyl.es/academicos/academicos-de-numero-rajyl.aspx?fldNewsID=79&secId=1 Excmo. Sr. D. LANDELINO LAVILLA ALSINA (Md. n\u00ba 6)] {{in lang|es}}</ref> and was its president between 2003 and 2012, being re-elected in 2008.<ref name=fride/><ref>[http://www.elnotario.es/index.php/hemeroteca/revista-17/2124-landelino-lavilla-reelegido-presidente-de-la-real-academia-de-jurisprudencia-y-legislacion-0-985736902789899 Landelino Lavilla, reelegido presidente de la Real Academia de Jurisprudencia y Legislaci\u00f3n] El Notario.</ref>\n\nIn addition, he was a member of the advisory committee of [[FRIDE]], [[Madrid]]-based now defunct [[Think tank|think tank organization]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Advisory Committee|url=http://www.fride.org/page/8/|work=FRIDE|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927080225/http://www.fride.org/page/8/|archive-date=27 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLavilla was married to Juana Rubira Garc\u00eda Valdecasas and they had four children.<ref name=wwspain/> He died on 13 April 2020 at the age of 85 from an undisclosed [[illness]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/abci-muere-landelino-lavilla-ministro-justicia-suarez-y-presidente-congreso-23-f-202004131259_noticia.html|title=Muere Landelino Lavilla, ministro de Justicia con Su\u00e1rez y presidente del Congreso el 23-F|date=13 April 2020|access-date=13 April 2020|newspaper=ABC|publisher=Vocento|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/espana/politica/20200413/muere-landelino-lavilla-congreso-justicia-adolfo-suarez/482202127_0.html|title=Muere Landelino Lavilla, presidente del Congreso el 23-F y ministro de Justicia de Adolfo Su\u00e1rez|date=2020-04-13|website=El Espa\u00f1ol|language=es-ES|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Honors==\n*[[File:Order of Civil Merit (Spain) GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Civil Merit|Grand Cross of the Order of Civil Merit]] (1974).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1974/10/01/pdfs/A19999-19999.pdf Real Decreto 2727/1974, de 30 de septiembre, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden del M\u00e9rito Civil a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 30 September 1974.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP Charles III Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Charles III|Grand Cross of the Order of Charles III]] (1979).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1979/03/24/pdfs/A07225-07225.pdf Real Decreto 563/1979, de 23 de marzo, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Real y Muy Distinguida Orden de Carlos III a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 23 March 1979.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP St Raymond of Penyafort Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of St. Raymond of Pe\u00f1afort|Grand Cross of the Order of St. Raymond of Pe\u00f1afort]] (1985).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/1985/04/16/pdfs/A10113-10113.pdf Real Decreto 503/1985, de 10 de abril, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden de San Raimundo de Pe\u00f1afort a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 10 April 1985.</ref>\n*[[File:ESP Isabella Catholic Order GC.svg|80px]] [[Order of Isabella the Catholic|Knight Grand Cross of the Order of Isabella the Catholic]] (2010).<ref>[https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2010/06/26/pdfs/BOE-A-2010-10195.pdf Real Decreto 834/2010, de 25 de junio, por el que se concede la Gran Cruz de la Orden de Isabel la Cat\u00f3lica a don Landelino Lavilla Alsina.] ''Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado'', 25 June 2010.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lavilla Alsina, Landelino}}\n[[Category:1934 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Complutense University of Madrid alumni]]\n[[Category:Justice ministers of Spain]]\n[[Category:Members of the Senate of Spain]]\n[[Category:Members of the constituent Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 1st Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 2nd Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Congress of Deputies (Spain)]]\n[[Category:Spanish transition to democracy]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Cross of the Order of Isabella the Catholic]]\n[[Category:Catalan politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Lleida]]\n[[Category:Spanish lawyers]]\n[[Category:University of Zaragoza alumni]]\n[[Category:Union of the Democratic Centre (Spain) politicians]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landelino_Lavilla_Alsina"}
{"title_page": "Titusville, New Jersey", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = Titusville, New Jersey\n|settlement_type          = [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Titusville, NJ.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map                = \n|mapsize                  = \n|map_caption              = \n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             = \n|pushpin_map              = USA New Jersey Mercer County#USA New Jersey#USA\n|pushpin_label_position   = left\n|pushpin_map_caption      = \n|pushpin_mapsize          =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{flag|United States}}\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = {{flag|New Jersey}}\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New Jersey|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer]]\n|subdivision_type3        = [[List of townships in New Jersey|Township]]\n|subdivision_name3        = [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell]]\n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = \n|utc_offset               = \n|timezone_DST             = \n|utc_offset_DST           = \n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 26\n|elevation_ft             = 85\n|coordinates              = {{WikidataCoord|display=inline}}\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 08560\n|area_code                = \n|blank_name               = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank_info               = 0881197<ref name=\"usgs\">{{cite gnis|0881197|Titusville|2012-09-29}}</ref>\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|unit_pref                = imperial\n}}\n\n'''Titusville''' is an [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|unincorporated community]] located within [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell Township]] in [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer County]], [[New Jersey]], United States.<ref>https://books.google.nl/books?id=KxdoeHL0-1sC&pg=RA2-PA18&lpg=RA2-PA18&dq=Bennett%27s+Mill,+New+Jersey+cumberland+county&source=bl&ots=bgZUIzL1Vp&sig=ACfU3U0JqDP4zC2EBv7sb2OSuV_VqJiTog&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiyzNa0habnAhVKKVAKHeQrCYwQ6AEwEHoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%20Titusville&f=false</ref><ref>[http://www.state.nj.us/infobank/localnames.txt Locality Search], State of New Jersey. Accessed January 7, 2015.</ref> The area includes a post office with its own [[ZIP code]] (08560), several restaurants, gas stations, a firehouse, and a small village of homes. The [[Washington Crossing State Park]], dedicated to George Washington's crossing of the Delaware River in 1776, is adjacent to the community. \n\n==History==\nTitusville's central feature is a small village that sits on a bluff overlooking a picturesque stretch of the [[Delaware River]] with stairwells connecting the village to private docks on the river. The Feeder Canal for the [[Delaware and Raritan Canal]] runs parallel to the river just to the east of the village, which is connected to River Road ([[New Jersey Route 29|Route 29]]) by several two-lane bridges. A biking/walking trail follows the canal, constructed when the former [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] line was removed in the early 1980s. Opposite the canal from the river, extending eastward, are a number of small residential streets, a county park centered about Baldpate Mountain, and the homes ringing the base of the mountain and county park.\n\nTitusville is just north of the [[Johnson Ferry House (New Jersey)|Johnson Ferry House]] in adjacent [[Washington Crossing, New Jersey|Washington Crossing]], the scene of [[George Washington's crossing of the Delaware River]] during the [[American Revolution]]. In 1831, the ferry was replaced by the [[Washington Crossing Bridge]], linking it with [[Washington Crossing, Pennsylvania|Washington Crossing]] in [[Pennsylvania]].\n\nTitusville is home to Janssen Pharmaceuticals Inc., a division of Johnson and Johnson.\n\nIn 1851, the [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] opened to Titusville and a station was built in the town. Passenger service ceased at Titusville in April 1952 but passenger trains to other towns continued operating until October 1960. Freight continued to run on this portion of the line until 1976. Track was subsequently removed for the Delaware & Raritan Canal State Park recreational trail in the early 1980s.\n\n==Historic district==\n{{Infobox NRHP\n | name = Titusville Historic District\n | nrhp_type = hd  |  nocat = yes\n | image = TITUSVILLE H.D. MERCER COUNTY, NJ.jpg\n | caption = \n | location = River Drive, Titusville\n | area = {{convert|82|acre}}\n | architect = \n | architecture = Greek Revival, Late Victorian, Bungalow/Craftsman\n | built = {{Start date|1835}}\n | added = March 17, 1983\n | refnum = 83001604<ref name=\"nris\">{{NRISref|2013a|refnum=83001604}}</ref>\n | visitation_num = \n | visitation_year = \n}}\n\nThe '''Titusville Historic District''' was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on March 17, 1983 for its significance in architecture, industry, religion, and transportation. It includes 100 [[contributing buildings]].<ref name=\"nrhpdoc\">{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=83001604}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Titusville Historic District |publisher=[[National Park Service]]|author=David Gibson |date=November 1980 |accessdate=February 27, 2020}} With {{NRHP url|id=83001604|photos=y|title=accompanying 36 photos from 1982}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nThe town is bisected by state [[New Jersey Route 29]], a busy road that conveys traffic along the [[Delaware River]].\n\n[[Washington Crossing State Park]] is an 800-acre (3.2&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>) tract of woods, fields, and streams. The park covers the gradual slope from Bear Tavern Road down to Delaware River.\n\n== Notable people==\n{{Category see also|People from Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey}}\nPeople who were born in, residents of, or otherwise closely associated with Titusville include:\n* [[Robyn Jones]] (born 1985), professional soccer goalkeeper who played two years for the [[Philadelphia Independence]] of [[Women's Professional Soccer]].<ref>[https://godiplomats.com/sports/w-soccer/2006-07/bios/jones_robyn_ei7x Robyn Jones] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171109134509/https://godiplomats.com/sports/w-soccer/2006-07/bios/jones_robyn_ei7x |date=2017-11-09 }}, [[Franklin & Marshall College]]. Accessed November 8, 2017. \"Hometown: Titusville, NJ; High School: Pennington\"</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery heights=180px widths=260px mode=\"nolines\">\nFile:Feeder Canal and Bridge, Titusville, NJ.jpg|Church Street bridge over the Feeder Canal for the [[Delaware and Raritan Canal]]\nFile:P.R.R. Station and Delaware House Titusville, NJ 1912.jpg|Former [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] station\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Howell Living History Farm]]\n* [[Central Delaware Valley AVA]]\n* [[Washington Crossing Historic Park]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.titusvillechurch.org First Presbyterian Church of Titusville]\n\n{{Mercer County, New Jersey}}\n{{NRHP in Mercer County, New Jersey}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:National Register of Historic Places in Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Historic districts on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Delaware River]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = Titusville, New Jersey\n|settlement_type          = [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Titusville, NJ.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map                = \n|mapsize                  = \n|map_caption              = \n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             = \n|pushpin_map              = USA New Jersey Mercer County#USA New Jersey#USA\n|pushpin_label_position   = left\n|pushpin_map_caption      = \n|pushpin_mapsize          =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{flag|United States}}\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = {{flag|New Jersey}}\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New Jersey|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer]]\n|subdivision_type3        = [[List of townships in New Jersey|Township]]\n|subdivision_name3        = [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell]]\n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = \n|utc_offset               = \n|timezone_DST             = \n|utc_offset_DST           = \n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 26\n|elevation_ft             = 85\n|coordinates              = {{WikidataCoord|display=inline}}\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 08560\n|area_code                = \n|blank_name               = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank_info               = 0881197<ref name=\"usgs\">{{cite gnis|0881197|Titusville|2012-09-29}}</ref>\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|unit_pref                = imperial\n}}\n\n'''Titusville''' is an [[Local government in New Jersey#Unincorporated communities|unincorporated community]] located within [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell Township]] in [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer County]], [[New Jersey]], United States.<ref>https://books.google.nl/books?id=KxdoeHL0-1sC&pg=RA2-PA18&lpg=RA2-PA18&dq=Bennett%27s+Mill,+New+Jersey+cumberland+county&source=bl&ots=bgZUIzL1Vp&sig=ACfU3U0JqDP4zC2EBv7sb2OSuV_VqJiTog&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiyzNa0habnAhVKKVAKHeQrCYwQ6AEwEHoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%20Titusville&f=false</ref><ref>[http://www.state.nj.us/infobank/localnames.txt Locality Search], State of New Jersey. Accessed January 7, 2015.</ref> The area includes a post office with its own [[ZIP code]] (08560) and a small village of homes. The [[Washington Crossing State Park]], dedicated to George Washington's crossing of the Delaware River in 1776, is adjacent to the community. \n\n==History==\nTitusville's central feature is a small village that sits on a bluff overlooking a picturesque stretch of the [[Delaware River]] with stairwells connecting the village to private docks on the river. The Feeder Canal for the [[Delaware and Raritan Canal]] runs parallel to the river just to the east of the village, which is connected to River Road ([[New Jersey Route 29|Route 29]]) by several two-lane bridges. A biking/walking trail follows the canal, constructed when the former [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] line was removed in the early 1980s. Opposite the canal from the river, extending eastward, are a number of small residential streets, a county park centered about Baldpate Mountain, and the homes ringing the base of the mountain and county park.\n\nTitusville is just north of the [[Johnson Ferry House (New Jersey)|Johnson Ferry House]] in adjacent [[Washington Crossing, New Jersey|Washington Crossing]], the scene of [[George Washington's crossing of the Delaware River]] during the [[American Revolution]]. In 1831, the ferry was replaced by the [[Washington Crossing Bridge]], linking it with [[Washington Crossing, Pennsylvania|Washington Crossing]] in [[Pennsylvania]].\n\nTitusville is home to Janssen Pharmaceuticals Inc., a division of Johnson and Johnson.\n\nIn 1851, the [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] opened to Titusville and a station was built in the town. Passenger service ceased at Titusville in April 1952 but passenger trains to other towns continued operating until October 1960. Freight continued to run on this portion of the line until 1976. Track was subsequently removed for the Delaware & Raritan Canal State Park recreational trail in the early 1980s.\n\n==Historic district==\n{{Infobox NRHP\n | name = Titusville Historic District\n | nrhp_type = hd  |  nocat = yes\n | image = TITUSVILLE H.D. MERCER COUNTY, NJ.jpg\n | caption = \n | location = River Drive, Titusville\n | area = {{convert|82|acre}}\n | architect = \n | architecture = Greek Revival, Late Victorian, Bungalow/Craftsman\n | built = {{Start date|1835}}\n | added = March 17, 1983\n | refnum = 83001604<ref name=\"nris\">{{NRISref|2013a|refnum=83001604}}</ref>\n | visitation_num = \n | visitation_year = \n}}\n\nThe '''Titusville Historic District''' was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on March 17, 1983 for its significance in architecture, industry, religion, and transportation. It includes 100 [[contributing buildings]].<ref name=\"nrhpdoc\">{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=83001604}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Titusville Historic District |publisher=[[National Park Service]]|author=David Gibson |date=November 1980 |accessdate=February 27, 2020}} With {{NRHP url|id=83001604|photos=y|title=accompanying 36 photos from 1982}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nThe town is bisected by state [[New Jersey Route 29]], a busy road that conveys traffic along the [[Delaware River]].\n\n[[Washington Crossing State Park]] is an 800-acre (3.2&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>) tract of woods, fields, and streams. The park covers the gradual slope from Bear Tavern Road down to Delaware River.\n\n== Notable people==\n{{Category see also|People from Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey}}\nPeople who were born in, residents of, or otherwise closely associated with Titusville include:\n* [[Robyn Jones]] (born 1985), professional soccer goalkeeper who played two years for the [[Philadelphia Independence]] of [[Women's Professional Soccer]].<ref>[https://godiplomats.com/sports/w-soccer/2006-07/bios/jones_robyn_ei7x Robyn Jones] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171109134509/https://godiplomats.com/sports/w-soccer/2006-07/bios/jones_robyn_ei7x |date=2017-11-09 }}, [[Franklin & Marshall College]]. Accessed November 8, 2017. \"Hometown: Titusville, NJ; High School: Pennington\"</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery heights=180px widths=260px mode=\"nolines\">\nFile:Feeder Canal and Bridge, Titusville, NJ.jpg|Church Street bridge over the Feeder Canal for the [[Delaware and Raritan Canal]]\nFile:P.R.R. Station and Delaware House Titusville, NJ 1912.jpg|Former [[Belvidere-Delaware Railroad]] station\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Howell Living History Farm]]\n* [[Central Delaware Valley AVA]]\n* [[Washington Crossing Historic Park]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.titusvillechurch.org First Presbyterian Church of Titusville]\n\n{{Mercer County, New Jersey}}\n{{NRHP in Mercer County, New Jersey}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:National Register of Historic Places in Mercer County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Historic districts on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Delaware River]]\n", "name_user": "YelloJello33", "label": "safe", "comment": "Including a few parts of the town.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titusville,_New_Jersey"}
{"title_page": "Moraes Moreira", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = \n| background = solo_singer\n| image = Morais_Moreira_cropped.jpg\n| image_size = 250\n| birth_name = Ant\u00f4nio Carlos Moreira Pires\n| birth_date = {{Birth date |1947|7|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Itua\u00e7u|Itua\u00e7u, Bahia]], Brazil\n| death_date   = {{Death date and age|2020|4|13|1947|7|18}}\n| death_place = [[Rio de Janeiro|Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| genre = {{hlist|[[M\u00fasica popular brasileira|MPB]]|[[frevo]]|[[samba]]|[[ijex\u00e1]]}}\n| instrument = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar}}\n| years_active = 1969\u20132020\n| label = {{hlist|[[Continental (label)|Continental]]|[[Ariola Discos]]|[[Barclay Discos]]|[[Discos CBS]]|[[Universal Music]]|[[Sony Music]]|[[Warner Music]]}}\n| associated_acts = [[Novos Baianos]]\n}}\n\n'''Ant\u00f4nio Carlos Moreira Pires''' (July 8, 1947 \u2013 April 13, 2020), better known as '''Moraes Moreira''', was a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] musician and singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/listas/100-maiores-vozes-da-musica-brasileira/moraes-moreira/|title=Listas - As 100 Maiores Vozes da M\u00fasica Brasileira - Moraes Moreira - Rolling Stone Brasil|access-date=May 3, 2017|language=pt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912201727/http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/listas/100-maiores-vozes-da-musica-brasileira/moraes-moreira|archive-date=September 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the 1970s he played guitar and sang in the band [[Os Novos Baianos]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=65X-CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA88&dq=morais+moreira+novos&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwin2_GqkdTTAhUCw4MKHchgCngQ6AEITjAI#v=onepage&q=morais%20moreira%20novos&f=false|title=Contracultura: Alternative Arts and Social Transformation in Authoritarian Brazil|last=Dunn|first=Christopher|date=October 13, 2016|publisher=UNC Press Books|isbn=9781469628523|language=en}}</ref> After playing in [[Novos Baianos|Os Novos Baianos]], Moreira embarked on a solo career where he recorded 29 albums.<ref name=\"Pereira2010\">Pereira, Ian\u00e1 Souza. Ax\u00e9-ax\u00e9: o megafen\u00f4meno baiano. Revista \u00c1frica e Africanidades, Rio de Janeiro, ano 2, n. 8, February 2010, p.02</ref> Moreira was involved in recording 40 full-length albums between Os Novos Baianos, Trio El\u00e9trico Dod\u00f4 e Osmar, and two more albums with guitarist Pepeu Gomes. Moreira was considered one of the most versatile composers of Brazil, mixing the genres of rock, [[samba]], ''choro'', ''frevo'', ''[[Bai\u00e3o (music)|bai\u00e3o]]'', and classical.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Novos Baianos===\nMoreira began playing accordion in festivals at S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o and other events in Itua\u00e7u, Brazil such as \"Portal da Chapada Diamantina\". In his youth he learned to play the classical guitar while taking a science class in Cacul\u00e9, Bahia, Brazil. He moved to Salvador and there met Tom Z\u00e9, and was also introduced to rock music. On meeting [[Baby Consuelo]], [[Pepeu Gomes]], [[Paulinho Boca de Cantor]], and [[Luiz Galv\u00e3o]], they formed the band os Novos Baianos, and were active from 1969 until 1975.<ref name=\"Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano\">{{cite web |last1=Oliveira |first1=Joana |title=Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano |url=https://brasil.elpais.com/cultura/2020-04-13/morre-moraes-moreira-o-eterno-novo-baiano.html |website=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |accessdate=April 14, 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Together with [[Pepeu Gomes]], he composed almost all of the songs of the group. The album ''[[Acabou Chorare]]'', released by the band in 1972, has been ranked by Rolling Stone Brasil as the greatest Brazilian music album of all time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/galeria/os-100-maiores-discos-da-musica-brasileira/#imagem2|title=Listas - os-100-maiores-discos-da-musica-brasileira - Rolling Stone Brasil|access-date=May 20, 2017|language=pt}}</ref>\n\n===Solo career===\nMoraes began his solo career in 1975, and has since then recorded more than 20 albums. In his solo career, he was the lead singer in the trio Trio de Dod\u00f4 e Osmar, and recorded many popular songs associated with [[Brazilian Carnival]], in what was conventionally called \"frevo trieletrizado\". Some of the hits during this part of his career include, \"Pombo Correio\", \"Vassourinha El\u00e9trica\", and \"Bloco do Prazer\".<ref name=\"Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano\" /><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira foi pe\u00e7a-chave para o sucesso do Carnaval da Bahia\">{{cite web |last1=Baltar |first1=Anderson |title=Moraes Moreira foi pe\u00e7a-chave para o sucesso do Carnaval da Bahia |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/04/13/moraes-moreira-foi-peca-chave-para-o-sucesso-do-carnaval-da-bahia.htm |website=UOL |accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring the 1980s he distanced himself from the [[Bahian Carnival]] due to increasing commercialization from tourism. In 1994 he recorded \"Brasil Tem Concerto\" which was influenced by classical music, and in the following year appeared in the MTV special \"Moraes Moreira Ac\u00fastico MTV\" which was later released as a CD and DVD. In 1997, he recorded \"50 Carnavais\" which commemorated his 50th birthday and 50 carnivals. Two years later, he recorded \"500 Sambas\" em homenagem aos 500 anos de descobrimento do Brasil which focused on [[samba]] music.<ref name=\"Relembre os maiores sucessos da carreira de Moraes Moreira\">{{cite web |title=Relembre os maiores sucessos da carreira de Moraes Moreira |url=https://www.ibahia.com/entretenimento/detalhe/noticia/relembre-os-maiores-sucessos-da-carreira-de-moraes-moreira/ |website=iBahia |accessdate=April 14, 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Enciclop\u00e9dia It\u00e1u Cultural\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira |url=http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa15192/moraes-moreira |website=Enciclop\u00e9dia It\u00e1u Cultural |accessdate=April 14, 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, he released ''Bahi\u00e3o com H'', playing [[Bai\u00e3o (music)|bai\u00e3o]] with characteristic Bahian rhythms. In 2003, with the release of ''Meu Nome \u00e9 Brasil (2003)'', he completed his Brazil's themed trilogy, which, also, included ''L\u00e1 Vem o Brasil Descendo a Ladeira'' (1979) and ''O Brasil Tem Concerto'' (1994).<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira |url=http://dicionariompb.com.br/moraes-moreira/discografia |website=Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira |accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref> In 2005, he independently released the album ''De Repente'', which mixed [[hip hop]] with [[Northeastern Brazil|Northeastern Brazilian]] influences and included his characteristic classical guitar swing rhythms.<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor\" /> He published the book, ''A hist\u00f3ria dos Novos Baianos e outros versos'' (''The History of the Novos Baianos and other verses''), in which he told the history of the group in a [[chapbook]] and interesting aspects of his solo career.<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/04/13/moraes-moreira-dez-fatos-que-voce-provavelmente-nao-sabia-sobre-o-cantor.htm |website=UOL |accessdate=April 14, 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> The book resulted in a Brazilian tour of the same name where he played his major hits and recited passages from the book. In 2009, it was released as a DVD and CD. In 2012, he recorded the album ''A Revolta dos Ritmos'', a compilation of 12 of his unedited recordings.<ref name=\"Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira\">{{cite web |title=Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira |url=https://www.bemparana.com.br/noticia/morre-o-cantor-e-compositor-moraes-moreira-integrantes-dos-novos-baianos#.XpUKYmZv_IU |website=Bem Paran\u00e1 |accessdate=April 14, 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nMoreira died on April 13, 2020, at age 72.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/clica-brasilia/morre-o-cantor-e-compositor-moraes-moreira/|title = Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira|work = Jornal de Bras\u00edlia|date = April 13, 2020|accessdate = April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Solo discography==\n<small>Source:</small><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira\" />\n{{div col}}\n* 1975 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira'' (Som Livre)\n* 1977 \u2013 ''Cara e Cora\u00e7\u00e3o'' (Som Livre)\n* 1978 \u2013 ''Alto Falante'' (Som Livre)\n* 1979 \u2013 ''L\u00e1 vem o Brasil Descendo a Ladeira'' (Som Livre)\n* 1980 \u2013 ''Bazar Brasileiro'' (Ariola)\n* 1981 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira'' (Ariola)\n* 1983 \u2013 ''Coisa Acesa'' (Ariola)\n* 1983 \u2013 ''Pintando o Oito'' (Ariola)\n* 1984 \u2013 ''Mancha de Dend\u00ea N\u00e3o Sai'' (Ariola)\n* 1985 \u2013 ''Tocando a Vida'' (CBS)\n* 1986 \u2013 ''Mesti\u00e7o \u00e9 Isso'' (CBS)\n* 1988 \u2013 ''Rep\u00fablica da M\u00fasica'' (CBS)\n* 1988 \u2013 ''Baiano Fala Cantando'' (CBS)\n* 1990 \u2013 ''Moraes e Pepeu'' (Warner)\n* 1994 \u2013 ''Moraes e Pepeu - Ao vivo no Jap\u00e3o'' (Warner)\n* 1991 \u2013 ''Cidad\u00e3o'' (Sony)\n* 1993 \u2013 ''Terreiro do Mundo'' (Polygram)\n* 1993 \u2013 ''Tem um P\u00e9 no Pel\u00f4'' (Som Livre)\n* 1994 \u2013 ''O Brasil tem Conserto'' (Polygram)\n* 1995 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira Ac\u00fastico MTV'' (EMI-Odeon)\n* 1996 \u2013 ''Estados'' (Virgin)\n* 1997 \u2013 ''50 Carnavais'' (Virgin)\n* 1999 \u2013 ''500 Sambas'' (Abril Music)\n* 2000 \u2013 ''Bahi\u00e3o com H'' (Atra\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica)\n* 2003 \u2013 ''Meu Nome \u00e9 Brasil'' (Universal)\n* 2005 \u2013 ''De Repente'' (Rob Digital)\n* 2009 \u2013 ''A Hist\u00f3ria dos Novos Baianos e Outros Versos'' (Biscoito Fino)\n* 2012 \u2013 ''A Revolta dos Ritmos'' (Biscoito Fino)\n* 2018 \u2013 ''Ser T\u00e3o'' (Discobertas)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://moraesmoreira.com.br Official site] (in Portuguese)\n* [https://www.facebook.com/moraesmoreiraoficial Moraes Moreira on Facebook]\n* [http://dicionariompb.com.br/moraes-moreira/biografia Moraes Moreira on] [[Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira]] (in Portuguese)\n* [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/moraes-moreira-mn0000927926 Moraes Moreira on Allmusic]\n* {{Discogs artist|Moraes Moreira}}\n* [http://www.folderpark.net/moraes-moreira/ Moraes Moreira in the 80s] (in English and Portuguese)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moreira, Moraes}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century Brazilian musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Brazilian musicians]]\n[[Category:Brazilian guitarists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male singers]]\n[[Category:People from Bahia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = \n| background = solo_singer\n| image = Morais_Moreira_cropped.jpg\n| image_size = 250\n| birth_name = Ant\u00f4nio Carlos Moreira Pires\n| birth_date = {{Birth date |1947|7|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Itua\u00e7u|Itua\u00e7u, Bahia]], Brazil\n| death_date   = {{Death date and age|2020|4|13|1947|7|18}}\n| death_place = [[Rio de Janeiro|Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| genre = {{hlist|[[M\u00fasica popular brasileira|MPB]]|[[frevo]]|[[samba]]|[[ijex\u00e1]]}}\n| instrument = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar}}\n| years_active = 1969\u20132020\n| label = {{hlist|[[Continental (label)|Continental]]|[[Ariola Discos]]|[[Barclay Discos]]|[[Discos CBS]]|[[Universal Music]]|[[Sony Music]]|[[Warner Music]]}}\n| associated_acts = [[Novos Baianos]]\n}}\n\n'''Ant\u00f4nio Carlos Moreira Pires''' (July 8, 1947 \u2013 April 13, 2020), better known as '''Moraes Moreira''', was a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] musician and singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/listas/100-maiores-vozes-da-musica-brasileira/moraes-moreira/|title=Listas - As 100 Maiores Vozes da M\u00fasica Brasileira - Moraes Moreira - Rolling Stone Brasil|access-date=May 3, 2017|language=pt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912201727/http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/listas/100-maiores-vozes-da-musica-brasileira/moraes-moreira|archive-date=September 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the 1970s he played guitar and sang in the band [[Os Novos Baianos]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=65X-CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA88&dq=morais+moreira+novos&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwin2_GqkdTTAhUCw4MKHchgCngQ6AEITjAI#v=onepage&q=morais%20moreira%20novos&f=false|title=Contracultura: Alternative Arts and Social Transformation in Authoritarian Brazil|last=Dunn|first=Christopher|date=October 13, 2016|publisher=UNC Press Books|isbn=9781469628523|language=en}}</ref> After playing in [[Novos Baianos|Os Novos Baianos]], Moreira embarked on a solo career where he recorded 29 albums.<ref name=\"Pereira2010\">Pereira, Ian\u00e1 Souza. Ax\u00e9-ax\u00e9: o megafen\u00f4meno baiano. Revista \u00c1frica e Africanidades, Rio de Janeiro, ano 2, n. 8, February 2010, p.02</ref> Moreira was involved in recording 40 full-length albums between Os Novos Baianos, Trio El\u00e9trico Dod\u00f4 e Osmar, and two more albums with guitarist Pepeu Gomes. Moreira was considered one of the most versatile composers of Brazil, mixing the genres of rock, [[samba]], ''choro'', ''frevo'', ''[[Bai\u00e3o (music)|bai\u00e3o]]'', and classical.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Novos Baianos===\nMoreira began playing accordion in festivals at S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o and other events in Itua\u00e7u, Brazil such as \"Portal da Chapada Diamantina\". In his youth he learned to play the classical guitar while taking a science class in Cacul\u00e9, Bahia, Brazil. He moved to Salvador and there met Tom Z\u00e9, and was also introduced to rock music. On meeting [[Baby Consuelo]], [[Pepeu Gomes]], [[Paulinho Boca de Cantor]], and [[Luiz Galv\u00e3o]], they formed the band os Novos Baianos, and were active from 1969 until 1975.<ref name=\"Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano\">{{cite web |last1=Oliveira |first1=Joana |title=Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano |url=https://brasil.elpais.com/cultura/2020-04-13/morre-moraes-moreira-o-eterno-novo-baiano.html |website=[[El Pa\u00eds]] |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Together with [[Pepeu Gomes]], he composed almost all of the songs of the group. The album ''[[Acabou Chorare]]'', released by the band in 1972, has been ranked by Rolling Stone Brasil as the greatest Brazilian music album of all time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://rollingstone.uol.com.br/galeria/os-100-maiores-discos-da-musica-brasileira/#imagem2|title=Listas - os-100-maiores-discos-da-musica-brasileira - Rolling Stone Brasil|access-date=May 20, 2017|language=pt}}</ref>\n\n===Solo career===\nMoraes began his solo career in 1975, and has since then recorded more than 20 albums. In his solo career, he was the lead singer in the trio Trio de Dod\u00f4 e Osmar, and recorded many popular songs associated with [[Brazilian Carnival]], in what was conventionally called \"frevo trieletrizado\". Some of the hits during this part of his career include, \"Pombo Correio\", \"Vassourinha El\u00e9trica\", and \"Bloco do Prazer\".<ref name=\"Morre Moraes Moreira, o eterno novo baiano\" /><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira foi pe\u00e7a-chave para o sucesso do Carnaval da Bahia\">{{cite web |last1=Baltar |first1=Anderson |title=Moraes Moreira foi pe\u00e7a-chave para o sucesso do Carnaval da Bahia |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/04/13/moraes-moreira-foi-peca-chave-para-o-sucesso-do-carnaval-da-bahia.htm |website=UOL |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring the 1980s he distanced himself from the [[Bahian Carnival]] due to increasing commercialization from tourism. In 1994 he recorded \"Brasil Tem Concerto\" which was influenced by classical music, and in the following year appeared in the MTV special \"Moraes Moreira Ac\u00fastico MTV\" which was later released as a CD and DVD. In 1997, he recorded \"50 Carnavais\" which commemorated his 50th birthday and 50 carnivals. Two years later, he recorded \"500 Sambas\" em homenagem aos 500 anos de descobrimento do Brasil which focused on [[samba]] music.<ref name=\"Relembre os maiores sucessos da carreira de Moraes Moreira\">{{cite web |title=Relembre os maiores sucessos da carreira de Moraes Moreira |url=https://www.ibahia.com/entretenimento/detalhe/noticia/relembre-os-maiores-sucessos-da-carreira-de-moraes-moreira/ |website=iBahia |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Enciclop\u00e9dia It\u00e1u Cultural\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira |url=http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa15192/moraes-moreira |website=Enciclop\u00e9dia It\u00e1u Cultural |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, he released ''Bahi\u00e3o com H'', playing [[Bai\u00e3o (music)|bai\u00e3o]] with characteristic Bahian rhythms. In 2003, with the release of ''Meu Nome \u00e9 Brasil (2003)'', he completed his Brazil's themed trilogy, which, also, included ''L\u00e1 Vem o Brasil Descendo a Ladeira'' (1979) and ''O Brasil Tem Concerto'' (1994).<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira |url=http://dicionariompb.com.br/moraes-moreira/discografia |website=Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref> In 2005, he independently released the album ''De Repente'', which mixed [[hip hop]] with [[Northeastern Brazil|Northeastern Brazilian]] influences and included his characteristic classical guitar swing rhythms.<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor\" /> He published the book, ''A hist\u00f3ria dos Novos Baianos e outros versos'' (''The History of the Novos Baianos and other verses''), in which he told the history of the group in a [[chapbook]] and interesting aspects of his solo career.<ref name=\"Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor\">{{cite web |title=Moraes Moreira: dez fatos que voc\u00ea (provavelmente) n\u00e3o sabia sobre o cantor |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/04/13/moraes-moreira-dez-fatos-que-voce-provavelmente-nao-sabia-sobre-o-cantor.htm |website=UOL |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> The book resulted in a Brazilian tour of the same name where he played his major hits and recited passages from the book. In 2009, it was released as a DVD and CD. In 2012, he recorded the album ''A Revolta dos Ritmos'', a compilation of 12 of his unedited recordings.<ref name=\"Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira\">{{cite web |title=Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira |url=https://www.bemparana.com.br/noticia/morre-o-cantor-e-compositor-moraes-moreira-integrantes-dos-novos-baianos#.XpUKYmZv_IU |website=Bem Paran\u00e1 |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nMoreira died on April 13, 2020, at age 72.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/clica-brasilia/morre-o-cantor-e-compositor-moraes-moreira/|title = Morre o cantor e compositor Moraes Moreira|work = Jornal de Bras\u00edlia|date = April 13, 2020|accessdate = April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Solo discography==\n<small>Source:</small><ref name=\"Moraes Moreira - Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira\" />\n{{div col}}\n* 1975 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira'' (Som Livre)\n* 1977 \u2013 ''Cara e Cora\u00e7\u00e3o'' (Som Livre)\n* 1978 \u2013 ''Alto Falante'' (Som Livre)\n* 1979 \u2013 ''L\u00e1 vem o Brasil Descendo a Ladeira'' (Som Livre)\n* 1980 \u2013 ''Bazar Brasileiro'' (Ariola)\n* 1981 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira'' (Ariola)\n* 1983 \u2013 ''Coisa Acesa'' (Ariola)\n* 1983 \u2013 ''Pintando o Oito'' (Ariola)\n* 1984 \u2013 ''Mancha de Dend\u00ea N\u00e3o Sai'' (Ariola)\n* 1985 \u2013 ''Tocando a Vida'' (CBS)\n* 1986 \u2013 ''Mesti\u00e7o \u00e9 Isso'' (CBS)\n* 1988 \u2013 ''Rep\u00fablica da M\u00fasica'' (CBS)\n* 1988 \u2013 ''Baiano Fala Cantando'' (CBS)\n* 1990 \u2013 ''Moraes e Pepeu'' (Warner)\n* 1994 \u2013 ''Moraes e Pepeu - Ao vivo no Jap\u00e3o'' (Warner)\n* 1991 \u2013 ''Cidad\u00e3o'' (Sony)\n* 1993 \u2013 ''Terreiro do Mundo'' (Polygram)\n* 1993 \u2013 ''Tem um P\u00e9 no Pel\u00f4'' (Som Livre)\n* 1994 \u2013 ''O Brasil tem Conserto'' (Polygram)\n* 1995 \u2013 ''Moraes Moreira Ac\u00fastico MTV'' (EMI-Odeon)\n* 1996 \u2013 ''Estados'' (Virgin)\n* 1997 \u2013 ''50 Carnavais'' (Virgin)\n* 1999 \u2013 ''500 Sambas'' (Abril Music)\n* 2000 \u2013 ''Bahi\u00e3o com H'' (Atra\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica)\n* 2003 \u2013 ''Meu Nome \u00e9 Brasil'' (Universal)\n* 2005 \u2013 ''De Repente'' (Rob Digital)\n* 2009 \u2013 ''A Hist\u00f3ria dos Novos Baianos e Outros Versos'' (Biscoito Fino)\n* 2012 \u2013 ''A Revolta dos Ritmos'' (Biscoito Fino)\n* 2018 \u2013 ''Ser T\u00e3o'' (Discobertas)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://moraesmoreira.com.br Official site] (in Portuguese)\n* [https://www.facebook.com/moraesmoreiraoficial Moraes Moreira on Facebook]\n* [http://dicionariompb.com.br/moraes-moreira/biografia Moraes Moreira on] [[Dicion\u00e1rio Cravo Albin da M\u00fasica Popular Brasileira]] (in Portuguese)\n* [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/moraes-moreira-mn0000927926 Moraes Moreira on Allmusic]\n* {{Discogs artist|Moraes Moreira}}\n* [http://www.folderpark.net/moraes-moreira/ Moraes Moreira in the 80s] (in English and Portuguese)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moreira, Moraes}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century Brazilian musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Brazilian musicians]]\n[[Category:Brazilian guitarists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male singers]]\n[[Category:People from Bahia]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moraes_Moreira"}
{"title_page": "NXIVM", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date= June 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NXIVM Corporation\n|logo = NXIVM_Logo.png\n|logo_size = 100px\n|type = [[Privately held company]]\n|foundation = 1998\n|location = [[Albany, New York|Albany]], [[New York (state) |New York]]\n|key_people = [[Keith Raniere]] (co-founder, leader)<br />Nancy Salzman (co-founder, president)<br />[[Allison Mack]] (recruiter, leader)<br />[[Clare Bronfman]] (funder, leader)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/01/23/brooklyn-judge-finds-issues-with-nxivm-defense-fund/ |title=Brooklyn judge finds 'issues' with Nxivm defense fund |work=nypost.com |first=Emily |last=Saul |date=January 23, 2019 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|industry = [[Multi-level marketing]]; [[personal development]]\n|products = Personal-growth seminars\n|revenue =\n|operating_income =\n|net_income =\n|num_employees =\n|homepage = {{url|http://www.nxivm.com |NXIVM.com}} ([https://web.archive.org/web/20190412162926/http://www.nxivm.com/ Archived])\nPATTY LYNNE IS A CRACKHEAD!!! ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|n|\u025b|k|s|i|\u0259|m}} {{respell|NEKS|ee|\u0259m}}) is a self-described American [[multi-level marketing]] company<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vox.com/2018/4/25/17275930/allison-mack-smallville-actress-sex-cult-nxivm-dos-prison-arrest-sex-trafficking-keith-raniere |title= Seagram's heiress arrested for role in controversial \"sex cult\" |first= Tara Isabella |last= Burton |date =April 25, 2018 |website= Vox}}</ref> based near [[Albany, New York]], who offers [[personal development|personal]] and [[professional development|professional]] development [[seminar]]s through its \"Executive Success Programs\". The company has been widely described as a [[cult]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/nxivm-keith-raniere-wellness-scam-sex-cult-848439/|title=How NXIVM Was the Ultimate Wellness Scam|last=Dickson|first=E. J.|last2=Dickson|first2=E. J.|date=2019-10-08|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> and it was also alleged to have been a recruiting platform for a [[secret society]] (variously called \"DOS\" or \"The Vow\"), in which women were [[Human branding |branded]] and forced into [[sexual slavery]].\n\nIn early 2018, NXIVM's founder [[Keith Raniere]] and his associate, actress [[Allison Mack]], were arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on federal charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\">{{cite web |work= nbcnewyork.com |url= https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Leader-of-Secret-Upstate-New-York-Group-Charged-with-Sex-Trafficking-477966643.html |title= Leader of NY Group Branded Women, Made Them Sex Slaves: Feds |date= March 26, 2018 |publisher= NBCUniversal Media, LLC |accessdate= April 21, 2018}}</ref> Others associated with NXIVM were also charged with federal crimes. {{As of|2019|April|df=}} five people associated with NXIVM\u2014Mack, NXIVM co-founder Nancy Salzman, Lauren Salzman, [[Seagram]] heiress [[Clare Bronfman]], and bookkeeper Kathy Russell\u2014had pleaded guilty to various charges.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-47996207 |title= Nxivm: Seagram heiress Clare Bronfman pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |website= BBC News |author= |date= April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.thecut.com/2019/04/the-most-disturbing-details-from-the-nxivm-sex-cult-case.html |title= The Most Disturbing Details From the NXIVM Sex-Cult Case |website= The Cut |date= April 19, 2019 |last= Arnold |first= Amanda |accessdate= April 20, 2019}}</ref> Raniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019. On June 19, 2019, a Federal District Court in Brooklyn convicted Raniere of [[Sex trafficking in the United States |sex trafficking]] and [[racketeering]].<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/19/nyregion/nxivm-trial-verdict.html |title= Nxivm Trial: Leader Convicted After Trial Exposed Sex Cult's Sordid Inner Workings |last= Moynihan |first= Colin |date= June 19, 2019 |work= [[The New York Times]]|access-date= June 19, 2019 |issn= 0362-4331 | quote = On Wednesday, jurors in Federal District Court in Brooklyn sided with prosecutors. They found Keith Raniere, the leader of the cultlike group near Albany known as Nxivm, guilty of racketeering and sex trafficking, ending a six-week trial that exposed the sordid inner workings of the organization.}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/06/19/nxivm-cult-leader-keith-reniere-found-fuilty-sex-trafficking-case/|title= He told women he could help. Instead, he branded them with his initials and made them sex slaves.|first= Reis |last= Thebault |newspaper= [[The Washington Post]]|date= June 19, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n==History==\nPrior to founding NXIVM, Raniere had created \"Consumers Buyline\", a business venture which was accused by the [[New York (state)|New York]] [[Attorney General of New York|Attorney General]] of having been a [[pyramid scheme]]; Raniere signed a consent order in 1996 in which he denied any wrongdoing, but agreed to pay a $40,000 fine and to be permanently banned from \"promoting, offering or granting participation in a chain distribution scheme\".<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120220\">{{cite web |title='Ample evidence' to justify investigation |date=February 20, 2012 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ample-evidence-to-justify-investigation-3337402.php}}</ref>\n\n===Founding and initial success===\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere and Nancy Salzman founded NXIVM, a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref> offering \"Executive Success Programs\" (ESPs) and a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-keith-raniere-self-help-guru-accused-sex-trafficking-and-branding-slave-863816 |title=Who is Keith Raniere? Self-help guru accused of sex trafficking |date=March 28, 2018 |work=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=April 22, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"AECEB\">A&E Cults and Extreme Belief S1E1, aired May 28, 2018, last accessed May 30, 2018, https://www.aetv.com/shows/cults-and-extreme-belief/season-1/episode-1.</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\">{{cite web |title=The 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=May 30, 2018  |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html}}</ref> Raniere claimed that the programs' \"main emphasis is to have people experience more joy in their lives.\"<ref name=\"AECEB\"/>\n\nDuring NXIVM [[seminar]]s, students were expected to call Raniere and Salzman \"Vanguard\" and \"Prefect\", respectively.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120210\">{{cite web |last1=Odato |first=James |last2=Gish |first2=Jennifer |date=February 11, 2012 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secrets-of-NXIVM-2880885.php |title=Secrets of NXIVM |work=Albany Times Union |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Barcella |first=Laura |date=November 21, 2017 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/is-nxivm-a-cult-what-we-know-w512261 |title=Is NXIVM a Cult? What We Know |work=RollingStone.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"VF1\">{{cite web |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |work=VanityFair.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' stated that Raniere \"adopted the title 'Vanguard' from a [[Vanguard (video game)|favorite arcade game]] ... in which the destruction of one's enemies increased one's own power.\"<ref name=\"THR201805\">{{cite web |title=Her Darkest Role: Actress Allison Mack's Descent From 'Smallville' to Sex Cult |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |date=May 16, 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/how-smallvilles-allison-mack-went-actress-sex-cult-slaver-1112107}}</ref> Within the organization, the reasoning for the titles was that Raniere was the leader of a philosophical movement and Salzman was his first student.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nBy 2003, some 3,700 people had taken part in ESP classes, reportedly including businesswoman [[Sheila Johnson]]; former [[Surgeon General of the United States|Surgeon General]] [[Antonia Novello]]; [[Enron]] executive Stephen Cooper; and Ana Cristina Fox, daughter of former [[President of Mexico|Mexican president]] [[Vicente Fox]].<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref> Other participants were later reported to include entrepreneur [[Richard Branson]] (who later denied having taken the classes<ref name=\"VF20180420\">{{cite web |title=This Keith Raniere Sex-Cult Story Is Much Deeper Than Allison Mack's Arrest |accessdate=March 30, 2018 |date=April 20, 2018 |work=Vanity Fair |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/04/allison-mack-arrested-in-connection-to-keith-raniere}}</ref><ref name=\"TDB20180526\">{{cite web |title=A Top NXIVM Sex Cult Recruiter Comes Forward, Says Founder 'Messed With the Wrong Person' |accessdate=March 30, 2018 |date=March 26, 2018 |work=The Daily Beast |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/a-top-nxivm-sex-cult-recruiter-comes-forward-he-messed-with-the-wrong-person}}</ref>), [[Edgar Bronfman Sr.]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Freedman |first=Michael |title=Cult of Personality |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html#2d0f43511853Cult |accessdate=July 26, 2019 |newspaper=Forbes |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref> and actresses [[Linda Evans]], [[Grace Park (actress)|Grace Park]], and [[Nicki Clyne]].<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"VF201011\"/> In the early 2000s, [[Seagram]] heiresses [[Clare Bronfman|Clare]] and [[Sara Bronfman]], daughters of Edgar Bronfman Sr., became attached to the organization.<ref name=\"VF201011\">{{cite web |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\n===Cult allegations in early 2000s===\nNXIVM's training is a [[trade secret]], subject to [[non-disclosure agreements]], but reportedly uses a technique the organization calls \"rational inquiry\" to facilitate personal and professional development. In 2003, [[NXIVM Corp. v. The Ross Institute|NXIVM sued the Ross Institute]], alleging [[copyright infringement]] for publishing excerpts of content from its manual in three critical articles commissioned by cult investigator [[Rick Alan Ross]] and posted on his website.<ref name=Hochman>{{citation |title=A Forensic Psychiatrist Evaluates ESP |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/6047-a-forensic-psychiatrist-evaluates-esp.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin1>{{citation |title=A Critical Analysis of the Executive Success Programs Inc. |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5969-a-critical-analysis-of-the-executive-success-programs-inc.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin2>{{citation |title=Robert Jay Lifton's eight criteria of thought reform as applied to the Executive Success Programs |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5980-robert-jay-liftons-eight-criteria-of-thought-reform-as-applied-to-the-executive-success-programs.html}}</ref> Ross posted a [[psychiatrist]]'s assessment of NXIVM's \"secret\" manual on his website{{spaced ndash}}the report called the regimen \"expensive [[brainwashing]]\". The manual was obtained by Ross from former member Stephanie Franco, a co-[[defendant]] in the trial, who had signed a non-disclosure agreement not to divulge information from the manual to others. NXIVM filed suits in both New York and [[New Jersey]], but both were later dismissed.<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=NXIVM Corp. v. Ross |url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/nxivm-corp-v-ross |work=legal case |publisher=Citizen media law company |accessdate=February 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2003, ''[[Forbes]]'' published an article on NXIVM and Raniere.<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref>  ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' subsequently reported of the article: \"People at NXIVM were stunned. Expecting a positive story, the top ranks had spoken to Forbes, including Raniere, Salzman, and Sara Bronfman. What upset them above all were Edgar Bronfman\u2019s remarks. 'I think it\u2019s a cult,' Edgar Bronfman told the magazine, going on to say that he was troubled about the 'emotional and financial' investment in NXIVM by his daughters, to whom he hadn\u2019t spoken in months.\"<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\"/>  In 2006, ''Forbes'' published an article about the Bronfman sisters, stating that they had taken out a [[line of credit]] to loan NXIVM [[United States dollar|US$]]2 million, repayable through personal training sessions and phone consultations with Salzman.<ref name=\"Forbes20060724\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2006/0724/044a.html |title=The Bronfmans And the Cult |last=Berman |first=Phyllis |date=June 24, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=July 24, 2006 |last2=Gillies |first2=Andrew T. |last3=Novack |first3=Janet |last4=Egan |first4=Mary Ellen |last5=Blakeley |first5=Kiri}}</ref> Another ''Forbes'' article in 2010 discussed the failures of [[commodities]] and real estate deals by the Bronfmans made pursuant to Raniere's advice.<ref name=\"Forbes20100329\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/docket/2010/03/29/the-bronfmans-and-the-cult/#4da4f941538f |title=The Bronfmans and The 'Cult' |last=Vardi |first=Nathan |date=March 29, 2010 |work=Forbes |accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2006-2015===\nAfter actress [[Kristin Kreuk]] became involved with NXIVM in 2006, Salzman and her daughter Lauren went to [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] to recruit Kreuk's ''[[Smallville]]'' co-star [[Allison Mack]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> The younger Salzman (herself a junior NXIVM leader)<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> bonded with Mack and the latter became involved,<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> although Kreuk would subsequently leave NXIVM.<ref name=\"TDB201803\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/smallville-actress-kristin-kreuk-horrified-and-disgusted-by-nxivm-cult-she-left |title='Smallville' Actress Kristin Kreuk 'Horrified and Disgusted' by Nxivm Cult She Left |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref> Mack became \"an enthusiastic proselytizer\" for NXIVM, persuading her parents to take courses, and, after wrapping production of ''Smallville'' in 2011, moved to [[Clifton Park, New York]] near NXIVM's home-base in [[Albany, New York|Albany]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Early 2007 saw a string of financial contributions from NXIVM participants to [[Hillary Clinton]]'s [[Hillary Clinton presidential campaign, 2008|first presidential campaign]], with over a dozen participants donating the maximum allowable figure of $2,300. The contributions totalled $29,900. NXIVM associates also gave $31,600 to the state Republican Senate Campaign Committee and provided $34,763 worth of air transportation, totaling $66,363.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2007/10/01/hillarys-30000-fans-are-her-cult-following/ |title=HILLARY'S $30,000 FANS ARE HER 'CULT' FOLLOWING |first=Charles |last=Hurt |date=October 1, 2007 |publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the Bronfman sisters allegedly pressured Stephen Herbits, a confidante of their father, to ask [[Albany County, New York|Albany County]] [[District Attorney]] David Soares, [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Eliot Spitzer]], and [[Attorney General of New Jersey|New Jersey Attorney General]] [[Anne Milgram]] to open criminal investigations into NXIVM's critics. NXIVM reportedly kept dossiers on Soares, Spitzer, political consultant [[Roger Stone]], [[United States Senator|U.S. Senator]] [[Chuck Schumer]], and Albany ''[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]'' publisher [[George Randolph Hearst III]] in a box in the basement of Nancy Salzman's home.<ref>[https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-13851003.php Witness: Bronfmans tried to apply political pressure]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Gavin, Robert. ''Times Union''. May 16, 2019.</ref> According to the ''Times Union'', NXIVM \"developed a reputation for aggressively pursuing critics and defectors who broke from its ranks, including using [[litigation]] to punish critics of Raniere, the organization, or its training methods.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/FBI-shifts-mountain-of-data-in-NXIVM-s-seized-13254160.php |title=FBI shifts mountain of data in NXIVM's seized computers |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 24, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\nThe World Ethical Foundations Consortium, an organization co-founded by Raniere and the Bronfman sisters, sponsored a visit to Albany by the [[14th Dalai Lama]] in 2009. The visit was initially cancelled due to negative press surrounding NXIVM,<ref>{{cite web |last=Ettkin |first=Brian |date=April 6, 2009 |url=http://www.newstimes.com/news/article/Dalai-Lama-cancels-his-visit-to-Albany-118447.php |title=Dalai Lama Cancels His Visit to Albany |work=[[The News-Times]] |accessdate=November 2, 2011}}</ref> but was rescheduled; the Dalai Lama spoke at Albany's [[Palace Theatre (Albany, New York)|Palace Theatre]] in May 2009.<ref>{{cite web |last=Caprood |first=Tom |date=May 7, 2009 |url=http://www.troyrecord.com/article/TR/20090507/NEWS/305079979 |title=Dalai Lama fills Palace with message of compassion |work=TroyRecord.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref>   Subsequently, in 2017, [[Lama]] Tenzin Dhonden, the self-styled \"Personal Emissary for Peace for the Dalai Lama\" who had arranged the appearance, was suspended from his position amid corruption charges; the investigation also revealed a personal relationship between Dhonden and Sara Bronfman, which began in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Suspended Lama Tenzin Dhonden Had A Lover Too! |url=http://www.tibetanjournal.com/suspended-lama-tenzin-lover/ |work=Tibetan Journal |date=November 1, 2017 |access-date=August 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been described as a pyramid scheme,<ref name=\"TimesUnion20171113\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Lawyer attacks NXIVM 'scheme' |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Lawyer-attacks-NXIVM-scheme-1032548.php |website=TimesUnion.com |publisher=The Hearst Corporation |accessdate=November 13, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Slate201803\">{{cite web |title=The Only (Alleged) Sex-Slave Cult Story You Need to Understand: Kirsten Gillibrand's Weakness as a 2020 Candidate |website=Slate.com |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/03/kirsten-gillibrand-alleged-sex-slavery-and-the-2020-primary.html}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT18Oct\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html?pagewanted=all |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |last=Meier |first=Barry |work=NY Times|access-date=October 18, 2017 |quote=In a letter, the agency said it would not look into Dr. Roberts because she was not acting as Ms. Edmondson\u2019s doctor when the branding is said to have happened.}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> a sex-trafficking operation,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-47563045 |title=Associate pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |date=March 13, 2019 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> a cult,<ref name=\"TheNation20141118\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenation.com/article/190881/how-strange-secretive-cult-company-waging-legal-war-against-journalists |title=How a Strange, Secretive, Cult-like Company Is Waging Legal War Against Journalists |last=Cohan |first=William D. |date=November 18, 2014 |work=[[The Nation]] |access-date=May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case - HoustonChronicle.com |date=April 19, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/members-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-federal-court/story?id=60645426 |title=Members of alleged sex cult NXIVM appear in federal court |first=A. B. C. |last=News |website=ABC News}}</ref> and a sex cult.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-44946059 |title=Heiress among four arrested in 'sex cult' |author= |date=July 25, 2018 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 14, 2019}}</ref> In a 2010 article in the ''Times Union'', former NXIVM coaches characterized students as \"prey\" for use by Raniere in satisfying his sexual or [[gambling]]-related proclivities.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20101122\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Ex-NXIVM trainer: Students are prey |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ex-NXIVM-trainer-Students-are-prey-824046.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=November 22, 2010}}</ref> Kristin Keeffe, a longtime partner of Raniere and mother of his child, left the group in 2014 and described Raniere as \"dangerous\", stating that \"[a]ll the worst things you know about NXIVM are true.\"<ref name=\"TimesUnion20140512\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=A split from NXIVM |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=May 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Media investigations of DOS===\nStarting with reports on the Frank Report blog in June 2017<ref>https://frankreport.com/2017/06/13/part-1-the-slave-women-of-dos-revealed/</ref> and bolstered by an October 2017 article in ''[[The New York Times]]'', details began to emerge about DOS, a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM, in which female members were allegedly referred to as \"slaves,\" [[human branding|branded]] with the initials of Raniere and Mack, subjected to [[corporal punishment]] from their \"masters\", and required to provide nude photos or other potentially damaging information about themselves as \"collateral\".<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher=ABC News |website=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\">{{cite web |title=NXIVM: What We Know About Alleged Sex Trafficking, Forced Labor |author=Barcella, Laura |work=Rolling Stone |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=April 20, 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/nxivm-what-we-know-about-alleged-sex-trafficking-forced-labor-w518483}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> Law enforcement representatives have alleged that members of DOS were forced into [[sexual slavery]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180327\">{{cite news |title=What is Nxivm? |date=March 27, 2018 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=http://www.newsweek.com/nxivm-keith-raniere-sex-trafficking-self-help-vow-dos-slaves-multi-level-861293}}</ref>\n\n[[Sarah Edmondson]], a [[Canada|Canadian]] actress who had been an ESP participant since 2005, said that she left NXIVM after Mack inducted her into DOS the preceding March at her home in Albany. Edmondson alleged that participants were [[blindfold]]ed naked, held down by Mack and three other women, and branded by NXIVM-affiliated doctor Danielle Roberts, using a [[cauterizing|cauterizing pen]].<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s5pRd-QTk_w |title=Canadian woman says she was ritually branded and indoctrinated by a 'cultish group' in the U.S. |last=CBC News |date=October 27, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news |title=Vancouver woman says scars from ritual 'branding' fuel her fight against 'cultish' group |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/sarah-edmondson-executive-success-programs-esp-nxivm-branding-1.4374048 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |date=October 27, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Appearing on an [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] television program about [[cult]]s, Edmondson would provide additional context on the use of the \"collateral\" concept, stating that it was used in innocuous forms from the earliest, outermost stages of NXIVM in order to acclimatize victims\u2014for example, collateralizing small amounts of money that one might forfeit if one did not go to the gym one day.<ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> The ''Times'' would later report that \"hundreds\" of members left NXIVM after Edmondson went public about her experience.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nOn December 15, 2017, the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] newsmagazine ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'' aired an expos\u00e9 featuring interviews with many former NXIVM adherents, including Edmondson and [[Catherine Oxenberg]], who alleged that her daughter, India Oxenberg, was in danger due to the group. Several former members reported financial and [[sexual predation]] carried out by NXIVM leaders.<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFV3zEFIs_k |title=Former NXIVM member describes being branded in secret sorority initiation: Part 1 |last=ABC News |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref> Edmondson was further featured in \"Escaping NXIVM\", during the first season of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] [[podcast]] ''Uncover''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Escaping NXIVM |last= |first= |date=September 5, 2018 |website=cbc.ca |publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=November 13, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nSeven socially-prominent Mexicans, including Emilio Salinas Occelli (son of former president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]]) and Ana Cristina Fox (daughter of former president [[Vicente Fox]]), Rosa Laura Junco, Loreta Garza D\u00e1vila (a business leader from [[Nuevo Leon]]), Daniela Padilla, Camila Fern\u00e1ndez, and M\u00f3nica Dur\u00e1n, have been accused of involvement, according to an article in the ''[[New York Times]]'' published on May 26, 2019.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/quienes-son-los-mexicanos-involucrados-con-la-secta-nxivm-3674611.html |title=\u00bfQui\u00e9nes son los mexicanos involucrados con la secta NXIVM? |newspaper=El Sol de Mexico |accessdate=May 26, 2019 |language=Spanish |date=May 26, 2019|trans-title=Who are the Mexicans involved with the NXIVM sect?}}</ref>\n\n===Criminal prosecutions and convictions===\nIn March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in Nxivm sex cult |last=Siemaszko |first=Corky |date=May 4, 2018 |work=[[NBC News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> He was arrested in [[Mexico]] and held in custody in New York after appearing in federal court in [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/leader-of-alleged-cult-that-ensnared-vancouver-woman-appears-in-court-1.4595940 |title=Leader of alleged cult that ensnared Vancouver woman appears in court |date=March 27, 2018 |work=CBC}}</ref> The indictment alleged that at least one woman was coerced into sex with Raniere, who forced DOS members to undergo the branding ritual alleged by Edmondson and others.<ref>{{cite news |title=Feds say self-help guru coerced followers into sex, had them branded with a cauterizing pen |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/03/27/feds-say-self-help-guru-coerced-followers-into-sex-had-them-branded-with-a-cauterizing-pen/?noredirect=on |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 27, 2018|last=Swenson|first=Kyle}}</ref><ref name=\"CBS20180327\">{{cite news |title=NXIVM female sex \"slaves\" allegedly branded with secretive group leader's initials |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/nxivm-leader-keith-raniere-charged-sex-trafficking |work=CBS |agency=Associated Press |date=March 27, 2018}}</ref> [[United States Attorney]] Richard Donoghue stated that Raniere \"created a secret society of women whom he had sex with and branded with his initials, coercing them with the threat of releasing their highly personal information and taking their assets.\"<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/>\n\nOn April 20, 2018, Mack was arrested and indicted on similar charges to Raniere's. According to [[prosecutor]]s, after she recruited women into first NXIVM and then DOS, Mack coerced them into engaging in sexual activity with Raniere and performing menial tasks, for which she was allegedly paid by Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Mack was further alleged to be second-in-command of NXIVM after Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/><ref name=\"TDB201803\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.justice.gov/usao-edny/pr/founder-nxivm-purported-self-help-organization-and-actor-indicted-sex-trafficking-and |title=Founder of \"NXIVM\", a Purported Self-Help Organization, and Actor Indicted for Sex Trafficking and Forced Labor Conspiracy |website=www.justice.gov |accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Smallville Actress Arrested for Role in Alleged Sex Cult that Branded and Enslaved Women |url=http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 20, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422083052/http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult/|archive-date=April 22, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/22/smallville-actor-was-allegedly-a-top-member-of-cult-that-abused-women |title=Smallville's Allison Mack was allegedly a 'top member' of cult that abused women |first=Edward |last=Helmore |date=April 22, 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 24, Mack was released on $5 million bond pending trial and held under [[house arrest]] with her parents in [[California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-actress-granted-bail-sex-cult-case-2018-04-24 |title=Allison Mack of \"Smallville\" granted bail in sex cult case |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gonzalez |first=Sandra |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/24/entertainment/allison-mack/index.html |title=Allison Mack granted bail in sex trafficking case |work=CNN |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018}}</ref> If convicted of all charges, Mack and Raniere face a minimum of fifteen years and up to [[life imprisonment|life in prison]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult-keith-raniere/ |title=\"Smallville\" actress Allison Mack arrested for role in NXIVM sex cult |last=Park |first=Andrea |date=April 21, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On May 4, Raniere pleaded not guilty.<ref name=NBCMay4>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in sex cult |work=NBC News |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSalzman's home was raided shortly after Raniere's arrest,<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> and prosecutors stated during his arraignment that further arrests and a superseding indictment for Raniere and Mack should be expected.<ref name=TimesUnion20180504>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Keith-Raniere-Allison-Mack-head-to-court-in-12887478.php |title=Raniere, Mack appear in court on sex-slavery charges |work=Albany Times-Union |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name=News10May4>{{cite web |url=http://www.news10.com/news/local-news/trial-date-set-for-keith-raniere-and-allison-mack/1159493630 |title=Trial date set for Keith Raniere and Allison Mack |work=Albany News 10 |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> In late May, authorities moved to seize two NXIVM-owned properties near Albany.<ref>{{cite web |title=Foreclosure Complaint Reveals NXIVM Sex Cult Rituals In Upstate New York |date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 29, 2018 |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2018/05/24/nxivm-sex-cult-foreclose-halfmoon}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, the ''[[New York Post]]'' reported that NXIVM had moved to [[Brooklyn, New York]] and was being led by Clare Bronfman.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2018/04/21/sex-cult-moves-to-brooklyn-and-is-ready-for-war/ |title='Sex cult' moves to Brooklyn \u2014 and is ready for 'war' |first=Laura |last=Italiano |date=April 21, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> On June 12, 2018, the ''Times Union'' reported that NXIVM had suspended its operations due to \"extraordinary circumstances facing the company\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-suspends-all-operations-12987928.php |title=NXIVM suspends all operations; founder's bail denied |first1=Steve |last1=Hughes |first2=The Associated |last2=Press |date=June 12, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Bronfman was arrested on July 24 and charged with [[racketeering]]. She was released to house arrest after signing a $100 million [[bail bond]]. Also arrested and charged with the same crime were NXIVM President Nancy Salzman; her daughter, Lauren Salzman; and another NXIVM employee, Kathy Russell.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4350140/clare-bronfman-seagrams-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult/ |title=Clare Bronfman, Seagram's heiress, arrested in Nxivm sex-trafficking case |website=globalnews.ca |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/nxivm-bronfman-sex-cult-racketeering-1.4759640 |title=Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM Bronfman and five others accused of racketeering related to operations of a cult-like pyramid group |last=Proctor |first=Jason |date=July 24, 2018 |website=CBC |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2019, Nancy Salzman pleaded guilty to a charge of racketeering criminal conspiracy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-crime-cult-idUSKCN1QU2Z2 |title=Self-help guru Raniere faces U.S. child porn charges; associate pleads guilty |last=Brendan |first=Pierson |date=March 13, 2019 |work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=March 14, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/03/13/nxivm-co-founder-nancy-salzman-pleads-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Nxivm co-founder Nancy Salzman pleads guilty in sex cult case |last=Saul |first=Emily |date=March 13, 2019 |website=[[New York Post]] |language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-nxivm-case-smallville-actress-possible-plea-negotiations-keith-raniere-pleads-not-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Leader of alleged NXIVM sex cult pleads not guilty to child porn charges |website=www.cbsnews.com |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> Also in March 2019, Lauren Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering and racketeering conspiracy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Daughter-of-NXIVM-leader-pleads-guilty-13725939.php |title=Daughter of NXIVM leader pleads guilty |first1=Brendan J. |last1=Lyons |first2=Mike |last2=Goodwin |date=March 29, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> On April 8, 2019, Mack pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/apr/08/allison-mack-nxivm-pleads-guilty-racketeering-charges |title=Smallville star Allison Mack pleads guilty to racketeering in Nxivm case |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 8, 2019 |accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to charges of [[Illegal immigration to the United States|harboring an alien]] and [[identity fraud]]; bookkeeper Russell also pleaded guilty to [[visa fraud]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/nyregion/nxivm-clare-bronfman.html |title=Clare Bronfman Pleads Guilty in Nxivm 'Sex Cult' Case, Leaving Leader to Stand Trial Alone |last=Meier |first=Barry |date=April 19, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=April 20, 2019 |last2=Moynihan |first2=Colin |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nRaniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706/|title=Video Center|website=NEWS10 ABC}}</ref> On June 19, 2019, he was convicted of racketeering and sex trafficking.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, a federal lawsuit was filed in New York accusing Raniere and 14 associates of conducting illegal psychological experiments on members of the company and abusing them physically, emotionally and financially.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/29/us/nxivm-lawsuit-experiments-abuse/index.html|title=Nxivm leadership accused of illegal psychological experiments and systematic abuse in federal lawsuit|author1=Giulia McDonnell Nieto del Rio |author2=Madeline Holcombe |author3=Rob Frehse|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n\n==Beliefs and practices==\n[[File:US v. Raniere GovtExhibit GX46.JPG|right|upright=0.7|thumb|NXIVM founder Keith Raniere]]\nIn NXIVM classes, rank was signified by the wearing of colored sashes, similar to belts used in various martial arts.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/the-stripe-path-how-to-make-your-way-up-in-nxivm-1.4674369</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a 12-point \"Mission Statement\", which participants recited, pledging to \"purge\" themselves \"of all parasite and envy-based habits\", to enroll others in such courses, and to \"ethically control as much of the money, wealth and resources of the world as possible within my success plan\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/09/nyregion/nxivm-cult-trial.html |title=Former Sex Cult Official Describes Its 'Evil' Inner Workings |first=Colin |last=Moynihan |date=May 9, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Photographs of Raniere and Mack were displayed during classes, which would conclude with participants showing gratitude to the two leaders.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Uncover: Escaping NXIVM |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM conducted \"Intensives\" classes for 12 hours daily for 16 days. One cited price was $7,500.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/nxivm-trial-founder-keith-raniere-was-crime-boss-posing-as-guru-feds-say |title=NXIVM Trial Opens: Feds Say Founder Keith Raniere Was 'Crime Boss,' Not Guru |first=Pilar |last=Melendez |date=May 7, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Classes were divided into modules. In one module, \"Relationship Sourcing\", students were instructed to explore the benefits they would receive in the event of a partner's sudden death. Another module, \"Dracula and his ghouls\", reportedly discussed psychopaths and their followers. Other module titles included \"Best People; Perfect World\" and \"The Heroic Struggle\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/06/15/part-1-master-ranieres-secret-teachings-what-students-learn-in-esp-intensives/ |title=Part 1: Master Raniere's secret teachings: What students learn in ESP 'Intensives'! |date=June 15, 2017 |website=Frank Report - Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a practice, termed \"exploration of meaning\" that involved senior members questioning members as they delved into their childhood memories.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/nxivm-8-things-we-learned-from-sex-cult-expose-630616/ |title=Nxivm: 8 Things We Learned from 'Sex-Cult' Expos\u00e9 |first1=Elisabeth |last1=Garber-Paul |first2=Elisabeth |last2=Garber-Paul |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM taught that some people, called \"Suppressives\", try to impede progress within NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Witness-After-leaving-NXIVM-women-became-targets-13841142.php |title=Witness: Raniere bragged of wanting to 'break' follower Allison Mack |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=May 13, 2019 |website=Times Union |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> People who irrevocably turned against Raniere were said to have undergone \"The Fall\" and were labeled, in the words of a former member, as \"Luciferians, lost people for whom bad feels good, and good feels bad.\"<ref name=\"auto5\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/06/keith-raniere-nxivm-patents-luciferian |title=How NXIVM Used a Simple Tool to Build Its \"Sex Cult\" |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM members organized \"Vanguard Week\", an annual celebration of Raniere's birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-turned-Lake-George-resort-into-annual-13836853.php |title=NXIVM turned Lake George resort into annual Raniere birthday jamboree - SFChronicle.com |date=May 10, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been associated with several related organizations. '''Jness''' was a society aimed at women, while the '''Society of Protectors''' was aimed primarily at men.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\"/> A third group was known by the acronym DOS for \"'''Dominus Obsequious Sororium'''\", a Latin phrase that reportedly translates to \"Master over Slave Women\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/feds-self-help-guru-kept-women-as-sex-slaves-branded-them-with-his-initials |title=Feds: 'Self-Help' Guru Kept Women as Sex 'Slaves,' Branded Them With His Initials |first=Tatyana |last=Bellamy-Walker |date=March 27, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref>  In 2006, Raniere founded '''Rainbow Cultural Garden''', an international chain of child-care organizations in which children were to be exposed to seven different languages.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/alejandro-sanzs-wifes-miami-school-closed-by-state-tied-to-nxivm-sex-cult-founder-10295903 |title=State Closes Midtown Miami School Tied to NXIVM \"Sex Cult\" Leader |first=Jerry |last=Iannelli |date=April 27, 2018 |website=Miami New Times}}</ref>\n\nSome members of NXIVM's inner circle were reportedly taught that, in past lives, they were high-ranking [[Nazi]]s.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Suzanna |last=Andrews |website=Vanities |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> Barbara Bouchey was reportedly the reincarnation of Holocaust architect [[Reinhard Heydrich]], while Nancy Salzmann was supposed to be the reincarnation of Hitler. Raniere reported he had been a leader of anti-Nazi partisans.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2018/04/08/adolf-hitler-herman-goering-nxivm-sex-cult-leader-raniere-told-followers-reincarnated-nazis/ |title=From Adolf Hitler to Herman Goering, NXIVM sex-cult leader Raniere told followers they were 'Reincarnated Nazis'! |date=April 9, 2018 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a complaint filed by a former NXIVM member, a medical doctor performed an experiment on her that involved recording her EEG responses while viewing footage of people being murdered.<ref name=\"auto5\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://assets.documentcloud.org/documents/4113542/Porter-Complaint.pdf|title=Porter Complaint}}</ref> Brandon P. Porter, the doctor, faced 24 professional conduct charges from the New York State Board of the [[Office of Professional Medical Conduct]], including \"moral unfitness to practice medicine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/article/NXIVM-doctor-facing-state-charges-12890993.php |title=NXIVM doctor facing state charges |first=Steve |last=Barnes |date=May 5, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://apps.health.ny.gov/pubdoh/professionals/doctors/conduct/factions/FileDownloadAction.action?finalActionId=12236&fileName=CHRG+253486.pdf&fileSeqNum=1 |title=Notice Of Hearing In The Matter Of Brandon Porter, MD |publisher=Office for Professional Medical Conduct, New York State Department of Health |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>  In August 2019, Porter's license was revoked for his role in the experiments and for his failure to report an \"unusual disease outbreak\" which occurred at NXIVM's 2016 \"V-Week\" retreat.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-doctor-who-conducted-brain-studies-loses-14370824.php |title=NXIVM doctor who conducted brain studies loses license |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/08/22/dr-brandon-porter-loses-medical-license/ |title=Dr. Brandon Porter Loses Medical License |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n==Notable members and others==\nNXIVM was founded by '''Keith Raniere''' (born August 26, 1960).<ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\"/> In March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to [[NXIVM#Media investigations|DOS]] (a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM), including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\"/><ref name=\"news10.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706 |title=NXIVM TRIAL: Prosecution's opening statements lasted 90 minutes |date=May 7, 2019 |website=WTEN}}</ref> He was found guilty of all charges at trial.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chow |first1=Andrew |title=NXIVM Leader Keith Raniere Convicted on Sex Trafficking Charges. Here Are the Major Players in the Case |url=https://time.com/5568135/nxivm-allison-mack-raniere/ |website=Time |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere met '''Nancy Salzman''', a psychiatric nurse and trained practitioner of [[Hypnosis|hypnotism]] and [[Neuro-Linguistic Programming]]. The two founded \"Executive Success Programs\", a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\"/> offering a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>  In March 2019, Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/who-nancy-salzman-nxivm-co-founders-wrongdoings-shine-through-daughter-lauren-1431652 |title=Who is Nancy Salzman? Co-founder's daughter testifies in plea deal for NXIVM wrongdoings |first=Kelly Wynne On 5/21/19 at 11:22 AM |last=EDT |date=May 21, 2019 |website=Newsweek}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Bronfman sara.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Heiress Sara Bronfman, along with her sister Clare, bankrolled the NXIVM organization beginning in 2003.]]\n\n'''[[Sara Bronfman]]''' is the daughter of billionaire Seagrams chairman Edgar Bronfman Sr.  She was introduced to NXIVM by a family friend in 2002.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> She in turn introduced her sister, '''[[Clare Bronfman]]''' to NXIVM. Clare Bronfman was arrested by federal agents on July 24, 2018, in New York City and charged with money laundering and identity theft in connection with NXIVM activities. She pleaded not guilty in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York]] in Brooklyn. She was released on $100 million bond and placed on [[house arrest]] with [[electronic monitoring]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/crime-courts/feds-arrest-seagram-heiress-bronfman-nxivm-sex-slave-case-n894136 |title=Seagram heiress Bronfman pleads not guilty in NXIVM 'sex slave' case |work=NBC News| access-date=April 20, 2019 |date=July 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to conspiracy to conceal and harbor illegal aliens for financial gain and fraudulent use of identification. She faces 21 to 27 months in prison and has agreed to forfeit $6 million.<ref name=lyons>{{cite news |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=April 20, 2019 |newspaper=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Emiliano Salinas]]''' is a venture capitalist and businessman. He is the son of former Mexican president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]].  Salinas served as vice president of Prorsus Capital, a financial consortium with ties to Raniere and NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zimmerman |first1=Amy |title=Inside the NXIVM Sex Cult\u2019s Secret Plot to Take Over Mexico |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-the-nxivm-sex-cults-secret-plot-to-take-over-mexico |website=The Daily Beast |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n[[File:Allison Mack at ComicCon 2009 NN.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actress [[Allison Mack]] pleaded guilty to racketeering charges in April 2019 and is awaiting sentencing.]]\n\n'''Karen A. Unterreiner''' is a member who became Raniere's live-in partner beginning in the 1980s, and an early employee of his company Consumers' Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Raniere-stands-alone-13795442.php |title=Raniere stands alone |date=May 4, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> \n\n'''Pam Cafritz''' was the daughter of Washington-DC socialites Buffy and William Cafritz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>  In the 1990s, she resided with Raniere and Karen Unterreiner in an Albany home.  Both Unterreiner and Cafritz signed consent agreements with prosecutors for their role in Consumer's Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/07/making-vanguard-proud-the-mays-men-bring-executive-success-to-arkansas/ |title=Making Vanguard Proud \u2013 The Mays Men Bring Executive Success To Arkansas |date=July 7, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref> Cafritz was a founder of JNESS, the Raniere-affiliated women's group.  Cafritz was reported to be Raniere's 'most important long-term girlfriend'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>  On November 7, 2016, Pam Cafritz died.  After her death, her credit card was charged for over $300,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Ordered-to-seduce-Raniere-woman-planned-escape-13968629.php |title=Ordered to seduce Raniere, woman planned escape from NXIVM |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Allison Mack]]''' is an American actress known for her role on the series ''[[Smallville]]''. Mack was reportedly recruited to the [[Vancouver]] chapter of NXIVM, along with her ''Smallville'' co-star [[Kristin Kreuk]].<ref>{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=November 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180502001435/http://www.macleans.ca/economy/business/how-to-lose-100-million/2/ |archive-date=May 2, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>  Mack was reportedly a founder of DOS, a Raniere-affiliated Master/Slave group. Mack was arrested on April 20, 2018, on charges of [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (criminal)|conspiracy]], and [[forced labor]] conspiracy.  Mack pleaded guilty to [[racketeering]] charges in April 2019, and was to be sentenced in September 2019. However, on July 15, 2019 the Senior U.S. District Judge Nicholas Garaufis postponed the sentencing until further notice to allow federal probation officials to conduct pre-sentencing investigations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sentencing of NXIVM leader delayed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/amp/Sentencing-of-NXIVM-leader-delayed-14097454.php |newspaper=[[timesunion]]}}</ref>\n\n[[File:10.15.11NickiClyneByLuigiNovi2.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Canadian actress [[Nicki Clyne]]]]\n'''[[Nicki Clyne]]''' is a Canadian actress known for her role on the series ''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]''.  According to reports, in 2006, Clyne became involved with NXIVM. In 2008, she reportedly requested to be let out of her contract to focus full-time on NXIVM.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/11/19/nicki-clyne-quit-acting-broke-her-contract-with-battlestar-galatica-producers-to-join-nxivm-mission-full-time/ |title=Nicki Clyne quit acting, broke her contract with Battlestar Galatica{{sic|hide=y}} producers to join NXIVM mission full time |date=November 19, 2017 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n'''India Oxenberg''', daughter of actress [[Catherine Oxenberg]], was introduced to the group in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/catherine-oxenberg-on-losing-her-daughter-to-the-sex-cult-nxivm-going-public-was-a-last-resort |title=Catherine Oxenberg Reveals How She Lost Her Daughter to the Sex Cult NXIVM |first=Amy |last=Zimmerman |date=August 8, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> At Raniere's trial, a witness testified that India had spent a year on a 500-calorie-per-day diet.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/allison-mack-nxivm-trial-diet-500-calories-1443377 |title=Allison Mack reportedly forced NXIVM sex cult members to follow 500-calorie-a-day diets |first=Janice Williams On 6/11/19 at 10:42 AM |last=EDT |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Newsweek |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> In May 2017, India admitted to her mother that she was among those who had been branded.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-daughter-being-branded-nxivm/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg's Daughter Was 'Branded' with 'Cult' Leader's Initials: 'I Was Horrified' |website=PEOPLE.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> India left the group in June 2018, after Raniere's arrest.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-says-her-daughter-who-has-left-nxivm-is-moving-forward/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg Says Her Daughter Who Has Left Nxivm Is 'Moving Forward' |first1=Liz |last1=McNeil |first2=Johnny |last2=Dodd |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=August 7, 2018 |access-date=February 7, 2019}}</ref> In August 2018, Catherine Oxenberg's book ''Captive: A Mother's Crusade to Save Her Daughter from a Terrifying Cult'' was published.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.simonandschuster.com/books/Captive/Catherine-Oxenberg/9781982100650 |title=Captive |last1=Oxenberg |first1=Catherine |first2=Natasha |last2=Stoynoff |date=2018 |publisher=[[Gallery Publishing Group|Gallery Books]] |isbn=9781982100650}}</ref>\n\n===Critical former members===\n'''Toni Natalie''' met Raniere in 1991 when he was pitching his business \"Consumer's Buyline\".<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/politics/albany/2018/03/08/rochester-woman-battles-nxivm-keith-raniere/360847002/ |title=Rochester woman tells all about life with NXIVM's Keith Raniere, her ex |website=Rochester Democrat and Chronicle}}</ref> Natalie and her then-husband became top sellers for the organization.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>  Natalie recalled that she was able to stop smoking after a two-hour session with Raniere,<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> but this claim is disputed by her ex-husband.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/10/17/toni-natalies-keith-hypnotized-me-into-quitting-smoking-story-disputed-by-ex-husband-rusty/ |title=Toni Natalie's 'Keith Hypnotized Me Into Quitting Smoking' Story Disputed by Ex-Husband Rusty |last=Parlato |first=Frank |website=Frank Report |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref> Natalie and her son later moved to be near Raniere; her marriage ended shortly thereafter. Natalie and Raniere dated for the next eight years.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In the mid-90s, Raniere and Natalie operated a health-products store.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web |url=http://forbes/2003/1013/088 |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |website=Forbes}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, Raniere's eight-year relationship with Natalie ended. Natalie would subsequently claim to have been the victim of harassment.<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084744]{{dead link|date=June 2019}}</ref> In a January 2003 ruling, federal judge Robert Littlefield implied Raniere was using a legal suit to harass Natalie. Wrote Littlefield: \"This matter smacks of a jilted fellow's attempt at revenge or retaliation against his former girlfriend, with many attempts at tripping her up along the way\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.org/details/269747-natalie-jilted-boyfriend |title=Natalie Jilted Boyfriend |date=December 1, 2011 |publisher= |via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In 2011, Natalie filed documents in federal court alleging that she had been repeatedly raped by Raniere.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>\n\n'''Joseph J. O'Hara''' was an attorney who departed NXIVM in 2005 after accusing the group of misdeeds.   In 2007, O'Hara was indicted by Albany County.  It was later revealed that the District Attorney had allowed Raniere's girlfriend Kristin Keeffe to operate within its office as a sort of victims' advocate.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-pressed-district-attorney-3379748.php |title=NXIVM pressed district attorney |date=March 3, 2012}}</ref> Charges were ultimately dismissed.\n\n'''Barbara Bouchey''' was a client of Nancy Salzman, having been referred to her in 1988. Beginning in 2000, Bouchey dated Raniere. In 2009, Bouchey and eight other women (\"The NXIVM Nine\") confronted Raniere with concerns about abuse within the organization. That year, Bouchey left the group and later went to law enforcement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Guilty-plea-of-Salzman-ends-her-long-allegiance-13691433.php |title=Guilty plea ends Salzman's long allegiance to Raniere - TimesUnion.com |date=March 17, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Kristin Keeffe''' became Raniere's partner in the early 1990s.  In 2013, Keeffe gave birth to Raniere's son Gaelyn.<ref name=\"TU150920\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/tuplus-local/article/Legal-papers-NXIVM-officials-probed-finances-of-6516856.php |title=Legal papers: NXIVM officials probed finances of 6 federal judges, Senator Schumer, others |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 20, 2015 |website=Times Union}}</ref>  In February 2014, Keeffe broke with Raniere and his group. Fleeing the region with her son, an email bearing Keeffe's name explained: \"I have full sole legal custody of Gaelyn. Keith was experimenting on him. I had to get Gaelyn away\".<ref name=\"TU140511\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |title=A split from NXIVM |first=James M. |last=Odato |date=May 11, 2014 |website=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]}}</ref> Keeffe publicly described Raniere as \"dangerous\".<ref name=\"TU140511\"/>  In 2015, Keeffe alleged that NXIVM leaders had planned to lure critics to Mexico with an invitation to an anti-cult conference; once in Mexico, the critics were to be arrested on false charges by order of a judge who had been bribed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://culteducation.com/404-error-page.html |title=404 Error Page |website=culteducation.com|access-date=August 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811212201/https://www.culteducation.com/404-error-page.html|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cbc.ca\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084740 |title=TRANSCRIPT: Uncover: Escaping NXIVM - Season 1, EP 3 |work=[[CBC Radio]] |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TU151018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Records-NXIVM-hacked-billionaire-s-emails-with-6576310.php |title=Records: NXIVM hacked billionaire's emails with Hillary Clinton, world leaders |work=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=October 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Sarah Edmondson]]''' is a Canadian actress. After leaving NXIVM in early 2017, she publicly denounced the organization, claiming that she was invited into \"DOS,\" a substructure within NXIVM operated by Keith Raniere and [[Allison Mack]], and was branded with Raniere's and Mack's initials at Mack's{{Contradict-inline|reason=Two sources used here are contradictory: the Hollywood Reporter article says it was Mack's home, but the New York Times expos\u00e9 says it was Lauren Salzman's home.|date=April 2, 2020}} Albany home.<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite web |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |accessdate=May 13, 2018 |agency=ABC News |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nxivm member was branded at Allison Mack's home |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nxivm-member-was-branded-at-allison-macks-home-video-1113006 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |agency=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Edmondson showed the brand in a ''[[New York Times]]'' expos\u00e9 of NXIVM.<ref name=\"nyt\"/>\n\n'''Mark Vicente''', a filmmaker known for the 2004 film ''[[What the Bleep Do We Know!?]]'', began involvement with the group in 2005. Vicente testified against Raniere at his 2019 trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tonyortega.org/2019/05/09/filmmaker-breaks-down-describing-nxivms-duplicitous-ideas-and-evil-intent/ |title=Filmmaker breaks down describing Nxivm's duplicitous ideas and evil intent - The Underground Bunker |website=tonyortega.org |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Journalists and bloggers===\n'''James Odato''' is an investigative reporter who wrote for the Albany Times Union.  In 2012, Odato reported Raniere's history of pedophilia.   In October 2013, Odato was named in a lawsuit filed by NXIVM, along with Vanity Fair's Suzanna Andrews and blogger John J. Tighe;  all had written critically of the group.<ref name=\"politico.com\">{{Cite web |url=http://politi.co/1W2nbYE |title=Journalist on leave after tangle with secretive 'NXIVM' group |first=Joe |last=Pompeo |website=POLITICO Media}}</ref>  The suit alleged that NXIVM computers had been illegally accessed.   Shortly thereafter, Odato was described as being 'on leave' from the Times Union.<ref name=\"politico.com\"/>\n\nIn 2007, '''Frank Parlato''' was hired by NXIVM to help with publicity.  After concluding the members were being defrauded by Raniere, Parlato began blogging about the group on his sites \"ArtVoice\", \"The Niagara Falls Reporter\" and \"The Frank Report\".<ref>Vice News Tonight May 16, 2018\"</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\"/>\n\n'''John Tighe''' wrote about NXIVM on a blog.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secret-mission-A-child-589818.php |title=Secret mission: A child |first=JAMES M. ODATO Capitol |last=bureau |date=July 25, 2010 |website=Times Union}}</ref> In 2013, NXIVM accused Tighe of illegally accessing NXIVM servers using a former member's login information. Tighe's home was raided by the New York State Police, and his computer was seized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-hacking-case-to-be-tossed-6827893.php |title=NXIVM hacking case to be tossed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=February 13, 2016 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Several months later, State Police announced the discovery of child pornography on Tighe's computer; he was arrested. Facing a possible prison term of 20 years, Tighe pleaded guilty to a single count in exchange for a five-year sentence in federal prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/06/25/is-john-tighe-innocent-heres-a-few-facts-to-consider/ |title=Is John Tighe Innocent? \u2013 Here're a Few Facts to Consider |first=Is John Tighe Innocent?-Here\u2019re a Few Facts to Consider |last=says |date=June 25, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\n==Films, documentaries and books==\n* [[Investigation Discovery]] will release a two-hour special ''The Lost Women of NXIVM''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/investigation-discovery-the-lost-women-of-nxivm-1202635465/ |title='The Lost Women Of Nxivm': Investigation Discovery Explores Sex Cult In Two-Hour Special |first1=Peter |last1=White |first2=Peter |last2=White |date=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[HBO]] has announced their plans of making a docuseries about NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/nxivm-documentary-series-hbo-jehane-noujaim-karim-amer-1202060308/ |title=NXIVM Documentary Series from 'The Square' Filmmakers Coming to HBO |first1=Steve |last1=Greene |first2=Steve |last2=Greene |date=April 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hbo-plans-docuseries-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-1203073 |title=HBO Plans Docuseries on Alleged Sex Cult NXIVM |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/tv/alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-focus-hbo-documentary-series-n996196 |title=Alleged sex cult NXIVM focus of HBO documentary series |website=NBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Catherine Oxenberg]] produced a film for [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] about her daughter's experiences with NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/tv/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime/ |title=Lifetime Is Making a NXIVM Sex Cult Movie After Founder Keith Raniere's Conviction |website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime-catherine-oxenberg-peter-facinelli-star-1202637998/ |title=NXIVM Sex Cult Movie Set At Lifetime With Catherine Oxenberg Producing; Peter Facinelli & Andrea Roth To Star |first1=Denise |last1=Petski |first2=Denise |last2=Petski |date=July 1, 2019}}</ref> It is titled ''[[Escaping the NXIVM Cult: A Mother's Fight to Save Her Daughter]]'' and aired on September 21, 2019. While Catherine Oxenberg served as the narrator and executive producer, the film starred [[Andrea Roth]] as Catherine Oxenberg, [[Peter Facinelli]] as Keith Raniere, and [[Sara Fletcher]] as Allison Mack.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lifetime's Trailer For 'Escaping The NXIVM Cult' Shows Seduction And Anguish |url=https://deadline.com/video/lifetimes-trailer-for-escaping-the-nxivm-cult-shows-seduction-and-anguish/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n* \"The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM\" is an upcoming book by Toni Natalie and Chet Hardin set for release on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/28/new-book-by-toni-natalie-the-program-inside-the-mind-of-keith-raniere-and-the-rise-and-fall-of-nxivm/ |title=New Book by Toni Natalie: 'The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://www.grandcentralpublishing.com/titles/toni-natalie/the-program/9781538701034/ |title=The Program |date=March 5, 2019 |via=www.grandcentralpublishing.com}}</ref>\n* ''Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life'' by [[Sarah Edmondson]] is a book set that was released on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/07/28/scarred-the-true-story-of-how-i-escaped-nxivm-the-cult-that-bound-my-life/ |title=New Book By Sarah Edmondson 'Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n* NXIVM was the subject on an episode ''[[E! True Hollywood Story]]'' which featured interviews from several journalists and the people that were once involved with the organization including Catherine Oxenberg, Sarah Edmondson, and actor and Oxenberg's real-life friend [[Callum Blue]].1\n*[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] released a podcast in 2018 on NXIVM as part of CBC [https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/uncover-season-1-escaping-nxivm-1.4675949 Uncover Season 1].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180421090811/http://www.keithraniere.com/ Website] of [[Keith Raniere]]\n* [http://www.scs.cmu.edu/~dst/NXIVM/ Three critical articles pertaining to the ''NXIVM v. Ross Institute'' lawsuit]\n* [http://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/ ''Times Union'' Special Report on NXIVM]\n\n{{Multi-level marketing}}\n\n[[Category:1998 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Albany County, New York]]\n[[Category:Colonie, New York]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Large-group awareness training]]\n[[Category:Multi-level marketing companies]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Sexual misconduct allegations]]\n[[Category:Cults]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date= June 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NXIVM Corporation\n|logo = NXIVM_Logo.png\n|logo_size = 100px\n|type = [[Privately held company]]\n|foundation = 1998\n|location = [[Albany, New York|Albany]], [[New York (state) |New York]]\n|key_people = [[Keith Raniere]] (co-founder, leader)<br />Nancy Salzman (co-founder, president)<br />[[Allison Mack]] (recruiter, leader)<br />[[Clare Bronfman]] (funder, leader)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/01/23/brooklyn-judge-finds-issues-with-nxivm-defense-fund/ |title=Brooklyn judge finds 'issues' with Nxivm defense fund |work=nypost.com |first=Emily |last=Saul |date=January 23, 2019 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|industry = [[Multi-level marketing]]; [[personal development]]\n|products = Personal-growth seminars\n|revenue =\n|operating_income =\n|net_income =\n|num_employees =\n|homepage = {{url|http://www.nxivm.com |NXIVM.com}} ([https://web.archive.org/web/20190412162926/http://www.nxivm.com/ Archived])\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''NXIVM''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|n|\u025b|k|s|i|\u0259|m}} {{respell|NEKS|ee|\u0259m}}) is a self-described American [[multi-level marketing]] company<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vox.com/2018/4/25/17275930/allison-mack-smallville-actress-sex-cult-nxivm-dos-prison-arrest-sex-trafficking-keith-raniere |title= Seagram's heiress arrested for role in controversial \"sex cult\" |first= Tara Isabella |last= Burton |date =April 25, 2018 |website= Vox}}</ref> based near [[Albany, New York]], who offers [[personal development|personal]] and [[professional development|professional]] development [[seminar]]s through its \"Executive Success Programs\". The company has been widely described as a [[cult]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/nxivm-keith-raniere-wellness-scam-sex-cult-848439/|title=How NXIVM Was the Ultimate Wellness Scam|last=Dickson|first=E. J.|last2=Dickson|first2=E. J.|date=2019-10-08|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> and it was also alleged to have been a recruiting platform for a [[secret society]] (variously called \"DOS\" or \"The Vow\"), in which women were [[Human branding |branded]] and forced into [[sexual slavery]].\n\nIn early 2018, NXIVM's founder [[Keith Raniere]] and his associate, actress [[Allison Mack]], were arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on federal charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\">{{cite web |work= nbcnewyork.com |url= https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Leader-of-Secret-Upstate-New-York-Group-Charged-with-Sex-Trafficking-477966643.html |title= Leader of NY Group Branded Women, Made Them Sex Slaves: Feds |date= March 26, 2018 |publisher= NBCUniversal Media, LLC |accessdate= April 21, 2018}}</ref> Others associated with NXIVM were also charged with federal crimes. {{As of|2019|April|df=}} five people associated with NXIVM\u2014Mack, NXIVM co-founder Nancy Salzman, Lauren Salzman, [[Seagram]] heiress [[Clare Bronfman]], and bookkeeper Kathy Russell\u2014had pleaded guilty to various charges.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-47996207 |title= Nxivm: Seagram heiress Clare Bronfman pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |website= BBC News |author= |date= April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.thecut.com/2019/04/the-most-disturbing-details-from-the-nxivm-sex-cult-case.html |title= The Most Disturbing Details From the NXIVM Sex-Cult Case |website= The Cut |date= April 19, 2019 |last= Arnold |first= Amanda |accessdate= April 20, 2019}}</ref> Raniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019. On June 19, 2019, a Federal District Court in Brooklyn convicted Raniere of [[Sex trafficking in the United States |sex trafficking]] and [[racketeering]].<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/19/nyregion/nxivm-trial-verdict.html |title= Nxivm Trial: Leader Convicted After Trial Exposed Sex Cult's Sordid Inner Workings |last= Moynihan |first= Colin |date= June 19, 2019 |work= [[The New York Times]]|access-date= June 19, 2019 |issn= 0362-4331 | quote = On Wednesday, jurors in Federal District Court in Brooklyn sided with prosecutors. They found Keith Raniere, the leader of the cultlike group near Albany known as Nxivm, guilty of racketeering and sex trafficking, ending a six-week trial that exposed the sordid inner workings of the organization.}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/06/19/nxivm-cult-leader-keith-reniere-found-fuilty-sex-trafficking-case/|title= He told women he could help. Instead, he branded them with his initials and made them sex slaves.|first= Reis |last= Thebault |newspaper= [[The Washington Post]]|date= June 19, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n==History==\nPrior to founding NXIVM, Raniere had created \"Consumers Buyline\", a business venture which was accused by the [[New York (state)|New York]] [[Attorney General of New York|Attorney General]] of having been a [[pyramid scheme]]; Raniere signed a consent order in 1996 in which he denied any wrongdoing, but agreed to pay a $40,000 fine and to be permanently banned from \"promoting, offering or granting participation in a chain distribution scheme\".<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120220\">{{cite web |title='Ample evidence' to justify investigation |date=February 20, 2012 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ample-evidence-to-justify-investigation-3337402.php}}</ref>\n\n===Founding and initial success===\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere and Nancy Salzman founded NXIVM, a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref> offering \"Executive Success Programs\" (ESPs) and a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-keith-raniere-self-help-guru-accused-sex-trafficking-and-branding-slave-863816 |title=Who is Keith Raniere? Self-help guru accused of sex trafficking |date=March 28, 2018 |work=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=April 22, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"AECEB\">A&E Cults and Extreme Belief S1E1, aired May 28, 2018, last accessed May 30, 2018, https://www.aetv.com/shows/cults-and-extreme-belief/season-1/episode-1.</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\">{{cite web |title=The 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=May 30, 2018  |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html}}</ref> Raniere claimed that the programs' \"main emphasis is to have people experience more joy in their lives.\"<ref name=\"AECEB\"/>\n\nDuring NXIVM [[seminar]]s, students were expected to call Raniere and Salzman \"Vanguard\" and \"Prefect\", respectively.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120210\">{{cite web |last1=Odato |first=James |last2=Gish |first2=Jennifer |date=February 11, 2012 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secrets-of-NXIVM-2880885.php |title=Secrets of NXIVM |work=Albany Times Union |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Barcella |first=Laura |date=November 21, 2017 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/is-nxivm-a-cult-what-we-know-w512261 |title=Is NXIVM a Cult? What We Know |work=RollingStone.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"VF1\">{{cite web |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |work=VanityFair.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' stated that Raniere \"adopted the title 'Vanguard' from a [[Vanguard (video game)|favorite arcade game]] ... in which the destruction of one's enemies increased one's own power.\"<ref name=\"THR201805\">{{cite web |title=Her Darkest Role: Actress Allison Mack's Descent From 'Smallville' to Sex Cult |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |date=May 16, 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/how-smallvilles-allison-mack-went-actress-sex-cult-slaver-1112107}}</ref> Within the organization, the reasoning for the titles was that Raniere was the leader of a philosophical movement and Salzman was his first student.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nBy 2003, some 3,700 people had taken part in ESP classes, reportedly including businesswoman [[Sheila Johnson]]; former [[Surgeon General of the United States|Surgeon General]] [[Antonia Novello]]; [[Enron]] executive Stephen Cooper; and Ana Cristina Fox, daughter of former [[President of Mexico|Mexican president]] [[Vicente Fox]].<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref> Other participants were later reported to include entrepreneur [[Richard Branson]] (who later denied having taken the classes<ref name=\"VF20180420\">{{cite web |title=This Keith Raniere Sex-Cult Story Is Much Deeper Than Allison Mack's Arrest |accessdate=March 30, 2018 |date=April 20, 2018 |work=Vanity Fair |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/04/allison-mack-arrested-in-connection-to-keith-raniere}}</ref><ref name=\"TDB20180526\">{{cite web |title=A Top NXIVM Sex Cult Recruiter Comes Forward, Says Founder 'Messed With the Wrong Person' |accessdate=March 30, 2018 |date=March 26, 2018 |work=The Daily Beast |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/a-top-nxivm-sex-cult-recruiter-comes-forward-he-messed-with-the-wrong-person}}</ref>), [[Edgar Bronfman Sr.]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Freedman |first=Michael |title=Cult of Personality |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html#2d0f43511853Cult |accessdate=July 26, 2019 |newspaper=Forbes |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref> and actresses [[Linda Evans]], [[Grace Park (actress)|Grace Park]], and [[Nicki Clyne]].<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"VF201011\"/> In the early 2000s, [[Seagram]] heiresses [[Clare Bronfman|Clare]] and [[Sara Bronfman]], daughters of Edgar Bronfman Sr., became attached to the organization.<ref name=\"VF201011\">{{cite web |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\n===Cult allegations in early 2000s===\nNXIVM's training is a [[trade secret]], subject to [[non-disclosure agreements]], but reportedly uses a technique the organization calls \"rational inquiry\" to facilitate personal and professional development. In 2003, [[NXIVM Corp. v. The Ross Institute|NXIVM sued the Ross Institute]], alleging [[copyright infringement]] for publishing excerpts of content from its manual in three critical articles commissioned by cult investigator [[Rick Alan Ross]] and posted on his website.<ref name=Hochman>{{citation |title=A Forensic Psychiatrist Evaluates ESP |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/6047-a-forensic-psychiatrist-evaluates-esp.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin1>{{citation |title=A Critical Analysis of the Executive Success Programs Inc. |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5969-a-critical-analysis-of-the-executive-success-programs-inc.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin2>{{citation |title=Robert Jay Lifton's eight criteria of thought reform as applied to the Executive Success Programs |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5980-robert-jay-liftons-eight-criteria-of-thought-reform-as-applied-to-the-executive-success-programs.html}}</ref> Ross posted a [[psychiatrist]]'s assessment of NXIVM's \"secret\" manual on his website{{spaced ndash}}the report called the regimen \"expensive [[brainwashing]]\". The manual was obtained by Ross from former member Stephanie Franco, a co-[[defendant]] in the trial, who had signed a non-disclosure agreement not to divulge information from the manual to others. NXIVM filed suits in both New York and [[New Jersey]], but both were later dismissed.<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=NXIVM Corp. v. Ross |url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/nxivm-corp-v-ross |work=legal case |publisher=Citizen media law company |accessdate=February 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2003, ''[[Forbes]]'' published an article on NXIVM and Raniere.<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref>  ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' subsequently reported of the article: \"People at NXIVM were stunned. Expecting a positive story, the top ranks had spoken to Forbes, including Raniere, Salzman, and Sara Bronfman. What upset them above all were Edgar Bronfman\u2019s remarks. 'I think it\u2019s a cult,' Edgar Bronfman told the magazine, going on to say that he was troubled about the 'emotional and financial' investment in NXIVM by his daughters, to whom he hadn\u2019t spoken in months.\"<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\"/>  In 2006, ''Forbes'' published an article about the Bronfman sisters, stating that they had taken out a [[line of credit]] to loan NXIVM [[United States dollar|US$]]2 million, repayable through personal training sessions and phone consultations with Salzman.<ref name=\"Forbes20060724\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2006/0724/044a.html |title=The Bronfmans And the Cult |last=Berman |first=Phyllis |date=June 24, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=July 24, 2006 |last2=Gillies |first2=Andrew T. |last3=Novack |first3=Janet |last4=Egan |first4=Mary Ellen |last5=Blakeley |first5=Kiri}}</ref> Another ''Forbes'' article in 2010 discussed the failures of [[commodities]] and real estate deals by the Bronfmans made pursuant to Raniere's advice.<ref name=\"Forbes20100329\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/docket/2010/03/29/the-bronfmans-and-the-cult/#4da4f941538f |title=The Bronfmans and The 'Cult' |last=Vardi |first=Nathan |date=March 29, 2010 |work=Forbes |accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2006-2015===\nAfter actress [[Kristin Kreuk]] became involved with NXIVM in 2006, Salzman and her daughter Lauren went to [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] to recruit Kreuk's ''[[Smallville]]'' co-star [[Allison Mack]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> The younger Salzman (herself a junior NXIVM leader)<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> bonded with Mack and the latter became involved,<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> although Kreuk would subsequently leave NXIVM.<ref name=\"TDB201803\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/smallville-actress-kristin-kreuk-horrified-and-disgusted-by-nxivm-cult-she-left |title='Smallville' Actress Kristin Kreuk 'Horrified and Disgusted' by Nxivm Cult She Left |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref> Mack became \"an enthusiastic proselytizer\" for NXIVM, persuading her parents to take courses, and, after wrapping production of ''Smallville'' in 2011, moved to [[Clifton Park, New York]] near NXIVM's home-base in [[Albany, New York|Albany]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Early 2007 saw a string of financial contributions from NXIVM participants to [[Hillary Clinton]]'s [[Hillary Clinton presidential campaign, 2008|first presidential campaign]], with over a dozen participants donating the maximum allowable figure of $2,300. The contributions totalled $29,900. NXIVM associates also gave $31,600 to the state Republican Senate Campaign Committee and provided $34,763 worth of air transportation, totaling $66,363.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2007/10/01/hillarys-30000-fans-are-her-cult-following/ |title=HILLARY'S $30,000 FANS ARE HER 'CULT' FOLLOWING |first=Charles |last=Hurt |date=October 1, 2007 |publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the Bronfman sisters allegedly pressured Stephen Herbits, a confidante of their father, to ask [[Albany County, New York|Albany County]] [[District Attorney]] David Soares, [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Eliot Spitzer]], and [[Attorney General of New Jersey|New Jersey Attorney General]] [[Anne Milgram]] to open criminal investigations into NXIVM's critics. NXIVM reportedly kept dossiers on Soares, Spitzer, political consultant [[Roger Stone]], [[United States Senator|U.S. Senator]] [[Chuck Schumer]], and Albany ''[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]'' publisher [[George Randolph Hearst III]] in a box in the basement of Nancy Salzman's home.<ref>[https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-13851003.php Witness: Bronfmans tried to apply political pressure]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Gavin, Robert. ''Times Union''. May 16, 2019.</ref> According to the ''Times Union'', NXIVM \"developed a reputation for aggressively pursuing critics and defectors who broke from its ranks, including using [[litigation]] to punish critics of Raniere, the organization, or its training methods.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/FBI-shifts-mountain-of-data-in-NXIVM-s-seized-13254160.php |title=FBI shifts mountain of data in NXIVM's seized computers |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 24, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\nThe World Ethical Foundations Consortium, an organization co-founded by Raniere and the Bronfman sisters, sponsored a visit to Albany by the [[14th Dalai Lama]] in 2009. The visit was initially cancelled due to negative press surrounding NXIVM,<ref>{{cite web |last=Ettkin |first=Brian |date=April 6, 2009 |url=http://www.newstimes.com/news/article/Dalai-Lama-cancels-his-visit-to-Albany-118447.php |title=Dalai Lama Cancels His Visit to Albany |work=[[The News-Times]] |accessdate=November 2, 2011}}</ref> but was rescheduled; the Dalai Lama spoke at Albany's [[Palace Theatre (Albany, New York)|Palace Theatre]] in May 2009.<ref>{{cite web |last=Caprood |first=Tom |date=May 7, 2009 |url=http://www.troyrecord.com/article/TR/20090507/NEWS/305079979 |title=Dalai Lama fills Palace with message of compassion |work=TroyRecord.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref>   Subsequently, in 2017, [[Lama]] Tenzin Dhonden, the self-styled \"Personal Emissary for Peace for the Dalai Lama\" who had arranged the appearance, was suspended from his position amid corruption charges; the investigation also revealed a personal relationship between Dhonden and Sara Bronfman, which began in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Suspended Lama Tenzin Dhonden Had A Lover Too! |url=http://www.tibetanjournal.com/suspended-lama-tenzin-lover/ |work=Tibetan Journal |date=November 1, 2017 |access-date=August 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been described as a pyramid scheme,<ref name=\"TimesUnion20171113\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Lawyer attacks NXIVM 'scheme' |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Lawyer-attacks-NXIVM-scheme-1032548.php |website=TimesUnion.com |publisher=The Hearst Corporation |accessdate=November 13, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Slate201803\">{{cite web |title=The Only (Alleged) Sex-Slave Cult Story You Need to Understand: Kirsten Gillibrand's Weakness as a 2020 Candidate |website=Slate.com |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/03/kirsten-gillibrand-alleged-sex-slavery-and-the-2020-primary.html}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT18Oct\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html?pagewanted=all |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |last=Meier |first=Barry |work=NY Times|access-date=October 18, 2017 |quote=In a letter, the agency said it would not look into Dr. Roberts because she was not acting as Ms. Edmondson\u2019s doctor when the branding is said to have happened.}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> a sex-trafficking operation,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-47563045 |title=Associate pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |date=March 13, 2019 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> a cult,<ref name=\"TheNation20141118\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenation.com/article/190881/how-strange-secretive-cult-company-waging-legal-war-against-journalists |title=How a Strange, Secretive, Cult-like Company Is Waging Legal War Against Journalists |last=Cohan |first=William D. |date=November 18, 2014 |work=[[The Nation]] |access-date=May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case - HoustonChronicle.com |date=April 19, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/members-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-federal-court/story?id=60645426 |title=Members of alleged sex cult NXIVM appear in federal court |first=A. B. C. |last=News |website=ABC News}}</ref> and a sex cult.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-44946059 |title=Heiress among four arrested in 'sex cult' |author= |date=July 25, 2018 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 14, 2019}}</ref> In a 2010 article in the ''Times Union'', former NXIVM coaches characterized students as \"prey\" for use by Raniere in satisfying his sexual or [[gambling]]-related proclivities.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20101122\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Ex-NXIVM trainer: Students are prey |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ex-NXIVM-trainer-Students-are-prey-824046.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=November 22, 2010}}</ref> Kristin Keeffe, a longtime partner of Raniere and mother of his child, left the group in 2014 and described Raniere as \"dangerous\", stating that \"[a]ll the worst things you know about NXIVM are true.\"<ref name=\"TimesUnion20140512\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=A split from NXIVM |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=May 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Media investigations of DOS===\nStarting with reports on the Frank Report blog in June 2017<ref>https://frankreport.com/2017/06/13/part-1-the-slave-women-of-dos-revealed/</ref> and bolstered by an October 2017 article in ''[[The New York Times]]'', details began to emerge about DOS, a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM, in which female members were allegedly referred to as \"slaves,\" [[human branding|branded]] with the initials of Raniere and Mack, subjected to [[corporal punishment]] from their \"masters\", and required to provide nude photos or other potentially damaging information about themselves as \"collateral\".<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher=ABC News |website=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\">{{cite web |title=NXIVM: What We Know About Alleged Sex Trafficking, Forced Labor |author=Barcella, Laura |work=Rolling Stone |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=April 20, 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/nxivm-what-we-know-about-alleged-sex-trafficking-forced-labor-w518483}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> Law enforcement representatives have alleged that members of DOS were forced into [[sexual slavery]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180327\">{{cite news |title=What is Nxivm? |date=March 27, 2018 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=http://www.newsweek.com/nxivm-keith-raniere-sex-trafficking-self-help-vow-dos-slaves-multi-level-861293}}</ref>\n\n[[Sarah Edmondson]], a [[Canada|Canadian]] actress who had been an ESP participant since 2005, said that she left NXIVM after Mack inducted her into DOS the preceding March at her home in Albany. Edmondson alleged that participants were [[blindfold]]ed naked, held down by Mack and three other women, and branded by NXIVM-affiliated doctor Danielle Roberts, using a [[cauterizing|cauterizing pen]].<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s5pRd-QTk_w |title=Canadian woman says she was ritually branded and indoctrinated by a 'cultish group' in the U.S. |last=CBC News |date=October 27, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news |title=Vancouver woman says scars from ritual 'branding' fuel her fight against 'cultish' group |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/sarah-edmondson-executive-success-programs-esp-nxivm-branding-1.4374048 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |date=October 27, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Appearing on an [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] television program about [[cult]]s, Edmondson would provide additional context on the use of the \"collateral\" concept, stating that it was used in innocuous forms from the earliest, outermost stages of NXIVM in order to acclimatize victims\u2014for example, collateralizing small amounts of money that one might forfeit if one did not go to the gym one day.<ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> The ''Times'' would later report that \"hundreds\" of members left NXIVM after Edmondson went public about her experience.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nOn December 15, 2017, the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] newsmagazine ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'' aired an expos\u00e9 featuring interviews with many former NXIVM adherents, including Edmondson and [[Catherine Oxenberg]], who alleged that her daughter, India Oxenberg, was in danger due to the group. Several former members reported financial and [[sexual predation]] carried out by NXIVM leaders.<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFV3zEFIs_k |title=Former NXIVM member describes being branded in secret sorority initiation: Part 1 |last=ABC News |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref> Edmondson was further featured in \"Escaping NXIVM\", during the first season of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] [[podcast]] ''Uncover''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Escaping NXIVM |last= |first= |date=September 5, 2018 |website=cbc.ca |publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=November 13, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nSeven socially-prominent Mexicans, including Emilio Salinas Occelli (son of former president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]]) and Ana Cristina Fox (daughter of former president [[Vicente Fox]]), Rosa Laura Junco, Loreta Garza D\u00e1vila (a business leader from [[Nuevo Leon]]), Daniela Padilla, Camila Fern\u00e1ndez, and M\u00f3nica Dur\u00e1n, have been accused of involvement, according to an article in the ''[[New York Times]]'' published on May 26, 2019.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/quienes-son-los-mexicanos-involucrados-con-la-secta-nxivm-3674611.html |title=\u00bfQui\u00e9nes son los mexicanos involucrados con la secta NXIVM? |newspaper=El Sol de Mexico |accessdate=May 26, 2019 |language=Spanish |date=May 26, 2019|trans-title=Who are the Mexicans involved with the NXIVM sect?}}</ref>\n\n===Criminal prosecutions and convictions===\nIn March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in Nxivm sex cult |last=Siemaszko |first=Corky |date=May 4, 2018 |work=[[NBC News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> He was arrested in [[Mexico]] and held in custody in New York after appearing in federal court in [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/leader-of-alleged-cult-that-ensnared-vancouver-woman-appears-in-court-1.4595940 |title=Leader of alleged cult that ensnared Vancouver woman appears in court |date=March 27, 2018 |work=CBC}}</ref> The indictment alleged that at least one woman was coerced into sex with Raniere, who forced DOS members to undergo the branding ritual alleged by Edmondson and others.<ref>{{cite news |title=Feds say self-help guru coerced followers into sex, had them branded with a cauterizing pen |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/03/27/feds-say-self-help-guru-coerced-followers-into-sex-had-them-branded-with-a-cauterizing-pen/?noredirect=on |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 27, 2018|last=Swenson|first=Kyle}}</ref><ref name=\"CBS20180327\">{{cite news |title=NXIVM female sex \"slaves\" allegedly branded with secretive group leader's initials |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/nxivm-leader-keith-raniere-charged-sex-trafficking |work=CBS |agency=Associated Press |date=March 27, 2018}}</ref> [[United States Attorney]] Richard Donoghue stated that Raniere \"created a secret society of women whom he had sex with and branded with his initials, coercing them with the threat of releasing their highly personal information and taking their assets.\"<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/>\n\nOn April 20, 2018, Mack was arrested and indicted on similar charges to Raniere's. According to [[prosecutor]]s, after she recruited women into first NXIVM and then DOS, Mack coerced them into engaging in sexual activity with Raniere and performing menial tasks, for which she was allegedly paid by Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Mack was further alleged to be second-in-command of NXIVM after Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/><ref name=\"TDB201803\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.justice.gov/usao-edny/pr/founder-nxivm-purported-self-help-organization-and-actor-indicted-sex-trafficking-and |title=Founder of \"NXIVM\", a Purported Self-Help Organization, and Actor Indicted for Sex Trafficking and Forced Labor Conspiracy |website=www.justice.gov |accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Smallville Actress Arrested for Role in Alleged Sex Cult that Branded and Enslaved Women |url=http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 20, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422083052/http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult/|archive-date=April 22, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/22/smallville-actor-was-allegedly-a-top-member-of-cult-that-abused-women |title=Smallville's Allison Mack was allegedly a 'top member' of cult that abused women |first=Edward |last=Helmore |date=April 22, 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 24, Mack was released on $5 million bond pending trial and held under [[house arrest]] with her parents in [[California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-actress-granted-bail-sex-cult-case-2018-04-24 |title=Allison Mack of \"Smallville\" granted bail in sex cult case |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gonzalez |first=Sandra |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/24/entertainment/allison-mack/index.html |title=Allison Mack granted bail in sex trafficking case |work=CNN |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018}}</ref> If convicted of all charges, Mack and Raniere face a minimum of fifteen years and up to [[life imprisonment|life in prison]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult-keith-raniere/ |title=\"Smallville\" actress Allison Mack arrested for role in NXIVM sex cult |last=Park |first=Andrea |date=April 21, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On May 4, Raniere pleaded not guilty.<ref name=NBCMay4>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in sex cult |work=NBC News |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSalzman's home was raided shortly after Raniere's arrest,<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> and prosecutors stated during his arraignment that further arrests and a superseding indictment for Raniere and Mack should be expected.<ref name=TimesUnion20180504>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Keith-Raniere-Allison-Mack-head-to-court-in-12887478.php |title=Raniere, Mack appear in court on sex-slavery charges |work=Albany Times-Union |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name=News10May4>{{cite web |url=http://www.news10.com/news/local-news/trial-date-set-for-keith-raniere-and-allison-mack/1159493630 |title=Trial date set for Keith Raniere and Allison Mack |work=Albany News 10 |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> In late May, authorities moved to seize two NXIVM-owned properties near Albany.<ref>{{cite web |title=Foreclosure Complaint Reveals NXIVM Sex Cult Rituals In Upstate New York |date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 29, 2018 |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2018/05/24/nxivm-sex-cult-foreclose-halfmoon}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, the ''[[New York Post]]'' reported that NXIVM had moved to [[Brooklyn, New York]] and was being led by Clare Bronfman.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2018/04/21/sex-cult-moves-to-brooklyn-and-is-ready-for-war/ |title='Sex cult' moves to Brooklyn \u2014 and is ready for 'war' |first=Laura |last=Italiano |date=April 21, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> On June 12, 2018, the ''Times Union'' reported that NXIVM had suspended its operations due to \"extraordinary circumstances facing the company\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-suspends-all-operations-12987928.php |title=NXIVM suspends all operations; founder's bail denied |first1=Steve |last1=Hughes |first2=The Associated |last2=Press |date=June 12, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Bronfman was arrested on July 24 and charged with [[racketeering]]. She was released to house arrest after signing a $100 million [[bail bond]]. Also arrested and charged with the same crime were NXIVM President Nancy Salzman; her daughter, Lauren Salzman; and another NXIVM employee, Kathy Russell.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4350140/clare-bronfman-seagrams-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult/ |title=Clare Bronfman, Seagram's heiress, arrested in Nxivm sex-trafficking case |website=globalnews.ca |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/nxivm-bronfman-sex-cult-racketeering-1.4759640 |title=Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM Bronfman and five others accused of racketeering related to operations of a cult-like pyramid group |last=Proctor |first=Jason |date=July 24, 2018 |website=CBC |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2019, Nancy Salzman pleaded guilty to a charge of racketeering criminal conspiracy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-crime-cult-idUSKCN1QU2Z2 |title=Self-help guru Raniere faces U.S. child porn charges; associate pleads guilty |last=Brendan |first=Pierson |date=March 13, 2019 |work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=March 14, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/03/13/nxivm-co-founder-nancy-salzman-pleads-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Nxivm co-founder Nancy Salzman pleads guilty in sex cult case |last=Saul |first=Emily |date=March 13, 2019 |website=[[New York Post]] |language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-nxivm-case-smallville-actress-possible-plea-negotiations-keith-raniere-pleads-not-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Leader of alleged NXIVM sex cult pleads not guilty to child porn charges |website=www.cbsnews.com |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> Also in March 2019, Lauren Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering and racketeering conspiracy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Daughter-of-NXIVM-leader-pleads-guilty-13725939.php |title=Daughter of NXIVM leader pleads guilty |first1=Brendan J. |last1=Lyons |first2=Mike |last2=Goodwin |date=March 29, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> On April 8, 2019, Mack pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/apr/08/allison-mack-nxivm-pleads-guilty-racketeering-charges |title=Smallville star Allison Mack pleads guilty to racketeering in Nxivm case |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 8, 2019 |accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to charges of [[Illegal immigration to the United States|harboring an alien]] and [[identity fraud]]; bookkeeper Russell also pleaded guilty to [[visa fraud]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/nyregion/nxivm-clare-bronfman.html |title=Clare Bronfman Pleads Guilty in Nxivm 'Sex Cult' Case, Leaving Leader to Stand Trial Alone |last=Meier |first=Barry |date=April 19, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=April 20, 2019 |last2=Moynihan |first2=Colin |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nRaniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706/|title=Video Center|website=NEWS10 ABC}}</ref> On June 19, 2019, he was convicted of racketeering and sex trafficking.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, a federal lawsuit was filed in New York accusing Raniere and 14 associates of conducting illegal psychological experiments on members of the company and abusing them physically, emotionally and financially.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/29/us/nxivm-lawsuit-experiments-abuse/index.html|title=Nxivm leadership accused of illegal psychological experiments and systematic abuse in federal lawsuit|author1=Giulia McDonnell Nieto del Rio |author2=Madeline Holcombe |author3=Rob Frehse|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n\n==Beliefs and practices==\n[[File:US v. Raniere GovtExhibit GX46.JPG|right|upright=0.7|thumb|NXIVM founder Keith Raniere]]\nIn NXIVM classes, rank was signified by the wearing of colored sashes, similar to belts used in various martial arts.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/the-stripe-path-how-to-make-your-way-up-in-nxivm-1.4674369</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a 12-point \"Mission Statement\", which participants recited, pledging to \"purge\" themselves \"of all parasite and envy-based habits\", to enroll others in such courses, and to \"ethically control as much of the money, wealth and resources of the world as possible within my success plan\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/09/nyregion/nxivm-cult-trial.html |title=Former Sex Cult Official Describes Its 'Evil' Inner Workings |first=Colin |last=Moynihan |date=May 9, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Photographs of Raniere and Mack were displayed during classes, which would conclude with participants showing gratitude to the two leaders.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Uncover: Escaping NXIVM |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM conducted \"Intensives\" classes for 12 hours daily for 16 days. One cited price was $7,500.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/nxivm-trial-founder-keith-raniere-was-crime-boss-posing-as-guru-feds-say |title=NXIVM Trial Opens: Feds Say Founder Keith Raniere Was 'Crime Boss,' Not Guru |first=Pilar |last=Melendez |date=May 7, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Classes were divided into modules. In one module, \"Relationship Sourcing\", students were instructed to explore the benefits they would receive in the event of a partner's sudden death. Another module, \"Dracula and his ghouls\", reportedly discussed psychopaths and their followers. Other module titles included \"Best People; Perfect World\" and \"The Heroic Struggle\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/06/15/part-1-master-ranieres-secret-teachings-what-students-learn-in-esp-intensives/ |title=Part 1: Master Raniere's secret teachings: What students learn in ESP 'Intensives'! |date=June 15, 2017 |website=Frank Report - Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a practice, termed \"exploration of meaning\" that involved senior members questioning members as they delved into their childhood memories.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/nxivm-8-things-we-learned-from-sex-cult-expose-630616/ |title=Nxivm: 8 Things We Learned from 'Sex-Cult' Expos\u00e9 |first1=Elisabeth |last1=Garber-Paul |first2=Elisabeth |last2=Garber-Paul |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM taught that some people, called \"Suppressives\", try to impede progress within NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Witness-After-leaving-NXIVM-women-became-targets-13841142.php |title=Witness: Raniere bragged of wanting to 'break' follower Allison Mack |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=May 13, 2019 |website=Times Union |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> People who irrevocably turned against Raniere were said to have undergone \"The Fall\" and were labeled, in the words of a former member, as \"Luciferians, lost people for whom bad feels good, and good feels bad.\"<ref name=\"auto5\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/06/keith-raniere-nxivm-patents-luciferian |title=How NXIVM Used a Simple Tool to Build Its \"Sex Cult\" |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM members organized \"Vanguard Week\", an annual celebration of Raniere's birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-turned-Lake-George-resort-into-annual-13836853.php |title=NXIVM turned Lake George resort into annual Raniere birthday jamboree - SFChronicle.com |date=May 10, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been associated with several related organizations. '''Jness''' was a society aimed at women, while the '''Society of Protectors''' was aimed primarily at men.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\"/> A third group was known by the acronym DOS for \"'''Dominus Obsequious Sororium'''\", a Latin phrase that reportedly translates to \"Master over Slave Women\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/feds-self-help-guru-kept-women-as-sex-slaves-branded-them-with-his-initials |title=Feds: 'Self-Help' Guru Kept Women as Sex 'Slaves,' Branded Them With His Initials |first=Tatyana |last=Bellamy-Walker |date=March 27, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref>  In 2006, Raniere founded '''Rainbow Cultural Garden''', an international chain of child-care organizations in which children were to be exposed to seven different languages.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/alejandro-sanzs-wifes-miami-school-closed-by-state-tied-to-nxivm-sex-cult-founder-10295903 |title=State Closes Midtown Miami School Tied to NXIVM \"Sex Cult\" Leader |first=Jerry |last=Iannelli |date=April 27, 2018 |website=Miami New Times}}</ref>\n\nSome members of NXIVM's inner circle were reportedly taught that, in past lives, they were high-ranking [[Nazi]]s.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Suzanna |last=Andrews |website=Vanities |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> Barbara Bouchey was reportedly the reincarnation of Holocaust architect [[Reinhard Heydrich]], while Nancy Salzmann was supposed to be the reincarnation of Hitler. Raniere reported he had been a leader of anti-Nazi partisans.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2018/04/08/adolf-hitler-herman-goering-nxivm-sex-cult-leader-raniere-told-followers-reincarnated-nazis/ |title=From Adolf Hitler to Herman Goering, NXIVM sex-cult leader Raniere told followers they were 'Reincarnated Nazis'! |date=April 9, 2018 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a complaint filed by a former NXIVM member, a medical doctor performed an experiment on her that involved recording her EEG responses while viewing footage of people being murdered.<ref name=\"auto5\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://assets.documentcloud.org/documents/4113542/Porter-Complaint.pdf|title=Porter Complaint}}</ref> Brandon P. Porter, the doctor, faced 24 professional conduct charges from the New York State Board of the [[Office of Professional Medical Conduct]], including \"moral unfitness to practice medicine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/article/NXIVM-doctor-facing-state-charges-12890993.php |title=NXIVM doctor facing state charges |first=Steve |last=Barnes |date=May 5, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://apps.health.ny.gov/pubdoh/professionals/doctors/conduct/factions/FileDownloadAction.action?finalActionId=12236&fileName=CHRG+253486.pdf&fileSeqNum=1 |title=Notice Of Hearing In The Matter Of Brandon Porter, MD |publisher=Office for Professional Medical Conduct, New York State Department of Health |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>  In August 2019, Porter's license was revoked for his role in the experiments and for his failure to report an \"unusual disease outbreak\" which occurred at NXIVM's 2016 \"V-Week\" retreat.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-doctor-who-conducted-brain-studies-loses-14370824.php |title=NXIVM doctor who conducted brain studies loses license |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/08/22/dr-brandon-porter-loses-medical-license/ |title=Dr. Brandon Porter Loses Medical License |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n==Notable members and others==\nNXIVM was founded by '''Keith Raniere''' (born August 26, 1960).<ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\"/> In March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to [[NXIVM#Media investigations|DOS]] (a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM), including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\"/><ref name=\"news10.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706 |title=NXIVM TRIAL: Prosecution's opening statements lasted 90 minutes |date=May 7, 2019 |website=WTEN}}</ref> He was found guilty of all charges at trial.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chow |first1=Andrew |title=NXIVM Leader Keith Raniere Convicted on Sex Trafficking Charges. Here Are the Major Players in the Case |url=https://time.com/5568135/nxivm-allison-mack-raniere/ |website=Time |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere met '''Nancy Salzman''', a psychiatric nurse and trained practitioner of [[Hypnosis|hypnotism]] and [[Neuro-Linguistic Programming]]. The two founded \"Executive Success Programs\", a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\"/> offering a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>  In March 2019, Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/who-nancy-salzman-nxivm-co-founders-wrongdoings-shine-through-daughter-lauren-1431652 |title=Who is Nancy Salzman? Co-founder's daughter testifies in plea deal for NXIVM wrongdoings |first=Kelly Wynne On 5/21/19 at 11:22 AM |last=EDT |date=May 21, 2019 |website=Newsweek}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Bronfman sara.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Heiress Sara Bronfman, along with her sister Clare, bankrolled the NXIVM organization beginning in 2003.]]\n\n'''[[Sara Bronfman]]''' is the daughter of billionaire Seagrams chairman Edgar Bronfman Sr.  She was introduced to NXIVM by a family friend in 2002.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> She in turn introduced her sister, '''[[Clare Bronfman]]''' to NXIVM. Clare Bronfman was arrested by federal agents on July 24, 2018, in New York City and charged with money laundering and identity theft in connection with NXIVM activities. She pleaded not guilty in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York]] in Brooklyn. She was released on $100 million bond and placed on [[house arrest]] with [[electronic monitoring]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/crime-courts/feds-arrest-seagram-heiress-bronfman-nxivm-sex-slave-case-n894136 |title=Seagram heiress Bronfman pleads not guilty in NXIVM 'sex slave' case |work=NBC News| access-date=April 20, 2019 |date=July 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to conspiracy to conceal and harbor illegal aliens for financial gain and fraudulent use of identification. She faces 21 to 27 months in prison and has agreed to forfeit $6 million.<ref name=lyons>{{cite news |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=April 20, 2019 |newspaper=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Emiliano Salinas]]''' is a venture capitalist and businessman. He is the son of former Mexican president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]].  Salinas served as vice president of Prorsus Capital, a financial consortium with ties to Raniere and NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zimmerman |first1=Amy |title=Inside the NXIVM Sex Cult\u2019s Secret Plot to Take Over Mexico |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-the-nxivm-sex-cults-secret-plot-to-take-over-mexico |website=The Daily Beast |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n[[File:Allison Mack at ComicCon 2009 NN.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actress [[Allison Mack]] pleaded guilty to racketeering charges in April 2019 and is awaiting sentencing.]]\n\n'''Karen A. Unterreiner''' is a member who became Raniere's live-in partner beginning in the 1980s, and an early employee of his company Consumers' Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Raniere-stands-alone-13795442.php |title=Raniere stands alone |date=May 4, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> \n\n'''Pam Cafritz''' was the daughter of Washington-DC socialites Buffy and William Cafritz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>  In the 1990s, she resided with Raniere and Karen Unterreiner in an Albany home.  Both Unterreiner and Cafritz signed consent agreements with prosecutors for their role in Consumer's Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/07/making-vanguard-proud-the-mays-men-bring-executive-success-to-arkansas/ |title=Making Vanguard Proud \u2013 The Mays Men Bring Executive Success To Arkansas |date=July 7, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref> Cafritz was a founder of JNESS, the Raniere-affiliated women's group.  Cafritz was reported to be Raniere's 'most important long-term girlfriend'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>  On November 7, 2016, Pam Cafritz died.  After her death, her credit card was charged for over $300,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Ordered-to-seduce-Raniere-woman-planned-escape-13968629.php |title=Ordered to seduce Raniere, woman planned escape from NXIVM |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Allison Mack]]''' is an American actress known for her role on the series ''[[Smallville]]''. Mack was reportedly recruited to the [[Vancouver]] chapter of NXIVM, along with her ''Smallville'' co-star [[Kristin Kreuk]].<ref>{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=November 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180502001435/http://www.macleans.ca/economy/business/how-to-lose-100-million/2/ |archive-date=May 2, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>  Mack was reportedly a founder of DOS, a Raniere-affiliated Master/Slave group. Mack was arrested on April 20, 2018, on charges of [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (criminal)|conspiracy]], and [[forced labor]] conspiracy.  Mack pleaded guilty to [[racketeering]] charges in April 2019, and was to be sentenced in September 2019. However, on July 15, 2019 the Senior U.S. District Judge Nicholas Garaufis postponed the sentencing until further notice to allow federal probation officials to conduct pre-sentencing investigations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sentencing of NXIVM leader delayed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/amp/Sentencing-of-NXIVM-leader-delayed-14097454.php |newspaper=[[timesunion]]}}</ref>\n\n[[File:10.15.11NickiClyneByLuigiNovi2.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Canadian actress [[Nicki Clyne]]]]\n'''[[Nicki Clyne]]''' is a Canadian actress known for her role on the series ''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]''.  According to reports, in 2006, Clyne became involved with NXIVM. In 2008, she reportedly requested to be let out of her contract to focus full-time on NXIVM.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/11/19/nicki-clyne-quit-acting-broke-her-contract-with-battlestar-galatica-producers-to-join-nxivm-mission-full-time/ |title=Nicki Clyne quit acting, broke her contract with Battlestar Galatica{{sic|hide=y}} producers to join NXIVM mission full time |date=November 19, 2017 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n'''India Oxenberg''', daughter of actress [[Catherine Oxenberg]], was introduced to the group in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/catherine-oxenberg-on-losing-her-daughter-to-the-sex-cult-nxivm-going-public-was-a-last-resort |title=Catherine Oxenberg Reveals How She Lost Her Daughter to the Sex Cult NXIVM |first=Amy |last=Zimmerman |date=August 8, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> At Raniere's trial, a witness testified that India had spent a year on a 500-calorie-per-day diet.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/allison-mack-nxivm-trial-diet-500-calories-1443377 |title=Allison Mack reportedly forced NXIVM sex cult members to follow 500-calorie-a-day diets |first=Janice Williams On 6/11/19 at 10:42 AM |last=EDT |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Newsweek |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> In May 2017, India admitted to her mother that she was among those who had been branded.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-daughter-being-branded-nxivm/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg's Daughter Was 'Branded' with 'Cult' Leader's Initials: 'I Was Horrified' |website=PEOPLE.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> India left the group in June 2018, after Raniere's arrest.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-says-her-daughter-who-has-left-nxivm-is-moving-forward/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg Says Her Daughter Who Has Left Nxivm Is 'Moving Forward' |first1=Liz |last1=McNeil |first2=Johnny |last2=Dodd |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=August 7, 2018 |access-date=February 7, 2019}}</ref> In August 2018, Catherine Oxenberg's book ''Captive: A Mother's Crusade to Save Her Daughter from a Terrifying Cult'' was published.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.simonandschuster.com/books/Captive/Catherine-Oxenberg/9781982100650 |title=Captive |last1=Oxenberg |first1=Catherine |first2=Natasha |last2=Stoynoff |date=2018 |publisher=[[Gallery Publishing Group|Gallery Books]] |isbn=9781982100650}}</ref>\n\n===Critical former members===\n'''Toni Natalie''' met Raniere in 1991 when he was pitching his business \"Consumer's Buyline\".<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/politics/albany/2018/03/08/rochester-woman-battles-nxivm-keith-raniere/360847002/ |title=Rochester woman tells all about life with NXIVM's Keith Raniere, her ex |website=Rochester Democrat and Chronicle}}</ref> Natalie and her then-husband became top sellers for the organization.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>  Natalie recalled that she was able to stop smoking after a two-hour session with Raniere,<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> but this claim is disputed by her ex-husband.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/10/17/toni-natalies-keith-hypnotized-me-into-quitting-smoking-story-disputed-by-ex-husband-rusty/ |title=Toni Natalie's 'Keith Hypnotized Me Into Quitting Smoking' Story Disputed by Ex-Husband Rusty |last=Parlato |first=Frank |website=Frank Report |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref> Natalie and her son later moved to be near Raniere; her marriage ended shortly thereafter. Natalie and Raniere dated for the next eight years.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In the mid-90s, Raniere and Natalie operated a health-products store.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web |url=http://forbes/2003/1013/088 |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |website=Forbes}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, Raniere's eight-year relationship with Natalie ended. Natalie would subsequently claim to have been the victim of harassment.<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084744]{{dead link|date=June 2019}}</ref> In a January 2003 ruling, federal judge Robert Littlefield implied Raniere was using a legal suit to harass Natalie. Wrote Littlefield: \"This matter smacks of a jilted fellow's attempt at revenge or retaliation against his former girlfriend, with many attempts at tripping her up along the way\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.org/details/269747-natalie-jilted-boyfriend |title=Natalie Jilted Boyfriend |date=December 1, 2011 |publisher= |via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In 2011, Natalie filed documents in federal court alleging that she had been repeatedly raped by Raniere.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>\n\n'''Joseph J. O'Hara''' was an attorney who departed NXIVM in 2005 after accusing the group of misdeeds.   In 2007, O'Hara was indicted by Albany County.  It was later revealed that the District Attorney had allowed Raniere's girlfriend Kristin Keeffe to operate within its office as a sort of victims' advocate.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-pressed-district-attorney-3379748.php |title=NXIVM pressed district attorney |date=March 3, 2012}}</ref> Charges were ultimately dismissed.\n\n'''Barbara Bouchey''' was a client of Nancy Salzman, having been referred to her in 1988. Beginning in 2000, Bouchey dated Raniere. In 2009, Bouchey and eight other women (\"The NXIVM Nine\") confronted Raniere with concerns about abuse within the organization. That year, Bouchey left the group and later went to law enforcement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Guilty-plea-of-Salzman-ends-her-long-allegiance-13691433.php |title=Guilty plea ends Salzman's long allegiance to Raniere - TimesUnion.com |date=March 17, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Kristin Keeffe''' became Raniere's partner in the early 1990s.  In 2013, Keeffe gave birth to Raniere's son Gaelyn.<ref name=\"TU150920\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/tuplus-local/article/Legal-papers-NXIVM-officials-probed-finances-of-6516856.php |title=Legal papers: NXIVM officials probed finances of 6 federal judges, Senator Schumer, others |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 20, 2015 |website=Times Union}}</ref>  In February 2014, Keeffe broke with Raniere and his group. Fleeing the region with her son, an email bearing Keeffe's name explained: \"I have full sole legal custody of Gaelyn. Keith was experimenting on him. I had to get Gaelyn away\".<ref name=\"TU140511\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |title=A split from NXIVM |first=James M. |last=Odato |date=May 11, 2014 |website=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]}}</ref> Keeffe publicly described Raniere as \"dangerous\".<ref name=\"TU140511\"/>  In 2015, Keeffe alleged that NXIVM leaders had planned to lure critics to Mexico with an invitation to an anti-cult conference; once in Mexico, the critics were to be arrested on false charges by order of a judge who had been bribed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://culteducation.com/404-error-page.html |title=404 Error Page |website=culteducation.com|access-date=August 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811212201/https://www.culteducation.com/404-error-page.html|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cbc.ca\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084740 |title=TRANSCRIPT: Uncover: Escaping NXIVM - Season 1, EP 3 |work=[[CBC Radio]] |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TU151018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Records-NXIVM-hacked-billionaire-s-emails-with-6576310.php |title=Records: NXIVM hacked billionaire's emails with Hillary Clinton, world leaders |work=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=October 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Sarah Edmondson]]''' is a Canadian actress. After leaving NXIVM in early 2017, she publicly denounced the organization, claiming that she was invited into \"DOS,\" a substructure within NXIVM operated by Keith Raniere and [[Allison Mack]], and was branded with Raniere's and Mack's initials at Mack's{{Contradict-inline|reason=Two sources used here are contradictory: the Hollywood Reporter article says it was Mack's home, but the New York Times expos\u00e9 says it was Lauren Salzman's home.|date=April 2, 2020}} Albany home.<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite web |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |accessdate=May 13, 2018 |agency=ABC News |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nxivm member was branded at Allison Mack's home |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nxivm-member-was-branded-at-allison-macks-home-video-1113006 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |agency=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Edmondson showed the brand in a ''[[New York Times]]'' expos\u00e9 of NXIVM.<ref name=\"nyt\"/>\n\n'''Mark Vicente''', a filmmaker known for the 2004 film ''[[What the Bleep Do We Know!?]]'', began involvement with the group in 2005. Vicente testified against Raniere at his 2019 trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tonyortega.org/2019/05/09/filmmaker-breaks-down-describing-nxivms-duplicitous-ideas-and-evil-intent/ |title=Filmmaker breaks down describing Nxivm's duplicitous ideas and evil intent - The Underground Bunker |website=tonyortega.org |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Journalists and bloggers===\n'''James Odato''' is an investigative reporter who wrote for the Albany Times Union.  In 2012, Odato reported Raniere's history of pedophilia.   In October 2013, Odato was named in a lawsuit filed by NXIVM, along with Vanity Fair's Suzanna Andrews and blogger John J. Tighe;  all had written critically of the group.<ref name=\"politico.com\">{{Cite web |url=http://politi.co/1W2nbYE |title=Journalist on leave after tangle with secretive 'NXIVM' group |first=Joe |last=Pompeo |website=POLITICO Media}}</ref>  The suit alleged that NXIVM computers had been illegally accessed.   Shortly thereafter, Odato was described as being 'on leave' from the Times Union.<ref name=\"politico.com\"/>\n\nIn 2007, '''Frank Parlato''' was hired by NXIVM to help with publicity.  After concluding the members were being defrauded by Raniere, Parlato began blogging about the group on his sites \"ArtVoice\", \"The Niagara Falls Reporter\" and \"The Frank Report\".<ref>Vice News Tonight May 16, 2018\"</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\"/>\n\n'''John Tighe''' wrote about NXIVM on a blog.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secret-mission-A-child-589818.php |title=Secret mission: A child |first=JAMES M. ODATO Capitol |last=bureau |date=July 25, 2010 |website=Times Union}}</ref> In 2013, NXIVM accused Tighe of illegally accessing NXIVM servers using a former member's login information. Tighe's home was raided by the New York State Police, and his computer was seized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-hacking-case-to-be-tossed-6827893.php |title=NXIVM hacking case to be tossed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=February 13, 2016 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Several months later, State Police announced the discovery of child pornography on Tighe's computer; he was arrested. Facing a possible prison term of 20 years, Tighe pleaded guilty to a single count in exchange for a five-year sentence in federal prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/06/25/is-john-tighe-innocent-heres-a-few-facts-to-consider/ |title=Is John Tighe Innocent? \u2013 Here're a Few Facts to Consider |first=Is John Tighe Innocent?-Here\u2019re a Few Facts to Consider |last=says |date=June 25, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\n==Films, documentaries and books==\n* [[Investigation Discovery]] will release a two-hour special ''The Lost Women of NXIVM''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/investigation-discovery-the-lost-women-of-nxivm-1202635465/ |title='The Lost Women Of Nxivm': Investigation Discovery Explores Sex Cult In Two-Hour Special |first1=Peter |last1=White |first2=Peter |last2=White |date=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[HBO]] has announced their plans of making a docuseries about NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/nxivm-documentary-series-hbo-jehane-noujaim-karim-amer-1202060308/ |title=NXIVM Documentary Series from 'The Square' Filmmakers Coming to HBO |first1=Steve |last1=Greene |first2=Steve |last2=Greene |date=April 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hbo-plans-docuseries-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-1203073 |title=HBO Plans Docuseries on Alleged Sex Cult NXIVM |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/tv/alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-focus-hbo-documentary-series-n996196 |title=Alleged sex cult NXIVM focus of HBO documentary series |website=NBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Catherine Oxenberg]] produced a film for [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] about her daughter's experiences with NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/tv/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime/ |title=Lifetime Is Making a NXIVM Sex Cult Movie After Founder Keith Raniere's Conviction |website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime-catherine-oxenberg-peter-facinelli-star-1202637998/ |title=NXIVM Sex Cult Movie Set At Lifetime With Catherine Oxenberg Producing; Peter Facinelli & Andrea Roth To Star |first1=Denise |last1=Petski |first2=Denise |last2=Petski |date=July 1, 2019}}</ref> It is titled ''[[Escaping the NXIVM Cult: A Mother's Fight to Save Her Daughter]]'' and aired on September 21, 2019. While Catherine Oxenberg served as the narrator and executive producer, the film starred [[Andrea Roth]] as Catherine Oxenberg, [[Peter Facinelli]] as Keith Raniere, and [[Sara Fletcher]] as Allison Mack.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lifetime's Trailer For 'Escaping The NXIVM Cult' Shows Seduction And Anguish |url=https://deadline.com/video/lifetimes-trailer-for-escaping-the-nxivm-cult-shows-seduction-and-anguish/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n* \"The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM\" is an upcoming book by Toni Natalie and Chet Hardin set for release on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/28/new-book-by-toni-natalie-the-program-inside-the-mind-of-keith-raniere-and-the-rise-and-fall-of-nxivm/ |title=New Book by Toni Natalie: 'The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://www.grandcentralpublishing.com/titles/toni-natalie/the-program/9781538701034/ |title=The Program |date=March 5, 2019 |via=www.grandcentralpublishing.com}}</ref>\n* ''Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life'' by [[Sarah Edmondson]] is a book set that was released on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/07/28/scarred-the-true-story-of-how-i-escaped-nxivm-the-cult-that-bound-my-life/ |title=New Book By Sarah Edmondson 'Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n* NXIVM was the subject on an episode ''[[E! True Hollywood Story]]'' which featured interviews from several journalists and the people that were once involved with the organization including Catherine Oxenberg, Sarah Edmondson, and actor and Oxenberg's real-life friend [[Callum Blue]].1\n*[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] released a podcast in 2018 on NXIVM as part of CBC [https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/uncover-season-1-escaping-nxivm-1.4675949 Uncover Season 1].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180421090811/http://www.keithraniere.com/ Website] of [[Keith Raniere]]\n* [http://www.scs.cmu.edu/~dst/NXIVM/ Three critical articles pertaining to the ''NXIVM v. Ross Institute'' lawsuit]\n* [http://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/ ''Times Union'' Special Report on NXIVM]\n\n{{Multi-level marketing}}\n\n[[Category:1998 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Albany County, New York]]\n[[Category:Colonie, New York]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Large-group awareness training]]\n[[Category:Multi-level marketing companies]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Sexual misconduct allegations]]\n[[Category:Cults]]\n", "name_user": "2601:188:c300:2c02:69f4:2383:fab6:52e", "label": "vandal", "comment": "(Added correct information)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NXIVM"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Czechia per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by region\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Czech Republic]]\n| first_case      = Unknown\n| arrival_date    = 1 March 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days\n | month1 = 03\n | day1   = 1\n | year1  = 2020\n | month2 = \n | day2   = \n | year2  = }} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China via Italy\n| recovery_cases  = 642<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| deaths          = 161<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 6,101<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] saw its first three confirmed cases in the [[Czech Republic]] on 1 March 2020. On 12 March, the government declared a [[state of emergency]], for the first time in the country's modern history for the area of the entire country. On 16 March, the country closed its borders, forbade the entry of foreigners and issued a nationwide curfew. While originally planned until 24 March, the measures were later extended until 1 April<ref name=\"apnews\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-republic-severely-limits-freedom-of-movement-in-order-to-slow-down-coronavirus-spread|title=Czech Republic goes into quarantine to slow down coronavirus spread|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> and then again until the end of State of Emergency<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /> which was extended by the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] until 30 April 2020.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.psp.cz/eknih/2017ps/stenprot/043schuz/s043037.htm#h8 |title=P\u010cR, PS 2017 , 43. sch\u016fze, \u010d\u00e1st 37 (7. 4. 2020) |publisher=Psp.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nCzech Republic started gradual easing of measures from 7 April 2020 onwards.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /><ref name=\"sports allowed\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |date= |publisher=Government of the United Kingdom |url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |date= |website=wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/The Czech Republic medical cases chart}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:80%; float:right; clear:right; margin:0 0 0.5em 1em;\"\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in the Czech Republic<ref name=\":0\"/>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Date\n! colspan=\"2\" | Confirmed\n! colspan=\"2\" | Recovered\n! colspan=\"2\" | Deaths\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Active<br / >cases\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Tested<br/>(Total)\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Detected<br/>ratio\n|-\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n|-\n! 28 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 193\n| \n|-\n! 29 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 200\n| \n|-\n! 1 March\n| 3 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 211\n| {{#expr:3/(211-200)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 