{"title_page": "Endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitor", "text_new": "'''Endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors''' ('''eCBRIs'''), also called '''cannabinoid reuptake inhibitors''' ('''CBRIs'''), are [[drug]]s which limit the reabsorption of [[endocannabinoid]] [[neurotransmitters]] by the releasing neuron.<ref name=\"pmid23236415\" /><ref name=\"pmid16770320\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Costa B, Siniscalco D, Trovato AE, Comelli F, Sotgiu ML, Colleoni M, Maione S, Rossi F, Giagnoni G | title = AM404, an inhibitor of anandamide uptake, prevents pain behaviour and modulates cytokine and apoptotic pathways in a rat model of neuropathic pain | journal = Br. J. Pharmacol. | volume = 148 | issue = 7 | pages = 1022\u201332 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16770320 | pmc = 1751928 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0706798 | url = }}</ref>\n\n==Pharmacology==\nEndocannabinoid uptake inhibitors that bind to [[fatty acid-binding proteins]] (FABPs) have been described.<ref name=\"pmid23236415\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Berger WT, Ralph BP, Kaczocha M, Sun J, Balius TE, Rizzo RC, Haj-Dahmane S, Ojima I, Deutsch DG | title = Targeting fatty acid binding protein (FABP) anandamide transporters - a novel strategy for development of anti-inflammatory and anti-nociceptive drugs | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 7 | issue = 12 | pages = e50968 | year = 2012 | pmid = 23236415 | pmc = 3517626 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0050968 | url = }}</ref> The inhibition of endocannabinoid reuptake raises the amount of those neurotransmitters available in the [[synaptic cleft]] and therefore increases [[neurotransmission]]. Following the increase of neurotransmission in the endocannabinoid system is the stimulation of its functions which, in humans, include: suppression of [[pain perception]] (analgesia), increased [[appetite]], [[Mood (psychology)|mood]] elevation and inhibition of short-term [[memory]].\n\n==Examples of eCBRIs==\n* [[AM404]]<ref name=\"pmid16770320\" />\n* [[AM1172]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Glaser ST, Kaczocha M, Deutsch DG | date = Aug 2005 | title = Anandamide transport: a critical review | url = | journal = Life Sci | volume = 77 | issue = 14| pages = 1584\u2013604 | pmid = 15979096 | doi = 10.1016/j.lfs.2005.05.007 }}</ref>\n* [[LY-2183240]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Moore SA, Nomikos GG, Dickason-Chesterfield AK, Schober DA, Schaus JM, Ying BP, Xu YC, Phebus L, Simmons RM, Li D, Iyengar S, Felder CC | year = 2005| title = ''Identification of a high-affinity binding site involved in the transport of endocannabinoids.'' | journal = [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] | volume =  102| issue = | pages =  17852\u20137| doi = 10.1073/pnas.0507470102 | pmid = 16314570 | pmc = 1295594 }}</ref> \n* [[O-2093]]\n* [[OMDM-2]]\n* [[UCM-707]]\n* [[VDM-11]]\n* [[Guineensine]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Nicolussi S, Viveros-Paredes JM, Gachet MS, Rau M, Flores-Soto ME, Blunder M, Gertsch J | date = Feb 2014 | title = Guineensine is a novel inhibitor of endocannabinoid uptake showing cannabimimetic behavioral effects in BALB/c mice | url = | journal = Pharmacol Res. | volume = 80 | issue = | pages = 52\u201365 | pmid = 24412246 | doi = 10.1016/j.phrs.2013.12.010 }}</ref>\n*[[WOBE437 and RX-055]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Chicca A, Nicolussi S, Bartholom\u00e4us R, Blunder M, Aparisi Rey A, Petrucci V, Reynoso-Moreno ID, Viveros-Paredes JM, Dalghi Gens M, Lutz B, Schi\u00f6th HB, Soeberdt M, Abels C, Charles RP, Altmann KH, Gertsch J | year = 2017| title = Chemical probes to potently and selectively inhibit endocannabinoid cellular reuptake | journal = Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A | volume = 55 | issue = 25| page = 555 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.1704065114 | pmid = 28584105 | pmc = 5488949 }}</ref><ref>Nicolussi S, Chicca A, Soeberdt M, Abels C, Viveros.Paredes JM, Aparisi-Rey A, Lutz B, Gertsch J. WOBE437 - Prototype of a novel class of potent, selective endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors. BPS 6th Eur Workshop on Cannabinoid Research 2013.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Endocannabinoid enhancer]]\n* [[Endocannabinoid system]]\n* [[Reuptake inhibitor]]\n* [[Cannabinoid receptor antagonist]]\n* [[Endocannabinoid transporters]]\n* [[FAAH inhibitor]]\n* [[MAGL inhibitor]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Cannabinoidergics}}\n\n[[Category:Neurochemistry]]\n[[Category:Cannabinoids]]\n[[Category:Endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors]]\n", "text_old": "'''Endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors''' ('''eCBRIs'''), also called '''cannabinoid reuptake inhibitors''' ('''CBRIs'''), are [[drug]]s which limit the reabsorption of [[endocannabinoid]] [[neurotransmitters]] by the releasing neuron.<ref name=\"pmid23236415\" /><ref name=\"pmid16770320\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Costa B, Siniscalco D, Trovato AE, Comelli F, Sotgiu ML, Colleoni M, Maione S, Rossi F, Giagnoni G | title = AM404, an inhibitor of anandamide uptake, prevents pain behaviour and modulates cytokine and apoptotic pathways in a rat model of neuropathic pain | journal = Br. J. Pharmacol. | volume = 148 | issue = 7 | pages = 1022\u201332 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16770320 | pmc = 1751928 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0706798 | url = }}</ref>\n\n==Pharmacology==\nEndocannabinoid uptake inhibitors that bind to [[fatty acid-binding proteins]] (FABPs) have been described.<ref name=\"pmid23236415\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Berger WT, Ralph BP, Kaczocha M, Sun J, Balius TE, Rizzo RC, Haj-Dahmane S, Ojima I, Deutsch DG | title = Targeting fatty acid binding protein (FABP) anandamide transporters - a novel strategy for development of anti-inflammatory and anti-nociceptive drugs | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 7 | issue = 12 | pages = e50968 | year = 2012 | pmid = 23236415 | pmc = 3517626 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0050968 | url = }}</ref> The inhibition of endocannabinoid reuptake raises the amount of those neurotransmitters available in the [[synaptic cleft]] and therefore increases [[neurotransmission]]. Following the increase of neurotransmission in the endocannabinoid system is the stimulation of its functions which, in humans, include: suppression of [[pain perception]] (analgesia), increased [[appetite]], [[Mood (psychology)|mood]] elevation and inhibition of short-term [[memory]].\n\n==Examples of eCBRIs==\n* [[AM404]]<ref name=\"pmid16770320\" />\n* [[AM1172]]<ref>Glaser ST, Kaczocha M, Deutsch DG. Anandamide transport: a critical review. ''Life Sci''. 2005 Aug 19;77(14):1584-604. {{PMID|15979096}}</ref>\n* [[LY-2183240]]<ref>S. A. Moore, G. G. Nomikos, A. K. Dickason-Chesterfield, D. A. Schober, J. M. Schaus, B. P. Ying, Y. C. Xu, L. Phebus, R. M. Simmons, D. Li, S. Iyengar, C. C. Felder: ''Identification of a high-affinity binding site involved in the transport of endocannabinoids.'' In: ''[[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]].'' Band 102, Nummer 49, Dezember 2005, S.&nbsp;17852\u201317857, {{DOI|10.1073/pnas.0507470102}}, {{PMID|16314570}}, {{PMC|1295594}}.</ref> \n* [[O-2093]]\n* [[OMDM-2]]\n* [[UCM-707]]\n* [[VDM-11]]\n* [[Guineensine]]<ref>Nicolussi S, Viveros-Paredes JM, Gachet MS, Rau M, Flores-Soto ME, Blunder M, Gertsch J. Guineensine is a novel inhibitor of endocannabinoid uptake showing cannabimimetic behavioral effects in BALB/c mice. Pharmacol Res. 2014 Feb;80:52-65. {{PMID|24412246}}</ref>\n*[[WOBE437 and RX-055]]<ref>Chicca A, Nicolussi S, Bartholom\u00e4us R, Blunder M, Aparisi Rey A, Petrucci V, Reynoso-Moreno IDC, Viveros-Paredes JM, Dalghi Gens M, Lutz B, Schi\u00f6th HB, Soeberdt M, Abels C, Charles RP, Altmann KH, Gertsch J. Chemical probes to potently and selectively inhibit endocannabinoid cellular reuptake.Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 2017 Jun 5. {{doi| 10.1073/pnas.1704065114}}. {{PMID|28584105}}</ref><ref>Nicolussi S, Chicca A, Soeberdt M, Abels C, Viveros.Paredes JM, Aparisi-Rey A, Lutz B, Gertsch J. WOBE437 - Prototype of a novel class of potent, selective endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors. BPS 6th Eur Workshop on Cannabinoid Research 2013.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Endocannabinoid enhancer]]\n* [[Endocannabinoid system]]\n* [[Reuptake inhibitor]]\n* [[Cannabinoid receptor antagonist]]\n* [[Endocannabinoid transporters]]\n* [[FAAH inhibitor]]\n* [[MAGL inhibitor]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Cannabinoidergics}}\n\n[[Category:Neurochemistry]]\n[[Category:Cannabinoids]]\n[[Category:Endocannabinoid reuptake inhibitors]]\n", "name_user": "Rjwilmsi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExamples of eCBRIs:Journal cites:, added 1 DOI, templated 1 journal cites", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocannabinoid_reuptake_inhibitor"}
{"title_page": "London 1 South", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox rugby league football competition\n|name = London 1 South\n|current_season = 2019\u201320 London 1 South\n|logo = England Rugby text logo.svg\n|sport = [[Rugby union]]\n|teams = 14\n|country = {{ENG}}\n|champion = [[Sevenoaks RFC|Sevenoaks]] (1st title)\n|season = 2018\u201319)<br>(promoted to [[London & South East Premier]] \n|most_champs = [[Basingstoke RFC|Basingstoke]], [[Camberley RFC|Camberley]], [[Canterbury RFC|Canterbury]], [[Haywards Heath RFC|Haywards Heath]], [[Sutton & Epsom RFC|Sutton & Epsom]], [[Gravesend RFC|Gravesend]]\n|count = 2\n|website = [https://archive.is/20131008012109/http://clubs.rfu.com/Fixtures/MatchByDivision.aspx?DivID=188172233 clubs.rfu.com]\n}}\n\n'''London 1 South''' is an English level 6 [[rugby union]] regional league for rugby clubs in [[London]] and the south-east of [[England]] including sides from [[East Sussex]], south [[Essex]], south [[Greater London]], [[Hampshire]], [[Kent]], [[Surrey]] and [[West Sussex]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sussex Rugby Union |title=League Make up |url=http://www.sussexrugby.co.uk/dyn/pages/competitions/league-results/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112130757/http://www.sussexrugby.co.uk/dyn/pages/competitions/league-results |archivedate=12 January 2010 }}</ref> It is the feeder league for [[London & South East Premier]] into which the champion team each season is promoted. The second-placed team enters a play-off against the runner-up of [[London 1 North]]. Three teams are relegated into a mixture of [[London 2 South East]] and [[London 2 South West]]. \n\n==Structure and format==\nThe fourteen teams play home and away matches from September through to April, making a total of twenty-six matches each. The results of the matches contribute points to the league as follows:\n*    4 points are awarded for a win\n*    2 points are awarded for a draw\n*    0 points are awarded for a loss, however\n*    1 losing (bonus) point is awarded to a team that loses a match by 7 points or fewer\n*    1 additional (bonus) point is awarded to a team scoring 4 tries or more in a match\n\nThere is one automatic promotion place, one play-off place for promotion and (usually) three relegation places. The first-placed team at the end of season wins promotion to [[London & South East Premier]] while the runner-up plays the second-placed team from [[London 1 North]], with the winner also being promoted. The last three placed clubs are usually relegated to either [[London 2 South East]] or [[London 2 South West]] depending on location.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gms.rfu.com/Gateway/CompetitionDetail.aspx?GroupID=10664 |title=Competition Details |publisher=RFU |date=2016-04-23 |accessdate=2016-06-10}}</ref>\n\n==Teams 2019\u201320==\n\n{{col-begin|width=100%}}\n{{col-break|width=80%}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=100%\n|-\n!|Team\n!|Ground\n!|Capacity\n!|City/Area\n!|Previous season\n|-\n| [[Beckenham Rugby Football Club|Beckenham]] || Balmoral Avenue || || [[Beckenham]], [[London]] || Promoted from [[London 2 South East|London 2 SE]] (champions)\t\n|-\n| [[Belsize Park RFC|Belsize Park]] || [[Regent's Park]] || || [[Belsize Park]], [[London]] || Promoted from [[London 2 North West|London 2 NW]] (champions){{#tag:ref|Likely level transfer from [[London 2 North West]] - this may change.|group=a}}\n|-\n| Camberley || Watchetts Recreation Ground || || [[Camberley]], [[Surrey]] || 3rd\n|-\n| [[Chichester RFC|Chichester]] || Oaklands Park || || [[Chichester]], [[West Sussex]] || 9th\n|-\n| [[Cobham RFC|Cobham]] || Old Surbitonians Memorial Ground || || [[Cobham, Surrey|Cobham]], [[Surrey]] || 10th\n|-\n| Dartfordians || Bourne Road || || [[Bexley]], [[London]] || 11th\n|-\n| H.A.C. || [[Artillery Ground]] || || [[Finsbury]], [[London]] || Level transfer from [[London 1 North]] (5th){{#tag:ref|Likely level transfer from