end RFC|Gravesend]]</div>|position=right}}   \n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=50.8518324|long=-.9847132|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Havant RFC|Havant]]</div>|position=left}}  \n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.4363785|long=-0.2516100|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[London Cornish RFC|L Cornish]]</div>|position=left}}\n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.268126|long=0.5326844|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Maidstone FC|Maidstone]]</div>|position=right}} \n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.3746569|long=0.4939288|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Medway RFC|Medway]]</div>|position=left}} \n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.449445|long=0.0134430|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Old Colfeians|O Colfeians]]</div>|position=top}}\n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.2738095|long=0.1953513|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Sevenoaks RFC|Sevenoaks]]</div>|position=bottom}}\n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=50.9214038|long=-1.5091093|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Tottonians RFC|Tottonians]]</div>|position=right}}\n{{location map~|UK England Southeast|lat=51.4984207|long=0.3476118|label=<div style=\"font-size:70%;\">[[Thurrock Rugby Football Club|Thurrock]]</div>|position=right}}\n}}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==2016\u201317==\n[[Sutton & Epsom RFC|Sutton & Epsom]],  the current champions were promoted to [[National League 3 London & SE|National 3 London & South East]] for the 2016\u201317 season, while the second-placed team, [[Guildford Rugby Football Club|Guildford]] beat [[Tring Rugby|Tring]], the runner-up from [[London 1 North]], in a play-off for the second promotion place. [[Twickenham RFC|Twickenham]] and [[Charlton Park Rugby Football Club|Charlton Park]] are relegated. Medway were also relegated despite finishing third due to an RFU punishment for incorrect registration of, and illegal payments to, players<ref name=medway>{{cite web|last=Cawdell |first=Luke |url=http://www.kentonline.co.uk/medway/sport/medway-punishment-reduced-93865/ |title=Medway rugby club receive a reduction in their punishment from the RFU |publisher=Kent Online |date=2016-04-07 |accessdate=2016-06-10}}</ref> thus granting a reprieve from relegation for [[Gosport and Fareham R.F.C.|Gosport and Fareham]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/rugby/gosport-fareham-rfc/long-serving-sumo-bids-farewell-to-gosport-fareham-1-7342743 |title=Long-serving \u2018Sumo\u2019 bids farewell to Gosport & Fareham |newspaper=Portsmouth News |date=2016-04-22 |accessdate=2016-06-10}}</ref>\n\nThey were replaced by [[Gravesend RFC|Gravesend]] who were relegated from National 3 London & SE. Promoted into the league were national RFU Intermediate Cup champions and unbeaten league winners of London 2 South East, [[Tunbridge Wells RFC|Tunbridge Wells]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Garrett |first=Glenn |url=http://www.courier.co.uk/LIVE-Tunbridge-Wells-v-St-Benedict-s-pre-match/story-29242616-detail/story.html |title=RECAP! Tunbridge Wells v St Benedict's \u2013 Wells put on a masterclass at Twickenham |publisher=Kent and Sussex Courier |date=2016-05-07 |accessdate=2016-06-10 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> as well as Cobham as champions of London 2 South West and play-off winners Sevenoaks.<ref name=fix>{{cite journal|url=http://rfulondon.com/16fix/l1s.pdf |title=London 1 South fixtures 2016\u201317 |publisher=RFU |date= |accessdate=2016-06-10}}</ref> CS Rugby 1863 were transferred from London 1 North because they were the most southern team in London 1 North due of an imbalace in North and South teams in the leagues.<ref name=fix />\n\n===Participating teams and locations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=50%\n|-\n!|Team\n!|Ground\n!|City/Area\n!|Previous season\n|-\n| [[Brighton Football Club (RFU)|Brighton]] || Waterhall || [[Brighton]], [[East Sussex]] || 5th\n|-\n| Chiswick || Dukes Meadows || [[Chiswick]], [[London Borough of Hounslow|Hounslow]], [[London]] || 10th\n|-\n| [[Chobham Rugby Football Club|Chobham]] || Fowlers Wells || [[Chobham]], [[Surrey]] || 8th\n|- \n| [[Cobham RFC|Cobham]] || Old Surbitonians Memorial Ground || [[Cobham, Surrey|Cobham]], Surrey || promoted from [[London 2 South West]] as champions\n|-\n| [[CS Rugby 1863]] || King's House Sports Ground || [[Chiswick]], London || level transferred from [[London 1 North]]\n|-\n| Dover || [[Crabble Athletic Ground]] || [[Dover]], [[Kent]] || 11th\n|-\n| [[Gosport and Fareham R.F.C.|Gosport & Fareham]] || Gosport Park || [[Gosport]], [[Hampshire]] || 12th\n|-\n| Gravesend || Donald Biggs Drive || [[Gravesend]], Kent || relegated from [[National League 3 London & SE]]\n|-\n| [[Havant RFC|Havant]] || Hook's Lane || [[Havant]], Hampshire || 9th\n|-\n| [[Maidstone FC|Maidstone]] || William Day Memorial Ground || [[Maidstone]], Kent || 6th\n|-\n| [[Sevenoaks RFC|Sevenoaks]] || Knole Paddock || [[Sevenoaks]], Kent || promoted from [[London 2 South East]] via play-off\n|-\n| Sidcup || Crescent Farm || [[Sidcup]], Kent || 4th\n|-\n| Tottonians || Water Lane || [[Totton and Eling|Totton]], Hampshire || 7th\n|-\n| [[Tunbridge Wells RFC|Tunbridge Wells]] || St Marks Recreation Ground || [[Royal Tunbridge Wells]], Kent || promoted from [[London 2 South East]] as champions\n|}\n\n==2015\u201316==\n\n===Participating teams and locations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=50%\n|-\n!|Team\n!|Ground\n!|City/Area\n!|Previous season\n|-\n| [[Brighton Football Club (RFU)|Brighton]] || Waterhall || [[Brighton]], [[East Sussex]] || 6th\n|-\n| [[Charlton Park Rugby Football Club|Charlton Park]] || Broad Walk || [[Kidbrooke]], [[London]] || 8th\n|-\n| Chiswick || Dukes Meadows || [[Chiswick]], London || promoted from [[London 2 North West]] via play-off\n|-\n| [[Chobham Rugby Football Club|Chobham]] || Fowlers Wells || [[Chobham]], [[Surrey]] || 2nd\n|-\n| Dover || Crabble Athletic Ground || [[Dover]], [[Kent]] || 10th\n|-\n|